  <book code="MAT" style="id">- Akawaio NT [ake] - Guyana 2010 (DBL 2015)</book>
  <para style="h">MAꞌSIU</para>
  <para style="toc1">Sises Ekareei Maꞌsiu Nʉmenukaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="toc2">Maꞌsiu</para>
  <para style="toc3">Ms</para>
  <para style="mt2">Sises Ekareei</para>
  <para style="mt1">Maꞌsiu</para>
  <para style="mt2">Nʉmenukaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="imt">Ekamanin</para>
  <para style="ip">
    <char style="bk">Sises Ekareei Maꞌsiu Nʉmenukaꞌpʉ</char> esi wakʉ itekare, Sises esi ekamasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ, pikaꞌtɨnin pe, pʉse rɨ esi Papa uya tʉmunkɨ amʉꞌ auroꞌkaꞌpʉ Penaroꞌ Ekonekan Nɨtoꞌ yau, ikuꞌtoꞌ pe tʉuya tukaiꞌ isauroꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ aꞌkuꞌtɨnin pe. Serɨ wakʉ itekare esi, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ rɨken iwanoꞌ pen nɨ, iꞌkoroꞌtau Sises entuꞌpʉ, ukoꞌmamʉꞌpʉ naꞌneꞌ rʉꞌsan, eꞌtane tanporon kon iwanoꞌ rɨ.</para>
  <para style="ip">
    <char style="bk">Maꞌsiu</char> uya kuru ikonekasaꞌ mɨrɨ wakʉ pe. Iyeꞌsaraꞌtɨsaꞌ Sises entuꞌpʉ pɨꞌ, iyepaꞌtaisimaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Makoi esiꞌpʉ iꞌtupɨtʉ pɨꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itekare ekama pɨꞌ, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enupa pɨꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ epiꞌtɨ pɨꞌ iyeꞌtʉrawasomaꞌpʉ Kiyarari po rɨ.</para>
  <para style="ip">Mɨrɨ tʉpo, Sises utɨꞌpʉ Kiyarari ponsiꞌkɨ Surusiran pona, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyeꞌkuꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ ton, Sises ukoꞌmantoꞌ uꞌmatʉ winɨkʉiꞌ, kurusuꞌ pona ipokapɨtʉꞌpʉ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyeꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ pokon pe rɨ.</para>
  <para style="ip">Serɨ wakʉ itekare uya Sises esi eke kuru rɨ Tiꞌsa pe ta, meruntɨ pe rɨ iyesi Papa Maimu enpoikanin pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe pɨꞌ enupanin. Enupan nɨtoꞌ iya amʉrasaꞌ mɨrɨ, 5 kaisaron ipɨꞌ usenupan nɨtoꞌ ton pe: (1) Wʉꞌ ponsiꞌkɨ inekamaꞌpʉ itekare, eꞌnɨtoꞌ eseru, tʉkuꞌsen, ikuꞌtoꞌ ike, Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yaꞌ tʉutɨsan pataꞌseꞌ (5–7 airɨ); (2) 12 kaisaron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton auroꞌkaꞌpʉ iya rʉꞌpʉ toꞌ ennoko tʉuya aꞌtai (10 airɨ); (3) Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe pantomʉ ton (13 airɨ); (4) Enupan nɨtoꞌ ɨꞌrɨ ta eꞌkwa pe ipoitorʉ pe eꞌnɨ esi tawon (18 airɨ); (5) Enupan nɨtoꞌ, pata weyu uꞌmaꞌtoꞌ pɨꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe weyu eꞌsepotoꞌ pɨꞌ (24–25 airɨ).</para>
  <para style="iot">Iyawon Ekamanin</para>
  <para style="io1">Sises Kʉrai tamokori ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyentuꞌpʉ (1:1–2:23)</para>
  <para style="io1">Isaan Paꞌtes eꞌtʉrawasomaꞌpʉ (3:1-12)</para>
  <para style="io1">Sises epaꞌtaisimaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Makoi uya iꞌtupɨtʉꞌpʉ (3:13–4:11)</para>
  <para style="io1">Kiyarari po annau Sises eꞌtʉrawasomaꞌpʉ (4:12–18:35)</para>
  <para style="io1">Kiyarari ponsiꞌkɨ Surusiran pona (19:1–20:34)</para>
  <para style="io1">Ikoꞌmantoꞌ uꞌmatʉ Surusiran piyau mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyau si (21:1–27:66)</para>
  <para style="io1">Itepuru eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkasaꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ isenpoikapɨtʉ (28:1-20)</para>
  <chapter number="1" style="c" sid="MAT 1" />
  <para style="s1">Sises Tamokori Ton Eseꞌ Asiꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 3:23-38">Ʉruꞌ 3:23-38</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 1:1" />Serɨ serɨ Sises Kʉrai tamokori ton eseꞌ asiꞌ, kin pe teꞌsen Tepiꞌ pa pe iyesiꞌpʉ, Epʉraꞌan pa pe nɨrɨ kanan teꞌsen.<verse eid="MAT 1:1" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 1:2" />Epʉraꞌan esiꞌpʉ Aisiꞌ kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:2">Aisiꞌ esiꞌpʉ Sekoꞌ kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:2">Sekoꞌ esiꞌpʉ Isuta mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyakon non kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:2" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 1:3" />Isuta esiꞌpʉ Peres mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Sera pokon kʉipʉnʉ pe, Temarʉ esiꞌpʉ naꞌneꞌ toꞌ san pe.</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:3">Peres esiꞌpʉ Esuran kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:3">Esuran esiꞌpʉ Ran kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:3" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 1:4" />Ran esiꞌpʉ Aminatapu kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:4">Aminatapu esiꞌpʉ Naisan kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:4">Naisan esiꞌpʉ Sarʉman kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:4" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 1:5" />Sarʉman esiꞌpʉ Powas kʉipʉnʉ pe, Reyapu esiꞌpʉ naꞌneꞌ isan pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:5">Powas esiꞌpʉ Opeꞌ kʉipʉnʉ pe, Ruꞌ esiꞌpʉ naꞌneꞌ isan pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:5">Opeꞌ esiꞌpʉ Iseꞌsi kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:5" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 1:6" />Iseꞌsi nin si esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ Tepiꞌ kin pe teꞌsen kʉipʉnʉ pe.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 1:6">Tepiꞌ esiꞌpʉ Saraman kʉipʉnʉ pe, Iuraya noꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ esiꞌpʉ naꞌneꞌ isan pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:6" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 1:7" />Saraman esiꞌpʉ Reyopowan kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:7">Reyopowan esiꞌpʉ Apaya kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:7">Apaya esiꞌpʉ Esa kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:7" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 1:8" />Esa esiꞌpʉ Iseyosapaꞌ kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:8">Iseyosapaꞌ esiꞌpʉ Iseyoran kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:8">Iseyoran esiꞌpʉ Usaya kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:8" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 1:9" />Usaya esiꞌpʉ Isoꞌtan kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:9">Isoꞌtan esiꞌpʉ Eyas kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:9">Eyas esiꞌpʉ Esiꞌkaya kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:9" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 1:10" />Esiꞌkaya esiꞌpʉ Manaꞌse kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:10">Manaꞌsa esiꞌpʉ Eman kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:10">Eman esiꞌpʉ Isoꞌsaya kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:10" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 1:11" />Isoꞌsaya esiꞌpʉ Iseꞌkonaya mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyakon non kʉipʉnʉ pe. Toꞌ eyaton non uya Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ aꞌsisaꞌ arɨ aꞌtaiꞌne Paperan pona.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1:11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2KI 24:14-15">2 Kin Amʉꞌ 24:14-15</ref>; <ref loc="2CH 36:10">2 Kʉronoꞌkʉrʉs 36:10</ref>; <ref loc="JER 27:20">Iseremaya 27:20</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 1:11" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 1:12" />Paperan pona Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ aꞌsisaꞌ asaꞌ toꞌ eyaton non uya aꞌtai:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:12">Iseꞌkonaya esiꞌpʉ Siyaꞌtiyerʉ kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:12">Siyaꞌtiyerʉ esiꞌpʉ Userupaperʉ kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:12" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 1:13" />Userupaperʉ esiꞌpʉ Apaiyutʉ kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:13">Apaiyutʉ esiꞌpʉ Iraiyaꞌkin kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:13">Iraiyaꞌkin esiꞌpʉ Esorʉ kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:13" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 1:14" />Esorʉ esiꞌpʉ Isatoꞌ kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:14">Isatoꞌ esiꞌpʉ Aꞌkin kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:14">Aꞌkin esiꞌpʉ Iraiyutʉ kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:14" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 1:15" />Iraiyutʉ esiꞌpʉ Eriyesarʉ kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:15">Eriyesarʉ esiꞌpʉ Maꞌtan kʉipʉnʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 1:15">Maꞌtan esiꞌpʉ Sekoꞌ kʉipʉnʉ pe,<verse eid="MAT 1:15" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 1:16" />Sekoꞌ esiꞌpʉ Isoseꞌ kʉipʉnʉ pe, Meri taanꞌpʉ si. Meri esiꞌpʉ Sises san pe, Kʉrai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1:16 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(Kiriꞌ maimu yau); mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(Ipuru maimu yau), asaꞌrɨ rɨ marɨ iyesi, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe. Apʉne, v. 17-18 enkɨ.</char></note> tatoꞌ san pe si.<verse eid="MAT 1:16" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 1:17" />Epʉraꞌan awonsiꞌkɨ Tepiꞌ, kin pe teꞌsen pʉꞌkʉ pona, 14 kaisa rɨ itamokori ton uꞌtɨsaꞌ esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ. Tepiꞌ, kin pe teꞌsen awonsiꞌkɨ, toꞌ eyaton non uya Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ aꞌsisaꞌ arɨ Paperan pona pʉꞌkʉ pona, 14 kaisa rɨ itamokori ton uꞌtɨsaꞌ esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ. Toꞌ eyaton non uya Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ aꞌsisaꞌ arɨꞌpʉ Paperan pona awonsiꞌkɨ, Kʉrai entu pʉꞌkʉ pona, 14 kaisa rɨ itamokori ton uꞌtɨsaꞌ esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 1:17" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Kʉrai Entuꞌpʉ Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 2:1-7">Ʉruꞌ 2:1-7</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 1:18" />Serɨ serɨ, Sises Kʉrai entuꞌpʉ pantomʉ: Isanon pe teꞌton kon, Meri, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Isoseꞌ pokon usauroꞌsaꞌ esiꞌpʉ temariꞌmatoꞌ kon pe, eꞌtane toꞌ utaꞌpɨtʉ rawɨrɨ rɨ, tʉumonoꞌtasaꞌ iꞌtuꞌpʉ Meri uya, Wakʉ Aꞌkwarʉ winɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1:18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 1:27">Ʉruꞌ 1:27</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 1:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 1:19" />Isoseꞌ esiꞌpʉ ipokenaꞌ pe teꞌsen, mɨrɨpan ekonekaꞌpʉ amaꞌai imariꞌmatoꞌ tʉuya ereutanʉꞌtoꞌ pe tʉuya.<verse eid="MAT 1:19" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 1:20" />Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ isenuminkaꞌpʉ tʉpo, Papa inserʉʉi uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ iyeꞌneꞌpɨtʉ yau, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Isoseꞌ, Tepiꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ, tenariꞌnʉnse pʉra Meri anʉnkɨ ɨnoꞌpʉ pe, apʉne pʉra Wakʉ Aꞌkwarʉ winɨ imonoꞌtasaꞌ mɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 1:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 1:21" />Warawoꞌ pe entunʉꞌtoꞌ iya oton, imʉre meseꞌtɨiꞌ Sises<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1:21 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Sises </char><char style="ft" closed="false">esi Kiriꞌ maimu </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Isaꞌsuwa </char><char style="ft" closed="false">awonsiꞌkɨ, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Itepuru uya toꞌ pikaꞌtɨ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe.</char></note> tukaiꞌ, apʉne pʉra tʉtonpa ton pikaꞌtɨtoꞌ iya oton pe iyesi pɨꞌ toꞌ makooi apai,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1:21 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 46:1">Sairaꞌ 46:1</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 1:31">Ʉruꞌ 1:31</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 1:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 1:22" />Serɨ eꞌkupʉꞌpʉ pena Papa usaurokʉꞌpʉ puꞌkenaꞌ Aisaya awɨrɨ aꞌkuꞌtɨnin pe: <verse eid="MAT 1:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 1:23" />“Aꞌpɨꞌpʉn uriꞌsan umonoꞌtatoꞌ oton, mɨrɨpan entutoꞌ oton warawoꞌ pe, mɨrɨpan esaꞌtoꞌ oton toꞌ uya Maniwerʉ tukaiꞌ,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1:23 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Aisaya 7:14 (LXX)</char></note> Papa esi upiyauꞌnokon” tawon taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 1:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 1:24" />Isoseꞌ upakasaꞌ uya nin si, Meri mariꞌmaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, Itepuru inserʉʉi uya tauroꞌkaꞌpʉ awɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan uya arɨꞌpʉ tiwʉꞌ taꞌ, <verse eid="MAT 1:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 1:25" />eꞌtane iyentu rawɨrɨ aꞌpɨꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ iya pen. Mɨrɨpan mʉre entusaꞌ eseꞌtɨꞌpʉ iya “Sises” tukaiꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1:25 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 2:21">Ʉruꞌ 2:21</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 1:25" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 1" />
  <chapter number="2" style="c" sid="MAT 2" />
  <para style="s1">Puꞌkenaꞌ Amʉꞌ Uya Sises Kaꞌkʉranpaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 2:1" />Sises entuꞌpʉ tʉpo Peꞌteriꞌen po Isutiya yau, kin pe Eraꞌ esi aꞌtai, puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ uyeeꞌpʉ wʉi enu uyepʉ winɨpai Surusiran pona, <verse eid="MAT 2:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 2:2" />mɨrɨpan kon uya, “Nai airɨ mʉre, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ kin pe teꞌton entusaꞌ nai? Kaiyonoꞌ epaꞌkasaꞌ eneꞌpʉ ina uya iyentusaꞌ ekamanin. Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ apurɨpɨꞌseꞌna ina uyeꞌsaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 2:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 2:3" />Serɨ tawon etasaꞌ kin pe teꞌsen Eraꞌ uya aꞌtai, isewankamaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kaisa rɨ Surusiran pon kon usewankamaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 2:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 2:4" />Tanporo Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan amʉranʉꞌsaꞌ tʉuya aꞌtai, toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ iya, “Nai yau Kʉrai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2:4 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai, </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya; Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe.</char></note> entutoꞌ oton tasaꞌ puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ uya nai?” tukaiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 2:4" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 2:5" />“Peꞌteriꞌen po, Isutiya yau,” tukaiꞌ toꞌ uya eikʉꞌpʉ. “Serɨ tukaiꞌ puꞌkenaꞌ uya imenukaꞌpʉ esi pena rɨ:<verse eid="MAT 2:5" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 2:6" />“‘Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon, Isutiya yawon, Peꞌteriꞌen pata pon kon,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 2:6">Isutiya yawoꞌnan pata ton tentakaiꞌ apata kon yau eke esaꞌ wannɨ eꞌsepotoꞌ oton,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 2:6">karimeru esaꞌ esi toꞌ esaꞌ pe kasa</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 2:6">umunkɨ, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ esaꞌ pe teꞌton,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2:6 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Maiꞌka 5:2</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 2:6">tawon,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 2:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 2:7" />Serɨ etasaꞌ Eraꞌ uya aꞌtai, tʉmaimu ennokoꞌpʉ iya puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ piyaꞌ toꞌ pokon pe amaꞌai teꞌsepotoꞌ kon pe, mɨrɨpan kon winɨ etaꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨ aꞌtai kaiyonoꞌ epaꞌkaꞌpʉ tukaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 2:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 2:8" />Mɨrɨpan kon ennokoꞌpʉ iya Peꞌteriꞌen pona, “Wakʉ pe mʉre mʉwarinpatʉiꞌ. Eposaꞌ auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, upanaꞌtɨiꞌ mɨsiꞌtʉiꞌ, urɨ rɨ nɨrɨ utɨtoꞌ pe apurɨpɨꞌseꞌna,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 2:8" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9-10" style="v" sid="MAT 2:9-10" />Kin maimu eta tʉuyaꞌnokon tʉpo, toꞌ utɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya kaiyonoꞌ kanan enkaaꞌpʉ, tʉneneꞌpʉ kon nʉꞌpʉ wʉi enu uyepʉ winɨ,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2:9 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">tʉneneꞌpʉ kon nʉꞌpʉ wʉi enu uyepʉ winɨ; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">tʉneneꞌpʉ kon nʉꞌpʉ iyenuku</char></note> mɨrɨpan pɨꞌ toꞌ eporiꞌmaꞌpʉ. Mɨrɨpan kon rawɨrɨ kaiyonoꞌ utɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan ereutaꞌpʉ mʉre pata epoi. <verse eid="MAT 2:9-10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 2:11" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ ewomʉꞌpʉ ɨutɨ taꞌ. Mʉre si ensaꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, isan, Meri pokon pe, toꞌ eꞌsekunkaꞌpʉ apurɨpɨtʉ pe. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, timamin kon yen aꞌkokaꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, mɨrɨpan kon uya irepapɨtʉꞌpʉ epeꞌkenaꞌ ton ke: korʉ ke, aꞌpoꞌnan ikɨtun, pʉrankensens tatoꞌ ke mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ karapa, mɨrʉ tatoꞌ ke.<verse eid="MAT 2:11" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 2:12" />Papa uya toꞌ panaꞌtɨꞌpʉ toꞌ eꞌneꞌpɨtʉ yau, toꞌ ennaꞌpo namaiꞌ kin pe teꞌsen Eraꞌ piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon ennaꞌpoꞌpʉ tʉpata kon yaꞌ tʉron nɨ awɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 2:12" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Isoseꞌ, Meri Uya Sises Arɨꞌpʉ Isiꞌ Pona</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 2:13" />Toꞌ utɨꞌpʉ tʉpo, Itepuru inserʉʉi usenpoikaꞌpʉ Isoseꞌ piyaꞌ iyeꞌneꞌpɨtʉ yau, “Isoseꞌ, eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌ, mʉre mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ isan tanʉnse ainʉnkɨ Isiꞌ pona. Kin Eraꞌ man iwarinpa pɨꞌ iwɨtoꞌ pe tʉuya,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 2:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 2:14" />Mɨrɨpan eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkasaꞌ uya mʉre mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ isan arɨꞌpʉ ewarupɨ nau Isiꞌ pona, <verse eid="MAT 2:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 2:15" />mɨrɨpan kon ukoꞌmamʉꞌpʉ Eraꞌ umaꞌta pona rɨ. Pena puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ nekamaꞌpʉ utaꞌkuꞌtɨꞌpʉ, “Umu kɨꞌma uya Isiꞌ apai,” tawon.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2:15 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Oseya 11:1</char></note><verse eid="MAT 2:15" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Soisa Amʉꞌ Uya Warawoꞌ Munkɨ Amʉꞌ Tʉꞌkaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 2:16" />Eraꞌ uya iꞌtusaꞌ aꞌtai puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ uya tennakasaꞌ, ipan pe isakorotaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya, “Warawoꞌ munkɨ amʉꞌ Peꞌteriꞌen pon kon itʉꞌkatɨꞌ asaꞌron wʉipiya airon kon mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ mɨrɨ oꞌkoiꞌno kon nɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya, puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ uya ekamaꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 2:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 2:17" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, puꞌkenaꞌ Iseremaya nekamaꞌpʉ utaꞌkuꞌtɨꞌpʉ:<verse eid="MAT 2:17" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 2:18" />“Main useta Rama pata po,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 2:18">tʉutaꞌkwarʉkaiꞌ ukaran nɨ esi eke pe rɨ,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 2:18">Rʉiꞌserʉ esi ukaran nɨ pɨꞌ tʉmunkɨ amʉꞌ wenai,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 2:18">tʉporiꞌma iꞌse pʉra iyesi,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 2:18">toꞌ pʉra iyesi pɨꞌ,”<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2:18 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Iseremaya 31:15</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 2:18">tawon.<verse eid="MAT 2:18" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Toꞌ Ennaꞌpoꞌpʉ Isiꞌ Apai</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 2:19" />Eraꞌ umaꞌtaꞌpʉ tʉpo, inserʉ usenpoikaꞌpʉ iyeꞌneꞌpɨtʉ yau Isoseꞌ piyaꞌ, Isiꞌ po, <verse eid="MAT 2:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 2:20" />“Eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌ, mʉre mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ isan akɨ Esuwerʉ pata pona. Kamoro mʉre wɨnɨ iꞌse teꞌsan umaꞌtaꞌpʉ man,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 2:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 2:21" />Mɨrɨpan eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ, mʉre mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ isan arɨꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan kon utɨꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ pata pona.<verse eid="MAT 2:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 2:22" />Eꞌtane Aꞌkeras enasaꞌ tʉkʉipʉnʉ Eraꞌ pataꞌpʉ yaꞌ kin pe Isutiya po etaꞌpʉ iya. Enariꞌkeꞌ pe iyesiꞌpʉ, mɨrɨ yaꞌ ɨtɨpai pʉra. Ipanamasaꞌ esiꞌpʉ iyeꞌneꞌpɨtʉ yau, mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ Kiyarari nono pona. <verse eid="MAT 2:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 2:23" />Mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ ɨkoꞌmanseꞌna Nasareꞌ pona. Puꞌkenaꞌ ton nekamaꞌpʉ utaꞌkuꞌtɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, “Nasarin<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2:23 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Nasarin; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">apʉne, Nonpa 6:1-21 enkɨ.</char></note> tukaiꞌ esaꞌtoꞌ oton,” tawon.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2:23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 1:24">Maꞌ 1:24</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 2:39">Ʉruꞌ 2:39</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 1:45">Isaan 1:45</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 2:23" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 2" />
  <chapter number="3" style="c" sid="MAT 3" />
  <para style="s1">Isaan Paꞌtes Tʉrawasooi</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 1:1-8">Maꞌ 1:1-8</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:1-18">Ʉruꞌ 3:1-18</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 1:19-28">Isaan 1:19-28</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 3:1" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Isaan Paꞌtes uyeeꞌpʉ. Itekare ekamaꞌpʉ iya Isutiya rɨmonoꞌtaai awɨrɨ, <verse eid="MAT 3:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 3:2" />“Amakooi kon apai eraꞌtɨtɨꞌ, apʉne pʉra Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe aꞌko pe man,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:2 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 4:17">Maꞌsiu 4:17</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 1:15">Maꞌ 1:15</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 3:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 3:3" />Isaan pʉse rɨ puꞌkenaꞌ Aisaya usaurokʉꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 3:3">“Rɨmonoꞌ tau kaꞌpon ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨtʉ,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 3:3">‘Itepuru eꞌma ikonekatɨꞌ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 3:3">toꞌsa rɨ iteꞌma ikonekatɨꞌ,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3:3 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Aisaya 40:3 (LXX)</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 3:3">tawon,” taꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 3:3" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 3:4" />Isaan pon esiꞌpʉ kiyamerʉ iꞌpoꞌ konekasaꞌ, oꞌ piꞌpɨ konekasaꞌ esiꞌpʉ ipokʉrʉʉi pe iworoꞌpai pɨꞌ. Itiꞌkiyari esiꞌpʉ kairau amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ teusan eꞌku.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:4 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2KI 1:8">2 Kin Amʉꞌ 1:8</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 3:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 3:5" />Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ utɨꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ Surusiran mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Isutiya apai, tanporo Isotan nono piyawoꞌ nan pata apaiꞌne. <verse eid="MAT 3:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 3:6" />Tʉmakooi kon ekama pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon paꞌtaisimaꞌpʉ iya Isotan tuna tʉuꞌtɨsen kau.<verse eid="MAT 3:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 3:7" />Eꞌtane tuꞌke Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Satuꞌsi amʉꞌ uyepʉ ene tʉuya aꞌtai epaꞌtaisiman kuꞌtoꞌ iya airɨ, taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon ɨsɨ ton ɨkʉi munkɨ ton! Ɨnʉꞌ uya apanaꞌtɨsaꞌ kon ayainʉmʉ kon pa nʉyeꞌaiꞌneꞌ ekotaꞌman nɨtoꞌ piyapai?<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:7 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 12:34">Maꞌsiu 12:34</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 23:33">23:33</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 3:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 3:8" />Epetatɨꞌ ɨyeraꞌtɨsaꞌ kon amakooi kon apai ekamanin ke. <verse eid="MAT 3:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 3:9" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon pe rɨ kɨsenuminkatʉu, ‘Epʉraꞌan esi ina kʉipʉnʉ pe,’ tukaiꞌ. Apanaꞌtɨ uya ꞌnokon serɨ, serɨ ton tɨꞌ apai Papa uya Epʉraꞌan munkɨ oton kon koneka mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:9 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 8:33">Isaan 8:33</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 3:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 3:10" />Waꞌka eꞌkamasaꞌ man yʉi amʉꞌ miꞌ airɨ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tanporon yʉi amʉꞌ tepetasen pen aꞌtɨtoꞌ oton nɨ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan enoꞌma apoꞌ yaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:10 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 7:19">Maꞌsiu 7:19</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 3:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 3:11" />“Apaꞌtaisima uya ꞌnokon tuna ke, amakooi kon apai ɨyeraꞌtɨ kon pa. Eꞌtane uyeꞌmaꞌpʉ pe meruntɨ kuru uyepʉ mɨrɨ uyentaino, isapatooi arɨ uya poken pʉra eꞌaiꞌneꞌ. Apaꞌtaisima iya ꞌnokon mɨrɨ Wakʉ Aꞌkwarʉ ke mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ apoꞌ ke. <verse eid="MAT 3:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 3:12" />Saraꞌsaraꞌpan tiꞌkiyari piꞌpɨ menkatoꞌ iya ike esi itemiyatʉ yau, mɨrɨpan uya iꞌkwatoꞌ tʉuya apon akoroka, taꞌnasi, wiꞌ amʉranʉkʉ iya itiwʉꞌ taꞌ, ipiꞌpɨ rʉꞌpʉ poꞌtɨ iya tʉusenkʉꞌsen pen apoꞌ ke,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PRO 5:14-23">Ipuꞌketʉ 5:14-23</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 3:12" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Isaan Uya Sises Paꞌtaisimaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 1:9-11">Maꞌ 1:9-11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:21-22">Ʉruꞌ 3:21-22</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 3:13" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uyeeꞌpʉ Kiyarari winɨ Isaan piyaꞌ Isotan tuna airɨ tʉpaꞌtaisimatoꞌ pe iya, <verse eid="MAT 3:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 3:14" />Isaan esiꞌpʉ ɨnereutanʉꞌpai, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Upaꞌtaisima auya ruꞌku iꞌse eꞌaiꞌ, mɨrɨ peꞌ eꞌtane upiyaꞌ ɨuyeꞌsaꞌ?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 3:14" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 3:15" />Sises uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Tɨwɨ mɨrɨ kasa rɨ ikuꞌkɨ, serɨ pe rɨken iyeꞌtoꞌ pe. Serɨ winɨ tanporo Papa eꞌtoꞌ iꞌse rɨ kupʉ mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Isaan uya ikupʉꞌpʉ imaimu awɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 3:15" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 3:16" />Inke pʉra tepaꞌtaisimaꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ pe, Sises ekanwakaꞌpʉ tuna kapai. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai kuru rɨ, kaꞌ utaꞌkokaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya Papa Aꞌkwarʉ uꞌtɨ eneꞌpʉ wakoꞌwa kasa, mɨrɨpan utaꞌsiꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 3:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 3:17" />Main, Epʉn winon uya taꞌpʉ, “Umu pʉse rɨ, uniꞌnʉnkanʉ; ipɨꞌ eporiꞌmayaiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:17 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 22:2">Iseneses 22:2</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 2:7">Eren 2:7</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 42:1">Aisaya 42:1</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 12:18">Maꞌsiu 12:18</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 17:5">17:5</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 1:11">Maꞌ 1:11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:35">Ʉruꞌ 9:35</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 3:17" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 3" />
  <chapter number="4" style="c" sid="MAT 4" />
  <para style="s1">Makoi Uya Sises Iꞌtupɨtʉꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 1:12-13">Maꞌ 1:12-13</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 4:1-13">Ʉruꞌ 4:1-13</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 4:1" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Iyaꞌkwarʉ uya Sises arɨꞌpʉ rɨmonoꞌ taꞌ Makoi uya iꞌtupɨꞌtoꞌ pe.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4:1 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="HEB 2:18">Ipuru 2:18</ref>; <ref loc="HEB 4:15">4:15</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 4:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 4:2" />Tʉuseruma tʉpo tentaꞌnaiꞌ pʉra 40 kaisa rɨ wʉi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ewarupɨ, mɨrɨpan esiꞌpʉ ipan pe kuru iwan pe. <verse eid="MAT 4:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 4:3" />Iꞌtupɨꞌnin uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Papa Mumu pe ɨwesi yau, se ton tɨꞌ amʉꞌ pɨꞌ pʉreti pe enakɨ kaꞌkɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 4:3" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 4:4" />Sises uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ, ‘Kaꞌpon esi tʉukoꞌmansen pʉreti pɨꞌ rɨken pen, eꞌtane tanporon nɨ main pɨꞌ Papa mʉta yapai tʉuyeꞌsen,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4:4 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Isuꞌtaronomi 8:3</char></note> tawon,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 4:4" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 4:5" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Makoi uya Sises arɨꞌpʉ wakʉ eke pata pona, mɨrɨpan uya Papa enaꞌ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ kaꞌtawon inakapu putu po iyeꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkatoꞌ pe ikupʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 4:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 4:6" />“Papa Mumu pe ɨwesi yau, ataꞌmoꞌkakɨ, apʉne pʉra iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 4:6">“‘Tinserʉʉi ton apiyoꞌma iya ɨpɨꞌ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 4:6">mɨrɨpan kon uya temiyatʉ kon yau ayanʉmʉ</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 4:6">tɨꞌ pona aꞌta wɨnɨ auya namaiꞌ,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4:6 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Eren 91:11-12</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 4:6">tawon,” taꞌpʉ Makoi uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 4:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 4:7" />Sises uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ rɨ nɨrɨ, ‘Itepuru, Papa, iteseꞌ pɨꞌ ɨweꞌtoꞌ kʉsiꞌtupɨtʉi,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4:7 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Isuꞌtaronomi 6:16</char></note> tasaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 4:7" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 4:8" />Makoi uya kanan arɨꞌpʉ kaꞌtawon wʉꞌ pona, mɨrɨpan uya tanporo eke ton pata enpoikaꞌpʉ itenu yaꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ wakʉ pe rɨ iyeꞌtoꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 4:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 4:9" />“Tanporo serɨ ton ke ɨrepa uya, urɨ pɨꞌ teꞌsekunkaiꞌ ɨwɨpʉrema yau,” taꞌpʉ iya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 4:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 4:10" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Upiyapai enta, Seꞌtan! <note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4:10 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Seꞌtan </char><char style="ft" closed="false">–Makoi eseꞌ isakon, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Papa eseru ewarumaꞌtɨnin </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe.</char></note> Apʉne pʉra iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ, ‘Itepuru, Papa, iteseꞌ pɨꞌ ɨweꞌtoꞌ pɨꞌ rɨken ɨpʉremaꞌ; Kʉrɨ rɨ rɨken poitorʉ pe eꞌkɨ,’<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4:10 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 6:13">Isuꞌtaronomi 6:13</ref></char></note> tawon,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 4:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 4:11" />Mɨrɨpan piyapai Makoi utɨꞌpʉ. Inserʉ amʉꞌ uyeeꞌpʉ ipikaꞌtɨiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 4:11" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Itekare Ekama Pɨꞌ Sises Epiyaꞌtɨꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 4:12" />Sises uya Isaan esi parikiꞌsi tau tawon etasaꞌ aꞌtai, iyennaꞌpoꞌpʉ Kiyarari pona.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4:12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 14:3">Maꞌsiu 14:3</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 6:17">Maꞌ 6:17</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:19-20">Ʉruꞌ 3:19-20</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 4:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 4:13" />Ɨkoꞌmanseꞌna itɨꞌpʉ Kaꞌpaneyan pona, Nasareꞌ tʉnɨnse. Mɨrɨ pata esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ parau kuꞌpɨri piyau Sepuran mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Naꞌtari nono airɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4:13 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 2:12">Isaan 2:12</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 4:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 4:14" />Puꞌkenaꞌ Aisaya uya taꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ aꞌkuꞌtɨ pe:<verse eid="MAT 4:14" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 4:15" />“Sepuran mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Naꞌtari nono pon kon,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 4:15">kaꞌpon amʉꞌ Kiyarari eꞌma awɨron kon mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tuna Isotan ratoi pon kon,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 4:15">Kiyarari, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ pen nono yau teꞌsan.<verse eid="MAT 4:15" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 4:16" />Pʉsamoro kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ewarupɨ yau tʉukoꞌmansan uya</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 4:16">eke rɨ iweyu ensaꞌ man;</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 4:16">umaꞌtan nɨtoꞌ nono yau teꞌsan pona iweyu eꞌweiꞌtɨsaꞌ man”<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4:15-16 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Aisaya 9:1-2</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 4:16">tawon.<verse eid="MAT 4:16" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 4:17" />Mɨrɨ siꞌkɨrɨ rɨ Sises epiyaꞌtɨꞌpʉ itekare ekama pɨꞌ, “Eraꞌtɨtɨꞌ amakooi kon apai, apʉne pʉra Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe man aꞌko pe!” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4:17 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 3:2">Maꞌsiu 3:2</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 4:17" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Uya Asakɨrɨꞌnan Kon Kɨꞌmaꞌpʉ Tʉpoitorʉ Pe</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 1:16-20">Maꞌ 1:16-20</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 5:1-11">Ʉruꞌ 5:1-11</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 4:18" />Sises usarɨ koroꞌtau parau kuꞌpɨri Kiyarari piyawɨrɨ, kaꞌpon eneꞌpʉ iya, takon yaꞌ teꞌsan, Saiman iteseꞌ, Piꞌta tatoꞌ ipɨꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Anturu si itakon. Tʉpunwerʉ kon tʉrʉ pɨꞌ toꞌ esiꞌpʉ parau kuꞌpɨri kau, apʉne pʉra moroꞌ amʉꞌ aꞌsinin nan pe tesi kon pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 4:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 4:19" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Upɨkɨrɨ ɨsiꞌtɨꞌ, ɨkonekatoꞌ kon pe uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ aꞌsinin nan pe,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 4:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 4:20" />Mɨrɨ pe rɨ, tʉpunwerʉ kon tʉnɨnse toꞌ utɨꞌpʉ ipɨkɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 4:20" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 4:21" />Mɨrɨ apai tʉutɨiꞌ, tʉron kon asaꞌron kon ɨsirunan eneꞌpʉ iya, Isens mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Isaan, Sepiti munkɨ amʉꞌ. Kanau yau toꞌ esiꞌpʉ, tʉkʉipʉnʉ kon Sepiti pokon pe tʉpunwerʉ kon konepɨtʉ pɨꞌ. Sises uya toꞌ kɨꞌmaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 4:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 4:22" />Inke pʉra, tʉkanwa kon mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉkʉipʉnʉ kon tʉnɨnse toꞌ utɨꞌpʉ ipɨkɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 4:22" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Eꞌneꞌ Ton Epiꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ Iya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 6:17-19">Ʉruꞌ 6:17-19</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 4:23" />Sises utɨꞌpʉ siya rɨ Kiyarari awɨrɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enupa pɨꞌ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ usenupatoꞌ iwʉꞌ tauꞌne. Wakʉ itekare ekama pɨꞌ iyesiꞌpʉ, Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe pɨꞌ. Paran pokon kon mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ takuruꞌkenaꞌ nan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ epiꞌtɨ pɨꞌ iyesiꞌpʉ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4:23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 9:35">Maꞌsiu 9:35</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 1:39">Maꞌ 1:39</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 4:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 4:24" />Itekareei utɨꞌpʉ siya rɨ Siriya poron pata awɨrɨꞌne rɨ, mɨrɨpan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya tanporo eꞌneꞌ pe teꞌsan neeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ, tiꞌtuiꞌ pʉra rɨ teparan ke teꞌsan. Tʉron kon eparan esiꞌpʉ ipan pe kuru teꞌkʉnkʉnmasen, tʉron kon yau makoi aꞌkwarʉ esiꞌpʉ, tʉron kon eparan esiꞌpʉ yai toꞌ ennoꞌpɨꞌnin, tʉron kon ipuꞌtɨkaꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ kon Sises uya tanporo pʉsamoro epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 4:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 4:25" />Eke pe rɨ anpisin Kiyarari awɨron kon, Teꞌkaꞌpores,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4:25 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Teꞌkaꞌpores –10 Kaisaron Pata </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa.</char></note> Surusiran, Isutiya pon kon, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Isotan nono ratoi pon kon utɨꞌpʉ ipɨkɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 4:25" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 4" />
  <chapter number="5" style="c" sid="MAT 5" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 5:1" />Sises uya anpisin pe kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ensaꞌ aꞌtai, iyekainʉmʉꞌpʉ iꞌkʉrʉ pona, mɨrɨpan ereutaꞌpʉ. Ipoitorʉ ton amʉraꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ, <verse eid="MAT 5:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 5:2" />mɨrɨpan kon enupa pɨꞌ iyeꞌsaraꞌtɨꞌpʉ:<verse eid="MAT 5:2" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Uya Papa Nʉkupʉnʉ Ton Poriꞌ Pe Ekamaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 6:20-23">Ʉruꞌ 6:20-23</ref>)</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 5:3" />“Poriꞌ pe entuꞌmaꞌ naꞌneꞌ nan taꞌkwarʉ kon yau esi,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 5:3">apʉne pʉra toꞌ iwanoꞌ pe Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi.<verse eid="MAT 5:3" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 5:4" />Poriꞌ pe teꞌton kon kamoro tʉutaꞌkwarʉkaiꞌ ukaran nɨ pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ nan serɨ pe,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 5:4">apʉne pʉra Papa uya poriꞌ pe toꞌ kuꞌtoꞌ oton.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:4 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 61:2">Aisaya 61:2</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 5:4" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 5:5" />Poriꞌ pe teꞌton kon kamoro mɨ pe teꞌkuꞌsan pen,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 5:5">apʉne pʉra tanporo rɨ non tʉrʉ Papa uya toꞌ enaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:5 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 37:11">Eren 37:11</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 5:5" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 5:6" />Poriꞌ pe teꞌton kon kamoro iwan pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tunaꞌkiriꞌ ke naꞌneꞌ nan ipokenaꞌ iꞌse,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 5:6">apʉne pʉra toꞌ rɨ aꞌwetatoꞌ oton.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:6 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 55:1-2">Aisaya 55:1-2</ref>; <ref loc="SIR 24:21">Sairaꞌ 24:21</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 5:6" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 5:7" />Poriꞌ pe teꞌton kon kamoro ɨsentuꞌkenaꞌ ton,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 5:7">apʉne pʉra Papa usentuꞌmatoꞌ oton toꞌ pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 5:7" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 5:8" />Poriꞌ pe teꞌton kon kamoro wakʉ pe tewan kon yau nekonekayaiꞌneꞌ nan,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 5:8">apʉne pʉra toꞌ uya Papa entoꞌ oton.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:8 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 24:3-4">Eren 24:3-4</ref>; 2 Estʉras 7:98</char></note><verse eid="MAT 5:8" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 5:9" />Poriꞌ pe teꞌton kon kamoro ɨsɨ pe teꞌsan iꞌnɨꞌpankanin nan,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 5:9">apʉne pʉra Papa munkɨ amʉꞌ pe toꞌ eꞌtoꞌ oton.<verse eid="MAT 5:9" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 5:10" />Poriꞌ pe teꞌton kon kamoro ɨsɨ pe rɨ, ipan pe rɨ tʉkotaꞌmasan wakʉ kupʉ toꞌ uya wenai,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 5:10">toꞌ iwanoꞌ pe Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:10 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1PE 3:14">1 Piꞌta 3:14</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 5:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 5:11" />“Poriꞌ pe ɨwesi kon mɨrɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya asapema kon aꞌtai, iwenai pʉra ɨkotaꞌmaꞌnokon aꞌtai mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ toꞌ usaurokʉ ɨri pe rɨ ɨpɨꞌnokon aꞌtai urɨ uriyaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1PE 4:14">1 Piꞌta 4:14</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 5:12" />Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ ipan pe poriꞌ pe kuru eꞌtɨꞌ, apʉne pʉra eke rɨ ɨyepeꞌpʉ kon esi pɨꞌ Epʉn po, apʉne pʉra mɨrɨ kasa rɨ arawɨron kon puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ kotaꞌmapɨtʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2CH 36:16">2 Kʉronoꞌkʉrʉs 36:16</ref>; <ref loc="SIR 2:8">Sairaꞌ 2:8</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 7:52">Inkupʉꞌpʉ 7:52</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 5:12" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Pɨkɨron Kon Esi Waiyo Mɨrɨ Awonsiꞌkɨ Iweyu Kasa</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 9:50">Maꞌ 9:50</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 14:34-35">Ʉruꞌ 14:34-35</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 5:13" />“Non waiyori pe rɨ ɨwesi kon, eꞌtane ineꞌneꞌ pe pʉra waiyo enasaꞌ yau, nai kasa ineꞌneꞌ pe kanan iyeꞌtoꞌ pe ikupʉ? Wakʉ pe pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ, enoꞌmatoꞌ pe rɨ iyesi kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya iwasaꞌpɨꞌtoꞌ pe tʉusarɨ kon aꞌtai.<verse eid="MAT 5:13" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 5:14" />“Serɨ non weyu pe rɨ ɨwesi kon. Wʉꞌ pon pata eꞌsoꞌnamʉ pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 8:12">Isaan 8:12</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 9:5">9:5</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 5:15" />Mɨrɨ pe pʉra kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya raanꞌpu poꞌtɨsaꞌ nonka pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ pʉsau oꞌkoiꞌ. Eꞌtane ruꞌku, toꞌ uya inonka iyapon pona, mɨrɨpan uya tanporon kon nɨ weiꞌtɨ ɨutɨ tau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:15 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 4:21">Maꞌ 4:21</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 8:16">Ʉruꞌ 8:16</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 11:33">11:33</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 5:16" />Mɨrɨ kasa, tɨwɨ ɨweyu pe naꞌneꞌ neꞌweiꞌtɨi kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya entoꞌ pe. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, wakʉ ɨnkupʉnʉ entoꞌ pe toꞌ uya, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Papa, ɨkʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon apurɨpɨꞌtoꞌ pe toꞌ uya nɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:16 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1PE 2:12">1 Piꞌta 2:12</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 5:16" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Papa Maimu Esi Eke Pe</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 5:17" />“Puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Mosiꞌ nekamaꞌpʉ Main enoꞌmaiꞌ uyeꞌsaꞌ tukaiꞌ kʉsiꞌtutʉu. Enoꞌmaseꞌna uyeꞌsaꞌ pen eꞌtane aꞌkuꞌtɨiꞌ ruꞌku uyeꞌsaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 5:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 5:18" />Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; Epʉn mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ non eꞌweuka pʉꞌkʉ pona, ɨꞌrɨ rɨ moꞌka pʉra iyesi Papa Maimu yapai. Aiko pe rɨ naꞌneꞌ pen nʉwaraiꞌkaꞌpʉ esi moro rɨ Main pe tanporon nɨ utaꞌkuꞌtɨ pʉꞌkʉ pona.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 16:17">Ʉruꞌ 16:17</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 5:19" />Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ aiko pe rʉꞌkwɨ naꞌneꞌ Main tonpa iꞌkwɨꞌnin mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉron kon enupanin mɨrɨ rɨ marɨ kuꞌtoꞌ pe toꞌ uya eꞌtoꞌ oton aiko pe Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yau; eꞌtane ɨnʉꞌ rɨ Main kupʉ pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipɨꞌ enupanin pe naꞌneꞌ eꞌtoꞌ oton eke pe kuru Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yau. <verse eid="MAT 5:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 5:20" />Ta uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, wakʉ rɨken kuꞌtoꞌ auyaꞌnokon pe iyesi Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan entai; mɨrɨ kupʉ auya pʉra iyesi aꞌtai, Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yaꞌ ɨyepaꞌkatoꞌ oton kon parɨ pen nɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 5:20" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Usaurokʉꞌpʉ Sakoro Pɨꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 5:21" />Miyarɨ rɨ usenupan nɨtoꞌ ekamaꞌpʉ Sises uya; “Etaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon pena rɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ taꞌpʉ, ‘Ɨtonpa kʉꞌwɨnɨi,’ tawon, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ, ‘Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ tʉtonpa wɨnin nʉꞌpʉ kotaꞌmatoꞌ oton,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5:21 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Eꞌsotas 20:13; Isuꞌtaronomi 5:17</char></note> tawon, <verse eid="MAT 5:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 5:22" />eꞌtane ta uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, ɨnʉꞌ rɨ sakoroꞌ pe naꞌneꞌ tʉtonpa pɨꞌ kotaꞌmatoꞌ oton Papa uya. Takapʉ uya kanan, ɨnʉꞌ rɨ tʉtonpa esaꞌnin ‘Raꞌka,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5:22 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Raꞌka; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Aramiꞌ usakorotasaꞌ maimu</char></note> tukaiꞌ esi Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ Konsʉrʉʉi ton nʉkotaꞌma ton pe, eꞌtane ɨnʉꞌ uya, ‘Ɨmɨrɨ, iyaꞌkwarʉ pʉn!’ tasaꞌ aꞌtai tʉtonpa pɨꞌ, ɨsɨ rɨ apoꞌ eꞌma tau iyesi mɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 5:22" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 5:23" />“Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, ɨuseꞌmatoꞌ Papa enaꞌ esi aꞌtai, moro ɨyenu yau ɨri pe ɨtonpa eꞌkuꞌtoꞌ ɨpɨꞌ tʉkuꞌse itɨkɨ ɨtonpa eꞌkuꞌtoꞌ ɨri pe ɨpɨꞌ konekaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 5:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 5:24" />Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ apon piyau ɨntʉrʉnʉ tʉnonkaiꞌ, wapiya ɨtonpa aꞌkɨrɨ ekoneka ta, ɨyennaꞌpo pa ɨntʉrʉnʉ tʉseꞌna.<verse eid="MAT 5:24" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 5:25" />“Oko pe pʉra ɨyeyaton koꞌtʉ taꞌ ayayaiꞌneꞌ aꞌkɨrɨ ekonekakaꞌkɨ ipokon pe rɨ marɨ ɨwesi koroꞌtau, ɨkotaꞌmatoꞌ yaꞌ ɨtʉrʉ iya wapiya, eseru aimenkanin uya ɨtʉrʉ pʉresiman enaꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨyenoꞌma toꞌ uya parikiꞌsi taꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 5:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 5:26" />Iꞌnapairon nɨ ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; ɨyepaꞌkatoꞌ oton kon pen nɨ tanporo ɨneꞌmanʉ kon iꞌmaꞌka auyaꞌnokon pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 5:26" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Usaurokʉꞌpʉ Ekuman Nɨtoꞌ Pɨꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 5:27" />“Etaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon; ‘Tʉtaanꞌpʉ kenan kʉsekumankai,’ tawon.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:27 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 20:14">Eꞌsotas 20:14</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 5:18">Isuꞌtaronomi 5:18</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 5:28" />Eꞌtane ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ uriꞌsan ensaꞌ aꞌtai ekumaiꞌ pe, iyekumakaꞌsaꞌ rɨ mɨrɨ uriꞌsan aꞌkɨrɨ tewan yau. <verse eid="MAT 5:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 5:29" />Enwoꞌneꞌ winon ɨyenu uya ɨyeꞌmakoima emapuꞌtɨ pe iyesi yau, imoꞌkakɨ enoꞌma pa; wakʉ iwa pe rɨ iyesi tikin nɨ ɨpun tonpaꞌkasaꞌ auya aꞌtai, tanporo ɨpun enoꞌma ekotaꞌman nɨtoꞌ yaꞌ entai.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:29 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 18:9">Maꞌsiu 18:9</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 9:47">Maꞌ 9:47</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 5:30" />Enwoꞌneꞌ winon ɨyemiyatʉ uya ɨyeꞌmakoima emapuꞌtɨ pe iyesi yau, aꞌtɨkɨ enoꞌma pa; wakʉ iwa pe iyesi mɨrɨ tikin nɨ ɨpun tonpaꞌkasaꞌ auya aꞌtai, tanporo ɨpun enoꞌma ekotaꞌman nɨtoꞌ yaꞌ entai,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:30 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 18:8">Maꞌsiu 18:8</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 9:43">Maꞌ 9:43</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 5:30" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Usaurokʉꞌpʉ Noꞌpʉ Nonkatoꞌ Pɨꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MAT 19:9">Maꞌsiu 19:9</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 10:11-12">Maꞌ 10:11-12</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 16:18">Ʉruꞌ 16:18</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 5:31" />“Tasaꞌ iya kanan, ‘Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ tʉnoꞌpʉ nonka aꞌtai, tɨwɨ nʉkaretaiꞌtɨi kuru rɨ iyeꞌnonka karetaai ke,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5:31 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Isuꞌtaronomi 24:1-4 </char></note> <note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:31 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 19:7">Maꞌsiu 19:7</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 10:4">Maꞌ 10:4</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 5:32" />eꞌtane ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; ɨnʉꞌ rɨ tʉnoꞌpʉ nonkayaiꞌneꞌ, iyekumasaꞌ pen nɨ eꞌtane uya tekumasen pe iyesi emapuꞌtɨ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨnʉꞌ rɨ inonkasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ mariꞌmayaiꞌneꞌ, ekuma pe iyesi mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:32 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1CO 7:10-11">1 Koren 7:10-11</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 5:32" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Usauroꞌnɨtoꞌ Pɨꞌ Enupan</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 5:33" />“Etaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon pena rɨ kanan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ taꞌpʉ, ‘Ausauroꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, ikuꞌtoꞌ pe auya kʉꞌpʉremekʉi, eꞌtane Papa yaꞌ ausauroꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ awɨrɨ rɨ eꞌkɨ.’<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:33 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LEV 19:12">Ripaitiꞌkas 19:12</ref>; <ref loc="NUM 30:2">Nonpa 30:2</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 23:21">Isuꞌtaronomi 23:21</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 5:34" />Eꞌtane ekama uya ɨpɨꞌ; ɨꞌrɨ rɨ kʉkai ɨnkuꞌton pen nɨ pɨꞌ, Epʉn nɨ kʉsesakʉi–Papa apon mɨrɨ,<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:34 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JAS 5:12">Isens 5:12</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 66:1">Aisaya 66:1</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 23:22">Maꞌsiu 23:22</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 5:35" />non nɨ kʉsesakʉi–Papa pʉta apon mɨrɨ; Surusiran nɨ kʉsesakʉi–eke kin pataꞌseꞌ mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:35 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 66:1">Aisaya 66:1</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 48:2">Eren 48:2</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 5:36" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ aꞌpai rɨ kʉsesakʉi, apʉne pʉra tikin nɨ rɨ aꞌpai iꞌpoꞌ aimuꞌnaka auya pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iꞌkʉrʉntanʉkʉ auya pʉra rɨ iyesi. <verse eid="MAT 5:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 5:37" />Ewaiꞌ ta auya aꞌtai, ewaiꞌ kaꞌkɨ; kane ta auya aꞌtai, kane kaꞌkɨ rɨ nɨrɨ. Tʉron nɨ pe ausaurokʉ aꞌtai mɨrɨ esi Makoi winon pe.<verse eid="MAT 5:37" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Useꞌman Nɨtoꞌ Pɨꞌ Enupan</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 6:29-30">Ʉruꞌ 6:29-30</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 5:38" />“Etaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon nɨ, ‘En epeꞌpʉ pe en nɨ esi; ɨ epeꞌpʉ pe ɨ rɨ esi,’ tawon.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:38 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 21:24">Eꞌsotas 21:24</ref>; <ref loc="LEV 24:20">Ripaitiꞌkas 24:20</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 19:21">Isuꞌtaronomi 19:21</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 5:39" />Eꞌtane ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; ɨri pe ɨkuꞌnin nʉꞌpʉ pɨꞌ kɨseꞌmai. Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ ɨwɨnɨ yau enwoꞌneꞌ winon ɨyeꞌpeta pɨꞌ, iratoi rʉꞌpʉ rɨ marɨ iraꞌtɨkɨ iwinɨkʉiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 5:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 5:40" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ ayarɨ pe iyesi yau koꞌtʉ taꞌ ɨꞌrɨ wenai rɨ, mɨrɨpan uya ɨpon moꞌka pe iyesi yau itepeꞌpʉ pe, tɨwɨ ipʉroꞌpon pokon pe ɨpon moꞌkai. <verse eid="MAT 5:40" /><verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 5:41" />Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ taꞌkwarʉkaiꞌ ayarɨ taꞌkɨrɨ aꞌtai 1 mayirʉ, enta 2 mayirʉ eꞌtoꞌ airɨ. <verse eid="MAT 5:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 5:42" />Ɨyekamaꞌpoyaiꞌneꞌnokon irepatɨꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ keraꞌtɨi ɨnʉꞌ rɨ ɨyekamaꞌponin ɨiwanoꞌ pɨꞌ piyapai.<verse eid="MAT 5:42" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Eyaton Wannɨ Iꞌnʉnkatoꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 6:27-28">Ʉruꞌ 6:27-28</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 6:32-36">32-36</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="43" style="v" sid="MAT 5:43" />“Etaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon; ‘Ɨtonpa iꞌnʉnkakɨ,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5:43 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Ripaitiꞌkas 19:18</char></note> ɨyeyaton ewarumaꞌtɨiꞌma.’<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:43 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 12:4-7">Sairaꞌ 12:4-7</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:43" /><verse number="44" style="v" sid="MAT 5:44" />Eꞌtane ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; ɨyeyaton kon nɨ iꞌnʉnkatɨꞌ,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5:44 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tʉron nɨ ton emen imenukasaꞌ uya iponantɨpɨꞌsaꞌ; </char><char style="fq" closed="false">kamoro apaꞌnʉꞌnin nan pona wakʉ inonkatɨꞌ, kamoro ɨyewarumaꞌtɨnin nan pɨꞌ wakʉ ikuꞌtɨꞌ </char></note> mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨpʉrematɨꞌ ɨkotaꞌmanin kon pona, <verse eid="MAT 5:44" /><verse number="45" style="v" sid="MAT 5:45" />Epʉn pon ɨkʉipʉnʉ kon munkɨ amʉꞌ pe ɨwesi kon pa. Ɨri ton nɨ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ wakʉ ton nɨ weyu pe wʉi enu enuku emapuꞌtɨnin. Ipokenaꞌ ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipokenaꞌ ton pen nɨ pona tuna ennoko iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:45 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 4:10">Sairaꞌ 4:10</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 5:45" /><verse number="46" style="v" sid="MAT 5:46" />Ɨiꞌnʉnkanin kon nɨken iꞌnʉnka auyaꞌnokon yau, ɨꞌrɨ ken si ɨyepeꞌpʉ kon eporo auyaꞌnokon mɨrɨ? Mɨrɨ peꞌ kupʉ pʉrata amʉranʉꞌnin nan uya pʉra nai? <verse eid="MAT 5:46" /><verse number="47" style="v" sid="MAT 5:47" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨtonpa ton nɨken nɨ pɨꞌ miyarɨ ta auyaꞌnokon yau, ɨꞌrɨ ken si kupʉ auyaꞌnokon tʉron kon entai? Mɨrɨ peꞌ kupʉ Papa apurɨnin nan pen uya pʉra nai? <verse eid="MAT 5:47" /><verse number="48" style="v" sid="MAT 5:48" />Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, wakʉ pe eꞌtɨꞌ, ɨkʉipʉnʉ kon, Epʉn pon esi wakʉ pe kasa,”<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5:48 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LEV 19:2">Ripaitiꞌkas 19:2</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 18:13">Isuꞌtaronomi 18:13</ref></char></note> taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 5:48" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 5" />
  <chapter number="6" style="c" sid="MAT 6" />
  <para style="s1">Entuꞌmanin Nan Entoꞌ Pɨꞌ Enupan</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 6:1" />Sises eꞌsaraꞌtɨkaaꞌpʉ kanan tʉpoitorʉ ton enupa pɨꞌ. Taꞌpʉ iya, “Tiꞌtuiꞌ eꞌtɨꞌ, wakʉ ɨnkupʉnʉ kon yau, wakʉ pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ pɨꞌ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya ɨyentoꞌ pe tukaiꞌ. Mɨrɨ kuꞌsaꞌ auya aꞌtai, ɨyepeꞌpʉ eporo auya pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ ɨkʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon winɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">6:1 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 23:5">Maꞌsiu 23:5</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 6:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 6:2" />Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ entuꞌmanin nan repa auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, eke pe kʉsekamai, wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan uya ikupʉ kasa Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ usenupatoꞌ iwʉꞌ tau, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ asanta tawɨrɨ rɨ, tapurɨtoꞌ kon pe kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya tukaiꞌ. Iꞌnapairon nɨ ekama uya serɨ ɨpɨꞌnokon, toꞌ uya tepeꞌpʉ kon epokaꞌsaꞌ rɨ mɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 6:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 6:3" />Eꞌtane entuꞌmanin nan repa auya aꞌtai, tɨwɨ akamisi winon ɨyemiyatʉ kʉsiꞌtunin ɨyenwoꞌnetʉ winon ɨyemiyatʉ nʉkupʉnʉ, <verse eid="MAT 6:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 6:4" />mɨrɨ pɨꞌ ɨnkupʉnʉ eꞌtoꞌ pe nesii amaꞌai, ɨkʉipʉnʉ, amaꞌai ɨnkupʉnʉ ennin nʉꞌpʉ uya ɨyeꞌmatoꞌ pe.<verse eid="MAT 6:4" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Ɨpʉreman Nɨtoꞌ Pɨꞌ Enupan</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 11:2-4">Ʉruꞌ 11:2-4</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 6:5" />“Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨwɨpʉrema kon aꞌtai, wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan kasa keꞌtʉu. Ɨpʉremapaino kon teꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaiꞌ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ usenupatoꞌ iwʉꞌ tau mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ asanta kaꞌtaporo rɨ, tentoꞌ kon pe kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya. Iꞌnapairon nɨ ekama uya serɨ ɨpɨꞌnokon, toꞌ uya tepeꞌpʉ kon epokaꞌsaꞌ rɨ mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">6:5 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 18:10-14">Ʉruꞌ 18:10-14</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 6:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 6:6" />Eꞌtane ɨwɨpʉrema aꞌtai, ɨiwʉꞌ pʉꞌkʉ taꞌ ewonkɨ, ɨmʉraꞌtaai aꞌkokɨ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨwɨpʉrema pa tʉusensen pen nɨ ɨkʉipʉnʉ pɨꞌ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, ɨkʉipʉnʉ, amaꞌai ɨnkupʉnʉ ennin uya ɨyeꞌmatoꞌ pe. <verse eid="MAT 6:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 6:7" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ amaimu rɨ marɨ tʉnaꞌpopɨꞌse kɨpʉremai, Papa iꞌtunin nan pen kasa tʉmaimu kon useta pe tekamaiꞌ, teꞌsan apʉne pʉra tuꞌkan nɨ esakʉ tʉuyaꞌnokon pɨꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">6:7 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 7:14">Sairaꞌ 7:14</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 6:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 6:8" />Toꞌ kasa keꞌtʉu, ɨkʉipʉnʉ uya rɨ iꞌtukaꞌsaꞌ iꞌse ɨweꞌtoꞌ tekamaꞌpo auya wapiya rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 6:8" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 6:9" />“Se kasa nin si ɨwɨpʉrematoꞌ kon esi mɨrɨ:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 6:9">“‘Ina Kʉipʉnʉ Epʉn pon,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 6:9">tʉnamasen pe ɨyeseꞌ nesii.<verse eid="MAT 6:9" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 6:10" />Ina esaꞌ pe ɨweꞌtoꞌ nʉyepʉi,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 6:10">serɨ non po ɨyeseru neꞌkupʉi Epʉn po iyesi naꞌneꞌ kasa.<verse eid="MAT 6:10" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 6:11" />Ina irepakɨ serɨ pe wʉi kaisa rɨ teꞌsen ina iꞌkiyari ke.<verse eid="MAT 6:11" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 6:12" />Ina nʉkoꞌmanʉkʉnʉ ɨri pɨꞌ ɨsentuꞌmakɨ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 6:12">ina usentuꞌmasaꞌ ɨri koꞌmanʉꞌnin nan pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ kasa.<verse eid="MAT 6:12" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 6:13" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ina kʉsarɨi iꞌtupɨꞌnɨtoꞌ yaꞌ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 6:13">eꞌtane ɨri pe teꞌsen piyapai ina imoꞌkakɨ.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">6:13 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tʉron nɨ ton emen imenukasaꞌ yau kanan; </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Ɨmɨrɨ esaꞌ wannɨ, meruntɨ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ eke, wakʉ inkeroꞌ rɨ. Amen.</char></note>’<verse eid="MAT 6:13" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 6:14" />“Apʉne pʉra kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya ɨri pe ɨkuꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ pɨꞌ ɨusentuꞌma yau, ɨkʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon nɨ nɨrɨ usentuꞌma mɨrɨ ɨpɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 6:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 6:15" />Eꞌtane ɨri pe ɨkuꞌnin nan nʉꞌpʉ kon pɨꞌ ɨusentuꞌma kon pʉra iyesi yau, ɨkʉipʉnʉ rɨ nɨrɨ usentuꞌma pʉra iyesi ɨpɨꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">6:15 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 11:25-26">Maꞌ 11:25-26</ref>; <ref loc="SIR 28:1-5">Sairaꞌ 28:1-5</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 6:15" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Useruman Nɨtoꞌ Pɨꞌ Enupan</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 6:16" />“Ɨuseruma aꞌtai tentaꞌnaiꞌ pʉra, pokoi pe ɨyemʉꞌ kʉꞌkupʉi wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan eꞌtoꞌ kasa, temʉꞌ rɨ toꞌ ena kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya rɨ nin tentoꞌ kon pe, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya rɨ nin tapurɨtoꞌ kon pe. Iꞌnapairon nɨ ekama uya ɨpɨꞌ, toꞌ uya tepeꞌpʉ kon epokaꞌsaꞌ rɨ mɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 6:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 6:17" />Eꞌtane ɨuseruma aꞌtai tentaꞌnaiꞌ pʉra, ɨsenpataukaꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ekarapaimaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">6:17 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JDT 10:3">Isutiꞌ 10:3</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 6:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 6:18" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, kaꞌpon uya ɨtoꞌkaꞌnʉkʉ pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ ɨuseruma tentaꞌnaiꞌ pʉra tukaiꞌ, eꞌtane ɨkʉipʉnʉ, tʉusensen pen nɨ uya iꞌtu, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨkʉipʉnʉ, amaꞌai teꞌkuꞌsen ennin nʉꞌpʉ uya rɨ ɨyeꞌmatoꞌ pe.<verse eid="MAT 6:18" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Imaminkeꞌ Pe Eꞌnɨtoꞌ Epʉn Po</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 12:33-34">Ʉruꞌ 12:33-34</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 6:19" />“Ɨimamin kʉsamʉranʉkʉi serɨ non po, ene amʉꞌ uya imaꞌtanʉꞌtoꞌ yau rɨ, ikarantoꞌ yau rɨ, amaꞌ amʉꞌ eꞌtoꞌ amaꞌ pe yau rɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">6:19 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JAS 5:2-3">Isens 5:2-3</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 6:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 6:20" />Eꞌtane Epʉn po ɨimamin kon amʉranʉꞌtɨꞌ, ene amʉꞌ uya imaꞌtanʉꞌtoꞌ pen pataꞌseꞌ yau, ikarantoꞌ pen yau, amaꞌ amʉꞌ eꞌtoꞌ amaꞌ pe pata pen nɨ yau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">6:20 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 29:11">Sairaꞌ 29:11</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 6:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 6:21" />Apʉne pʉra ɨimamin kon eꞌtoꞌ airɨ, mɨrɨ yau ɨyewan kon nɨ nɨrɨ esi.<verse eid="MAT 6:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 6:22" />“En esi pun raanꞌpuui pe rɨ. Wakʉ pe ɨyenu esi yau, tanporo ɨpun esi aꞌkwa pe. <verse eid="MAT 6:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 6:23" />Eꞌtane, wakʉ pe pʉra ɨyenu esi aꞌtai, ewarupɨ pe rɨ ɨpun esi. Iweyu pʉra ɨpun esi yau, ipan pe rɨ ewarupɨ pe iyesi mɨrɨ!<verse eid="MAT 6:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 6:24" />“Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ eꞌtʉrawasoma pʉra iyesi asaꞌron kon tepuru ton apiyoꞌ pe. Tikin nan ewarumaꞌtɨ iya, isakon iꞌnʉnka iya; tikin nan pɨꞌ itaꞌsi, isakon sanoma iya pʉra. Asaꞌrɨ rɨ marɨ Papa mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ pʉrata apiyoꞌ pe ɨwesi pʉra iyesi.<verse eid="MAT 6:24" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Kɨsewankamatʉu</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 16:13">Ʉruꞌ 16:13</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 12:22-31">12:22-31</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 6:25" />“Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, ekama uya serɨ ɨpɨꞌnokon, ɨukoꞌmantoꞌ kon pɨꞌ rɨ kɨsewankamatʉu, ɨiꞌkiyari kon pɨꞌ rɨ mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨuku kon pɨꞌ rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨpun kon pɨꞌ rɨ, ɨꞌrɨ esi upon pe tukaiꞌ. Ɨukoꞌmantoꞌ peꞌ esi pen mɨrɨ kiyari entai? Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨpun kon peꞌ esi pen pon entai? <verse eid="MAT 6:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 6:26" />Apʉne toron amʉꞌ entɨꞌ kaꞌtawon kon. Tiꞌkiyari kon pɨnnin nan pen nɨ, anʉnnin nan pen nɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra amʉranʉꞌnin nan pen nɨ, eꞌtane rɨ ɨkʉipʉnʉ kon, Epʉn pon uya toꞌ ewekʉ. Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon ken peꞌ si esi pen iꞌnʉnkenaꞌ pe toꞌ entai? <verse eid="MAT 6:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 6:27" />Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ ɨnka miyarɨ parɨ<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">6:27 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ ɨnka miyarɨ parɨ; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">usemoꞌka kusan pe parɨ</char></note> ipɨꞌ tʉusewankamaiꞌ?<verse eid="MAT 6:27" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 6:28" />“Ɨꞌrɨ pɨꞌ pon pɨꞌ ɨusewankama kon? Apʉne entɨꞌ pata ipʉrʉ esi wakʉ pe rɨ iyaꞌta tʉpataꞌseꞌ yau, teꞌtʉrawasomasen pen mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨꞌpɨꞌnin pen. <verse eid="MAT 6:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 6:29" />Mɨrɨ rɨ eꞌtane ekama uya serɨ ɨpɨꞌnokon; Saraman, imaminkenaꞌ epontɨsaꞌ pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ ton kasa.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">6:29 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1KI 10:4-7">1 Kin Amʉꞌ 10:4-7</ref>; <ref loc="2CH 9:3-6">2 Kʉronoꞌkʉrʉs 9:3-6</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 6:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 6:30" />Mɨrɨ kasa si Papa uya wanaꞌ rɨ pontɨ pe iyesi yau wanaꞌ serɨ pe naꞌneꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ awanapairɨ enoꞌma apoꞌ yaꞌ, mɨrɨ naꞌneꞌ entai peꞌ ɨpontɨ iya ꞌnokon pen mɨ? Aiko sɨ, aiko pe rʉꞌkwɨ rɨ apurɨtoꞌ auyaꞌnokon esi!<verse eid="MAT 6:30" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 6:31" />“Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ kɨsewankamatʉu, ‘Ɨꞌrɨ kuru ɨꞌtoꞌ pe?’ mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ‘Ɨꞌrɨ kuru ensitoꞌ pe?’ mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ‘Ɨꞌrɨ kuru eꞌtoꞌ pe upon kon pe?’ tukaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 6:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 6:32" />Apʉne pʉra Papa iꞌtunin nan pen eꞌtoꞌ ipɨkɨrɨ ton serɨ, mɨrɨpan ɨkʉipʉnʉ kon, Epʉn pon uya iꞌtu serɨ ton iꞌse ɨwesi kon. <verse eid="MAT 6:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 6:33" />Eꞌtane ruꞌku, wapiya kuru esaꞌ wannɨ pe iyeꞌtoꞌ iwarinpatɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipokenaꞌ pe iyeꞌtoꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tanporo serɨ ton nɨ nin si eꞌtʉrʉ mɨrɨ ɨyenaꞌnokon nɨ nɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 6:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 6:34" />Awanapairoꞌ pɨꞌ kɨsewankamai, tʉponaron nɨ mɨrɨ awanapairoꞌ pɨꞌ usewankaman; wʉi kaisa rɨ iponaroꞌ rɨ usewankaman nɨtoꞌ esi,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 6:34" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 6" />
  <chapter number="7" style="c" sid="MAT 7" />
  <para style="s1">Kaꞌpon Eseru Kʉsaimenkatʉu</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 6:37-38">Ʉruꞌ 6:37-38</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 6:41-42">41-42</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 7:1" />“Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ eseru kʉsaimenkatʉu, ɨyeseru kon nɨ nɨrɨ aimenka kʉseꞌnin. <verse eid="MAT 7:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 7:2" />Apʉne pʉra kaꞌpon amʉꞌ eseru maimenkayatʉiꞌneꞌ kasa rɨ marɨ ɨyeseru kon aimenka mɨrɨ. Iꞌtutoꞌ auyaꞌnokon yai pe rɨ ɨnkupʉꞌpʉ yai rɨ ɨyenaꞌnokon iꞌtu mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">7:2 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 4:24">Maꞌ 4:24</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 7:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 7:3" />“Ɨꞌrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ aiko rʉꞌkwɨ rɨ paranka punuꞌpɨ ɨnenpai ɨwesi ɨtonpa enu yawon, eke rɨ paranka eꞌtane ɨyenu yau? <verse eid="MAT 7:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 7:4" />Nai kasa ɨtonpa pɨꞌ, ‘Apʉne amuru simoꞌkaiꞌ ɨyenu apai,’ ta auya eke rɨ moro paranka eꞌtane ɨyenu yau? <verse eid="MAT 7:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 7:5" />Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan, wapiya kuru ɨyenu apai paranka imoꞌkakaꞌkɨ, mɨrɨ aꞌtai wakʉ pe ene auya ɨtonpa enu apai amuru moꞌka pa,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 7:5" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 7:6" />“Wakʉ pe teꞌsen kʉꞌtʉtʉu pero amʉꞌ enaꞌ; mokon pun ton ɨiwanoꞌ kon kʉsenoꞌmatʉu peiruku amʉꞌ enaꞌ, toꞌ uya iwasaꞌkapɨtʉ esi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ toꞌ eraꞌtɨ esi akarapɨꞌseꞌna.<verse eid="MAT 7:6" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Ekamaꞌpoꞌ, Iwarinpaꞌ, Iwɨpɨꞌkɨ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 11:9-13">Ʉruꞌ 11:9-13</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 7:7" />“Ekamaꞌpotɨꞌ; mɨrɨ aꞌtai, ɨyenaꞌnokon nɨ iyeꞌtʉrʉ. Iwarinpatɨꞌ; mɨrɨ aꞌtai, eporo auyaꞌnokon. Mʉraꞌta iwɨpɨꞌtɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan utaꞌkokatoꞌ pe ɨyenaꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 7:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 7:8" />Apʉne pʉra tanporon kon ekamaꞌpo pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ nan uya eporo; kʉrɨ rɨ iwarinpa pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ uya rɨ eporo, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kʉrɨ rɨ iwɨpɨtʉ pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ enaꞌ rɨ mʉraꞌta utaꞌkoka.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">7:8 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2ES 2:13">2 Estʉras 2:13</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 7:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 7:9" />Nai kʉrɨ warai uya tʉmu uya pʉreti ekamaꞌpo yau irepa tɨꞌ ke? <verse eid="MAT 7:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 7:10" />Mɨrɨ pe pʉra, moroꞌ ekamaꞌpo iya yau, irepa ɨkʉi ke? <verse eid="MAT 7:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 7:11" />Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon nin si ɨri ton uya iꞌtu yau wakʉ ton eꞌrepan nɨtoꞌ ke ɨmunkɨ kon amʉꞌ repa auyaꞌnokon, mɨrɨ entai kuru ɨkʉipʉnʉ kon, Epʉn pon uya wakʉ ton eꞌrepan nɨtoꞌ tʉrʉ kamoro ekamaꞌponin nan enaꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 7:11" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 7:12" />“Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ, tanporon yau rɨ ikuꞌtɨꞌ tʉron kon pɨꞌ, ikupʉ toꞌ uya iꞌse meꞌaiꞌneꞌ ɨpɨꞌnokon. Serɨ uya Main mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ rɨ nʉmenukaꞌpʉ amʉranʉkʉ mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">7:12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="TOB 4:15">Topayas 4:15</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 6:31">Ʉruꞌ 6:31</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 7:12" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Asaꞌron Asanta</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 13:24">Ʉruꞌ 13:24</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 7:13" />“Ewontɨꞌ aiko rʉꞌkwɨ mʉraꞌta awɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra eke mʉraꞌta mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ eke asanta esi umaꞌtan nɨtoꞌ yaꞌ utɨn eꞌma pe, mɨrɨpan tuꞌkan kon nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ewomʉ iyawɨrɨ, <verse eid="MAT 7:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 7:14" />eꞌtane aiko rʉꞌkwɨ mʉraꞌta mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ aiko rʉꞌkwɨ asanta esi wakʉ ukoꞌman nɨtoꞌ yaꞌ utɨn eꞌma pe, eꞌtane tuꞌkan kon pen nɨ utɨtoꞌ iyawɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">7:14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 15:17">Sairaꞌ 15:17</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 7:14" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Yʉi Mɨrɨ Awonsiꞌkɨ Iteperu</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 6:43-44">Ʉruꞌ 6:43-44</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 7:15" />Miyarɨ rɨ Sises esiꞌpʉ toꞌ enupa pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ, “Akono amʉꞌ pe teꞌsan entɨꞌ; toꞌ uyepʉ karimeru kasa, eꞌtane ɨsɨ ton, ene amʉꞌ kasa toꞌ esi. <verse eid="MAT 7:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 7:16" />Toꞌ iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon mɨrɨ toꞌ eperu winɨ. Tikʉ kenan apai peꞌ kʉreꞌ pʉipɨꞌnin nan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra piꞌ rɨ ɨmɨꞌnɨꞌta apai?<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">7:16 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 27:6">Sairaꞌ 27:6</ref></char></note> (Kane.) <verse eid="MAT 7:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 7:17" />Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, wakʉ yʉi epeta wakʉ pe rɨ, ɨri yʉi epeta ɨri pe rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 7:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 7:18" />Wakʉ yʉi epeta pʉra iyesi ɨri pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨri yʉi epeta pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ wakʉ pe. <verse eid="MAT 7:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 7:19" />Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya tʉusepetasen pen yʉi aꞌtɨ enoꞌmatoꞌ pe tʉuyaꞌnokon apoꞌ yaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">7:19 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 3:10">Maꞌsiu 3:10</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:9">Ʉruꞌ 3:9</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 7:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 7:20" />Mɨrɨ kasa toꞌ eperu winɨ toꞌ iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">7:20 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 12:33">Maꞌsiu 12:33</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 7:20" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Papa Rɨken Apurɨkɨ Tʉusewankamaiꞌ Pʉra</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 13:25-27">Ʉruꞌ 13:25-27</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 7:21" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ, “Tanporon kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ, ‘Uyepuru, uyepuru!’ tawon nan upɨꞌ epaꞌkatoꞌ oton pen nɨ Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe pataꞌseꞌ yaꞌ, eꞌtane kʉrɨ rɨken ukʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon eꞌtoꞌ iꞌse kuꞌnin. <verse eid="MAT 7:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 7:22" />Iweyu eꞌseposaꞌ aꞌtai, tuꞌkan kon nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya tatoꞌ oton upɨꞌ, ‘Uyepuru, uyepuru, puꞌkenaꞌ pe peꞌ ina usaurokʉ pʉn ɨyeseꞌ yau, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨyeseꞌ yau peꞌ ɨri aꞌkwarʉ ton enpaꞌkapɨtʉꞌpʉ ina uya pʉn, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ eke Papa tʉrawasooi kuꞌpɨtʉ pʉn peꞌ ina uya?’ <verse eid="MAT 7:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 7:23" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, tʉwapuꞌtɨiꞌ pʉra toꞌ pɨꞌ ekamatoꞌ uya oton, ‘Ɨiꞌtusaꞌ uya ꞌnokon pʉra man. Entantɨꞌ upiyapai, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon ɨri kuꞌnin nan!’” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">7:23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 6:8">Eren 6:8</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 7:23" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Asaꞌron Kon Ɨutɨ Amɨnin Nan</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 6:47-49">Ʉruꞌ 6:47-49</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 7:24" />“Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, tanporon kon serɨ ton umaimu ton eta pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ nan mɨrɨpan kupʉ pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ nan esi mɨrɨ taꞌkwarʉ kenan kaꞌpon kasa tɨꞌ po tiwʉꞌ amɨnin. <verse eid="MAT 7:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 7:25" />Tuna uyeeꞌpʉ, tuna apɨrʉ ton uꞌmaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ aꞌsetun uyeeꞌpʉ eꞌseꞌneꞌ pe ɨutɨ tʉwɨse, eꞌtane itaꞌmoꞌkaꞌpʉ pen nɨ, apʉne pʉra tɨꞌ po iyapon esi pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 7:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 7:26" />Eꞌtane tanporon kon serɨ ton umaimu ton eta pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ nan mɨrɨpan kupʉ toꞌ uya pʉra naꞌneꞌ nan esi mɨrɨ iyaꞌkwarʉ pʉn kaꞌpon kasa tiwʉꞌ amɨnin wɨꞌsɨꞌ po. <verse eid="MAT 7:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 7:27" />Tuna uyeeꞌpʉ, tuna apɨrʉ ton uꞌmaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ aꞌsetun uyeeꞌpʉ eꞌseꞌneꞌ pe ɨutɨ tʉwɨse, mɨrɨpan utaꞌmoꞌka uya eke pe pata aꞌmerunpaꞌpʉ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 7:27" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Meruntɨrʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 7:28" />Serɨ ton pɨꞌ Sises usaurokʉ eꞌnonkasaꞌ aꞌtai, anpisin ton nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ usewansiukaꞌpʉ enupan nɨtoꞌ iya pɨꞌ, <verse eid="MAT 7:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 7:29" />apʉne pʉra enupan iya pɨꞌ tʉmeruntɨrʉ kenan pe kuru rɨ, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan kasa pʉra.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">7:28-29 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 1:22">Maꞌ 1:22</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 4:32">Ʉruꞌ 4:32</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 7:29" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 7" />
  <chapter number="8" style="c" sid="MAT 8" />
  <para style="s1">Erekʉꞌpan Kaꞌpon Epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 1:40-45">Maꞌ 1:40-45</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 5:12-16">Ʉruꞌ 5:12-16</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 8:1" />Wʉꞌ ponsiꞌkɨ Sises uꞌtɨsaꞌ aꞌtai, anpisin ton nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya eꞌmaꞌpʉkaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 8:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 8:2" />Erekʉꞌpan kaꞌpon<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">8:2 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Erekʉꞌpan kaꞌpon; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Leper, </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Enkeriꞌsi pe. Kiriꞌ maimu yau utapurɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ tuꞌkan nɨ piꞌpɨ eparan eseꞌ pe, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">leprosy </char><char style="ft" closed="false">kuru pen nɨ pɨꞌ.</char></note> uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan eꞌsekunkaꞌpʉ irau. Mɨrɨpan uya, “Uyepuru, ɨnkuꞌpai ɨwesi yau, wakʉ pe rɨ ukupʉ auya,” taꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 8:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 8:3" />Temiyatʉ ɨnkaꞌpʉ Sises uya, mɨrɨpan uya aꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ, “Ɨnkuꞌpai rɨ eꞌaiꞌ, wakʉ pe eꞌkɨ!” taꞌpʉ iya ipɨꞌ. Inke pʉra rɨ, tʉwereei apai iyekonekaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 8:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 8:4" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uya, “Ɨnʉꞌ pɨꞌ rɨ kʉsekamai,” taꞌpʉ, “eꞌtane enta ɨsenpoikata useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin enaꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨntʉrʉnʉ pe teꞌsen Mosiꞌ uya tasaꞌ naꞌneꞌ awɨrɨ mʉtʉrʉiꞌ. Mɨrɨ uya rɨ nin si ɨusepiꞌtɨsaꞌ ekama mɨrɨ toꞌ pɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">8:4 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LEV 14:1-32">Ripaitiꞌkas 14:1-32</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 8:4" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Soisa Amʉꞌ Epuru Poitorʉ Epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 7:1-10">Ʉruꞌ 7:1-10</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 8:5" />Sises epaꞌkasaꞌ aꞌtai, Kaꞌpaneyan pona, soisa amʉꞌ epuru uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ tʉpikaꞌtɨtoꞌ pe iya ekamaꞌposeꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 8:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 8:6" />“Uyepuru, upoitorʉ man ipan pe eꞌneꞌ pe, ipuꞌtɨkaꞌsaꞌ teꞌkweꞌ tau rɨ iyesi, pata po,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 8:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 8:7" />“Miyarɨ rɨ utɨ mɨrɨ epiꞌtɨiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 8:7" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 8:8" />Soisa amʉꞌ epuru uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Uyepuru, uiwʉꞌ taꞌ ɨuyepʉ pokenaꞌ pen nɨ urɨ. Amaimu rɨken itʉkɨ; mɨrɨ aꞌtai, upoitorʉ usepiꞌtɨtoꞌ pe. <verse eid="MAT 8:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 8:9" />Apʉne pʉra urɨ kʉrɨ rɨ tepuru kenan, soisa amʉꞌ esaꞌ uwoꞌnoro teꞌsan. Pʉse pɨꞌ, ‘Enta,’ ta uya aꞌtai, itɨ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kʉrɨ pɨꞌ, ‘Ɨsiꞌkɨ,’ ta uya aꞌtai, iyepʉ. Upoitorʉ pɨꞌ, ‘Se ikuꞌkɨ,’ ta uya aꞌtai, ikupʉ iya,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">8:9 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="BAR 3:33-35">Paruꞌ 3:33-35</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 8:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 8:10" />Sises uya serɨ etasaꞌ aꞌtai, isewansiukaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ tʉpɨkɨrɨ teꞌsan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ, “Iꞌnapairon ekama uya serɨ ɨpɨꞌnokon, ɨnʉꞌ rɨ eposaꞌ uya pʉra rɨ man Esuwerʉ po eke rɨ serɨ waraino apurɨtoꞌ esaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 8:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 8:11" />Ta uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, tuꞌkan kon nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uyeꞌtoꞌ oton pata wʉi enu uyepʉ, wʉi enu utɨ winɨꞌne, mɨrɨpan kon ereutatoꞌ oton entaꞌnan pɨꞌ Epʉraꞌan, Aisiꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Sekoꞌ pokon pe Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">8:11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 13:29">Ʉruꞌ 13:29</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 8:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 8:12" />Eꞌtane esaꞌ wannɨ pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ yau teꞌton kon tasaꞌ kon nʉꞌsan enoꞌmatoꞌ iya oton ewarupɨ yaꞌ, ukaran nɨtoꞌ oton, ɨ eꞌkɨtɨtɨiꞌmatoꞌ oton yaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">8:12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 22:13">Maꞌsiu 22:13</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 25:30">25:30</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 13:28">Ʉruꞌ 13:28</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 8:12" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 8:13" />Mɨrɨpan soisa amʉꞌ epuru pɨꞌ Sises uya taꞌpʉ, “Ennaꞌpoꞌ, anapurɨnʉ awɨrɨ rɨ ɨpoitorʉ usepiꞌtɨ mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai rɨ, ipoitorʉ usepiꞌtɨꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 8:13" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tuꞌkan Kon Nɨ Epiꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 1:29-34">Maꞌ 1:29-34</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 4:38-41">Ʉruꞌ 4:38-41</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 8:14" />Sises utɨꞌpʉ Piꞌta iwʉꞌ taꞌ. Mɨrɨ yau, Piꞌta ewoꞌpʉ eneꞌpʉ iya teꞌkweꞌ tau eꞌkɨɨiꞌman pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 8:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 8:15" />Mɨrɨpan uya itemiyatʉ pɨꞌ aꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai rɨ, iyeꞌkɨɨiꞌmatoꞌ ereutaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ toꞌ mʉtaꞌnapaseꞌna.<verse eid="MAT 8:15" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 8:16" />Pata ukoꞌmansaꞌ aꞌtai, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya tuꞌkan kon nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ makoi aꞌkwarʉ yen ton pe teꞌsan neeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ. Se kasa rɨ tʉusauroꞌse makoi aꞌkwarʉ ton ennokoꞌpʉ iya, tanporo rɨ takuruꞌkenaꞌ nan epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 8:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 8:17" />Serɨ ton kupʉꞌpʉ iya pena puꞌkenaꞌ Aisaya nekamaꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ aꞌkuꞌtɨ pe:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 8:17">“Ɨꞌsɨꞌmʉra eꞌnɨtoꞌ moꞌkaꞌpʉ iya,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 8:17">mɨrɨpan uya uyeparan kon arɨꞌpʉ,”<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">8:17 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Aisaya 53:4 </char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 8:17">tawon.<verse eid="MAT 8:17" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tʉpɨkɨrɨ Eꞌpaino Kon Auroꞌkaꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 9:57-62">Ʉruꞌ 9:57-62</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 8:18" />Sises uya anpisin ensaꞌ aꞌtai tʉwoi, tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ, “Parau kuꞌpɨri ratoi pona eꞌkwɨrɨꞌnɨpaiꞌnokon,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 8:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 8:19" />Mɨrɨpan Main pɨꞌ enupanin uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ, “Uyepuru, siya rɨ mʉtɨyaiꞌneꞌ yaꞌ rɨ ayaꞌkɨrɨ utɨ serɨ,” taseꞌna ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 8:19" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 8:20" />Sises uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Maikan amʉꞌ kamoro tenkenaꞌ nan, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ toron amʉꞌ kanan esi tʉpon ke, eꞌtane Kaꞌpon, Papa winon esi mɨrɨ tiꞌpai nonkatoꞌ iya yau pʉn nɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 8:20" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 8:21" />Tʉron nɨ kanan kaꞌpon Sises poitorʉ pe eꞌpaino uya, “Uyepuru, apʉne ken si, wapiya ukʉipʉnʉ siuꞌnaꞌtɨkaꞌtaiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 8:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 8:22" />Eꞌtane Sises uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Tɨwɨ tʉꞌkoroꞌtauꞌnokon teꞌsen eriꞌsaꞌ uꞌnaꞌtɨi toꞌ; uyaꞌkɨrɨ ruꞌku utɨnpai,” taꞌpʉ iya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 8:22" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Ɨsɨ Rɨ Aꞌsetun Iꞌnɨꞌpanʉkʉꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 4:35-41">Maꞌ 4:35-41</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 8:22-25">Ʉruꞌ 8:22-25</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 8:23" />Sises ekanwaꞌtɨꞌpʉ kanau yaꞌ, mɨrɨpan aꞌkɨrɨ ipoitorʉ ton utɨꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 8:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 8:24" />Mɨrɨ koroꞌtau, iteꞌkwanau pʉra rɨ panaꞌ pe, ɨsɨ pe rɨ aꞌsetun uyeeꞌpʉ parau kuꞌpɨri kaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya eke pe rɨ sipaꞌsipa kupʉꞌpʉ tuna pʉroꞌpo. Eke pe sipaꞌsipa esi uya toꞌ kanwa paruꞌtɨ esiꞌpʉ, eꞌtane rɨ Sises esiꞌpʉ eꞌnʉn nɨ pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 8:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 8:25" />Ipoitorʉ ton utɨꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ enpakaseꞌna, taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ, “Ina epuru! Ina ipikaꞌtɨkɨ! Ina aputan pɨꞌ man!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 8:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 8:26" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon, aiko rʉꞌkwɨ apurɨtoꞌ iya toꞌ ton, ɨꞌrɨ pɨꞌ ɨyetʉipɨtʉ kon?” taꞌpʉ iya. Iyeꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya aꞌsetun mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ sipaꞌsipa eseremekʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan eꞌnɨꞌpamʉꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 8:26" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 8:27" />Kamoro si kaꞌpon amʉꞌ usewansiukaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan kon usekamaꞌpopɨtʉꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ pan si pʉse rɨ kaꞌpon? Aꞌsetun mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ sipaꞌsipa rɨ eꞌtoꞌ imaimu awɨrɨ!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 8:27" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Uya Makoi Aꞌkwarʉ Ton Ennokoꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 5:1-20">Maꞌ 5:1-20</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 8:26-39">Ʉruꞌ 8:26-39</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 8:28" />Sises mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoitorʉ ton uya si parau kuꞌpɨri Kiyarari nʉꞌkwɨrɨꞌnʉꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ Katara nono po tʉukoꞌmansan, asaꞌron kon makoi aꞌkwarʉ yen ton pe teꞌsan uyeeꞌpʉ uruwaiꞌ apai toꞌ winɨkʉiꞌ. Ɨsɨ ton nɨ, ɨnʉꞌ utɨ pokenaꞌ pen nɨ mɨrɨ awɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 8:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 8:29" />Mɨrɨpan kon ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ pe ina kuꞌseꞌna ɨuyeꞌsaꞌ, Papa Mumu? Iweyu rawɨrɨ rɨ peꞌ ina kotaꞌmaiꞌ ɨuyeꞌsaꞌ?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 8:29" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 8:30" />Ɨnnɨ kuru pʉra rɨ toꞌ piyapai tuꞌkan kon nɨ peiruku amʉꞌ esiꞌpʉ entaꞌnan pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 8:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 8:31" />Makoi aꞌkwarʉ yen ton uya Sises ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ ipan pe, “Ina ken si ennoko auya aꞌtai pʉsamo kaꞌpon amʉꞌ apai, apʉne ken si ina ennoꞌkɨ kamo tuꞌkan kon peiruku amʉꞌ yaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 8:31" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 8:32" />“Entantɨꞌ si,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya toꞌ pɨꞌ. Toꞌ epaꞌkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon utɨꞌpʉ peiruku amʉꞌ yaꞌ ewonseꞌna. Tanporo rɨ si kamoro peiruku amʉꞌ ekaꞌtumʉꞌpʉ mɨrɨ parau kuꞌpɨri kaꞌ tepitoren awɨrɨ rɨ, mɨrɨpan kon aputapɨtʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 8:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 8:33" />Mɨrɨ yau, toꞌ mainanpa pɨꞌ teꞌsan ekaꞌtumʉꞌpʉ pata pona, mɨrɨpan kon uya tanporo iyeꞌkuꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ ekamaꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ. Toꞌ uya rɨ nɨrɨ kamo makoi aꞌkwarʉ yen ton pe teꞌsan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ iyeꞌkuꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ ekamaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 8:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 8:34" />Mɨrɨpan tanporo rɨ mɨrɨ pata yau teꞌsan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ utɨꞌpʉ Sises enseꞌna. Toꞌ uya Sises ensaꞌ aꞌtai, tʉnono kon apai iyennaꞌpotoꞌ pe ipan pe toꞌ uya auroꞌkaꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 8:34" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 8" />
  <chapter number="9" style="c" sid="MAT 9" />
  <para style="s1">Ipuꞌtɨkaꞌsaꞌ Kaꞌpon Epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 2:1-12">Maꞌ 2:1-12</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 5:17-26">Ʉruꞌ 5:17-26</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 9:1" />Sises mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoitorʉ ton ekanwaꞌtɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon ɨꞌkwɨrɨtʉꞌpʉ. Toꞌ uyeeꞌpʉ tʉpataꞌseꞌ kon yaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 9:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 9:2" />Tʉron kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya ipuꞌtɨkaꞌsaꞌ neeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ. Sises uya pʉsamoro kaꞌpon amʉꞌ napurɨnʉ eneꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya ipuꞌtɨkaꞌsaꞌ pɨꞌ, “Utonpa, kenariꞌnʉmʉi, amakooi pɨꞌ usentuꞌmasaꞌ man,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 9:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 9:3" />Serɨ etasaꞌ Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan tonpa ton uya aꞌtai, “Pʉse rɨ kaꞌpon usaurokʉ Papa sapema pe rɨ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya tewan kon yau.<verse eid="MAT 9:3" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 9:4" />Sises uya toꞌ usenuminkatoꞌ iꞌtuꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨtoꞌ pe ɨri pe rɨ ɨusenuminka kon ɨyewan kon yau? <verse eid="MAT 9:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 9:5" />Nai esi saꞌman pe pʉra: ‘Amakooi pɨꞌ usentuꞌma,’ ta; mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ‘Eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌ, asakɨ,’ ta katɨ ipuꞌtɨkaꞌsaꞌ pɨꞌ? <verse eid="MAT 9:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 9:6" />Iꞌtu kon pa, Kaꞌpon, Papa winon piyau meruntɨ esi serɨ non po makoi pɨꞌ usentuꞌman nɨtoꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya. Sises uya taꞌpʉ ipuꞌtɨkaꞌsaꞌ kaꞌpon pɨꞌ, “Eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkakɨ, ayapon anʉnkɨ, ennaꞌpokɨ si apataꞌseꞌ yaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 9:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 9:7" />Pʉse rɨ kaꞌpon enaꞌpʉ wakʉ pe, mɨrɨpan eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkasaꞌ, ennaꞌpoꞌpʉ tʉpataꞌseꞌ yaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 9:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 9:8" />Serɨ ensaꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, ipan pe rɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enariꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ. Toꞌ uya si Papa apurɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ eke rɨ serɨ meruntɨ tʉsaꞌ iya pɨꞌ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enaꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 9:8" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Maꞌsiu Kɨꞌmaꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 2:13-17">Maꞌ 2:13-17</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 5:27-32">Ʉruꞌ 5:27-32</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 9:9" />Sises uya si mɨrɨ pata nɨmɨ aꞌtai, kaꞌpon ereutasaꞌ eneꞌpʉ iya pʉrata amʉranʉꞌnin pe eꞌnɨ iwʉꞌ tau, Maꞌsiu iteseꞌ. Sises uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Ɨsiꞌkɨ upoitorʉ pe, Maꞌsiu,” taꞌpʉ iya. Mɨrɨpan eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ, iyaꞌkɨrɨ itɨꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 9:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 9:10" />Sises entaꞌna koroꞌtau Maꞌsiu iwʉꞌ tau, tuꞌkan kon nɨ pʉrata amʉranʉꞌnin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉmakooikenaꞌ nan uyeeꞌpʉ ipokon pe entaꞌnaseꞌna, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoitorʉ ton pokon pe rɨ nɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 9:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 9:11" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ uya serɨ ensaꞌ aꞌtai, taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya Sises poitorʉ ton pɨꞌ, “Ɨꞌrɨtoꞌ pe ɨtiꞌsaai kon entaꞌna pʉrata amʉranʉꞌnin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉmakooikenaꞌ nan pokon pe rɨ?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9:10-11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 15:1-2">Ʉruꞌ 15:1-2</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 9:11" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 9:12" />Sises uya toꞌ etaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon pɨꞌ taꞌpʉ iya, “Atuꞌ kaꞌpon esi pen mɨrɨ taꞌta iꞌse eꞌtane, takuruꞌkenan esi iꞌse. <verse eid="MAT 9:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 9:13" />Ɨsenupatantɨꞌ, ɨꞌrɨ ta iya eꞌkwa pe serɨ esi tukaiꞌ: ‘Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ iꞌse esi ɨsentuꞌkenaꞌ pe, oꞌ ke tʉuseꞌmasan iꞌse esi pen,’<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9:13 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="HOS 6:6">Oseya 6:6</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 12:7">Maꞌsiu 12:7</ref></char></note> tawon. Uyeꞌsaꞌ serɨ ipokenaꞌ ton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ kɨꞌmaiꞌ pen, eꞌtane uyeꞌsaꞌ serɨ tʉmakooikenaꞌ nan kɨꞌmaseꞌna,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 9:13" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Emennaꞌ Eꞌsumatoꞌ Pe Pʉra Iyesi Mɨrɨ Penaroꞌ Pokon Pe</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 2:18-22">Maꞌ 2:18-22</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 5:33-39">Ʉruꞌ 5:33-39</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 9:14" />Mɨrɨ tʉpo, Isaan poitorʉ ton uyeeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ. Toꞌ uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Ɨꞌrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ ina mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ useruma tentaꞌnaiꞌ pʉra, eꞌtane ɨpoitorʉ ton useruma pʉra iyesi?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 9:14" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 9:15" />Sises uya toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ, “Nai kasa warawoꞌ temariꞌmasen nʉkɨꞌmaꞌsan esi tʉutaꞌkwarʉkaiꞌ ukaran nɨ pɨꞌ tʉpiyauꞌnokon nɨ iyeꞌtane? Iweyu rɨ eꞌseporo mɨrɨ temariꞌmasen utanʉntoꞌ oton toꞌ piyapai, mɨrɨ aꞌtai nin si toꞌ useruma mɨrɨ tentaꞌnaiꞌ pʉra,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 9:15" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 9:16" />Sises uya rɨ taꞌpʉ, “Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ pon pooiꞌpɨ pona pon atʉ punuꞌpɨ aꞌsiꞌtɨ pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ; emennaꞌ pon punuꞌpɨ uya ipooiꞌpɨ pon karaka mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan uya eke pe iteuta kupʉ mɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 9:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 9:17" />Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya emennaꞌ waain entɨ pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ ipooiꞌpɨ iten yaꞌ. Mɨrɨ kuꞌsaꞌ toꞌ uya aꞌtai, emennaꞌ waain uya penaroꞌ rʉꞌpʉ iten toiꞌkwa rɨ mɨrɨ; mɨrɨ tʉpo, asaꞌrɨ rɨ marɨ waain mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iten umaꞌtasaꞌ rɨ mɨrɨ. Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya emennaꞌ waain entɨtoꞌ pe iyesi emennaꞌ iten yaꞌ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, asaꞌrɨ rɨ marɨ wakʉ pe iyesi mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 9:17" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Iyeriꞌsaꞌ Uriꞌsan Mʉre Mɨrɨ Awonsiꞌkɨ Takuruꞌkenan Uriꞌsan</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 5:21-43">Maꞌ 5:21-43</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 8:40-56">Ʉruꞌ 8:40-56</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 9:18" />Serɨ rɨ ta Sises uya koroꞌtau, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ. Iyeꞌsekunkaꞌpʉ Sises rakʉiꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Uyensi umaꞌtasaꞌ man serɨ pe rɨ, eꞌtane uyaꞌkɨrɨ ɨsiꞌkɨ uiwʉꞌ taꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ aꞌpɨꞌtanʉꞌkɨ itoꞌpantoꞌ pe,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 9:18" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 9:19" />Sises eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ iyaꞌkɨrɨ. Ipoitorʉ ton nɨ nɨrɨ utɨꞌpʉ iyaꞌkɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 9:19" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 9:20" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai rɨ, uriꞌsan, mʉn ennoko pɨꞌ teꞌsen uyeeꞌpʉ ipɨkɨrɨ, ipon eꞌpi aꞌpɨꞌseꞌna. Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ ikoꞌmansaꞌ esiꞌpʉ 12 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya. <verse eid="MAT 9:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 9:21" />Tewan yau rʉꞌkwɨ rɨ, “Sises pon nɨ aꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ uya yau, usepiꞌtɨ rɨ mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 9:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 9:22" />Sises eraꞌtɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya eneꞌpʉ. Taꞌpʉ iya ipɨꞌ, “Kɨsewankamai, maꞌnon. Papa uya ɨyepiꞌtɨsaꞌ mɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra apurɨ auya ke,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya ipɨꞌ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai rɨ, uriꞌsan usepiꞌtɨꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 9:22" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 9:23" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises ewomʉꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru iwʉꞌ taꞌ. Mɨrɨ yau, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ, sarakuwa turunpa pɨꞌ teꞌsan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉron kon ukaran nɨ pɨꞌ teꞌsan ene tʉuya aꞌtai, <verse eid="MAT 9:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 9:24" />taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Entantɨꞌ, iyeriꞌsaꞌ pen mɨrɨ; iyeꞌnʉnsaꞌ rɨ nin mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya. Eꞌtane toꞌ utaꞌkɨrɨꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 9:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 9:25" />Pʉroroi pona toꞌ enpaꞌka tʉpo, ɨutɨ taꞌ iyewomʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya uriꞌsan anʉmʉꞌpʉ itemiyatʉ pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan utoꞌpamʉꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 9:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 9:26" />Mɨrɨpan ekareei utɨꞌpʉ siya rɨ mɨrɨ nono kaisarɨ rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 9:26" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tenkuꞌnaꞌ Nan Epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 9:27" />Sises uya si mɨrɨ pata nɨmɨ koroꞌtau, asaꞌron kon tenkuꞌnaꞌ nan uya eꞌmaꞌpʉkaꞌpʉ. Toꞌ ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨtʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Ɨmɨrɨ, Tepiꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ, ina pɨꞌ ɨsentuꞌmaꞌ!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 9:27" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 9:28" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si ɨutɨ taꞌ Sises ewonkaꞌsaꞌ koroꞌtau, toꞌ uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ. Toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ iya, “Mapurɨyatʉu peꞌ ɨyepiꞌtɨ uya ꞌnokon tukaiꞌ?” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 9:28">Mɨrɨpan kon uya si taꞌpʉ, “Ewaiꞌ, Uyepuru, ina uya rɨ ayapurɨ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 9:28" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 9:29" />Mɨrɨ tʉpo, Sises uya toꞌ enu aꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ, “Ɨsepiꞌtɨtɨꞌ si, apurɨ auyaꞌnokon ke,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 9:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 9:30" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ennin nan pe si toꞌ enaꞌpʉ. Mɨrɨ tʉpo, Sises uya taꞌpʉ ipan pe toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ kʉꞌpanaꞌtɨtʉu serɨ pɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 9:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 9:31" />Eꞌtane rɨ toꞌ utɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya serɨ si itekareei ekamaꞌpʉ siya rɨ mɨrɨ nono kaisarɨ rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 9:31" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 9:32" />Toꞌ utɨkaꞌtane rɨ, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya makoi yen, tʉusauroꞌsen pen kaꞌpon neeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 9:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 9:33" />Mɨrɨpan enpaꞌkasaꞌ iya aꞌtai, isaurokʉꞌpʉ. Ipan pe rɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ usewansiukaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya taꞌpʉ, “Serɨ waraino eꞌkupʉ ensaꞌ pʉra rɨ iyesi wapiya Esuwerʉ po!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 9:33" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 9:34" />Eꞌtane Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ uya taꞌpʉ, “Makoi amʉꞌ epuru winɨ makoi amʉꞌ enpaꞌkapɨtʉ iya,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9:34 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 10:25">Maꞌsiu 10:25</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 12:24">12:24</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 3:22">Maꞌ 3:22</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 11:15">Ʉruꞌ 11:15</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 9:34" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tuꞌkan Kon Pen Nɨ Tʉrawaso Amʉꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 9:35" />Sises utɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ tanporon eke iwa ton pata yauꞌne, mɨrɨpan uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enupaꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ usenupatoꞌ iwʉꞌ tauꞌne. Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe ekareei ekamaꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan uya tanporo kaꞌpon amʉꞌ epiꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ tiꞌtuiꞌ pʉra paran pɨꞌ takuruꞌke teꞌsan.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9:35 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 4:23">Maꞌsiu 4:23</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 1:39">Maꞌ 1:39</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 4:44">Ʉruꞌ 4:44</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 9:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 9:36" />Tuꞌkan kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ensaꞌ tʉuya aꞌtai, toꞌ pɨꞌ isentuꞌmaꞌpʉ, apʉne pʉra ipan pe rɨ usewankaman pɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tiwanoꞌ kon pe toꞌ epikaꞌtɨ poken pʉra rɨ toꞌ esi pɨꞌ. Toꞌ esiꞌpʉ karimeru amʉꞌ ipaꞌsimanin pʉnon kon kasa.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9:36 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="NUM 27:17">Nonpa 27:17</ref>; <ref loc="1KI 22:17">1 Kin Amʉꞌ 22:17</ref>; <ref loc="2CH 18:16">2 Kʉronoꞌkʉrʉs 18:16</ref>; <ref loc="EZK 34:5">Isiꞌkiyerʉ 34:5</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 6:34">Maꞌ 6:34</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 9:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 9:37" />Mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ, “Eke pe rɨ umɨ yau kiyari akʉꞌpʉsaꞌ tanʉnsen man eꞌtane, tuꞌke pʉra tʉrawaso amʉꞌ amʉranʉꞌnin nan esi. <verse eid="MAT 9:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 9:38" />Umɨ esaꞌ ekamaꞌpotɨꞌ, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ennoꞌtoꞌ pe iya kiyari akʉꞌpʉsaꞌ anʉmʉ amʉranʉꞌnin nan pe,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9:38 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 10:2">Ʉruꞌ 10:2</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 9:38" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 9" />
  <chapter number="10" style="c" sid="MAT 10" />
  <para style="s1">Sises Uya 12 Kaisaron Kon Tʉpoitorʉ Ton Ennokoꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 10:1" />12 kaisaron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton kɨꞌmaꞌpʉ iya tʉpiyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon repaꞌpʉ iya ɨri aꞌkwarʉ paꞌkatoꞌ meruntɨrʉ ke, tiꞌtuiꞌ pʉra rɨ paran ton pɨꞌ takuruꞌkeꞌne teꞌsan nɨrɨ epiꞌtɨpɨꞌnin nan pe. <verse eid="MAT 10:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 10:2" />Pʉsamoro naꞌneꞌ 12 kaisaron kon ennoꞌsaꞌ kon eseꞌ ton: wapiya Saiman (Piꞌta tukaiꞌ tesaꞌsen), iyakon Anturu; Isens, Sepiti mu, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyakon Isaan; <verse eid="MAT 10:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 10:3" />Piriꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Paꞌtaramiu; Tamas, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Maꞌsiu, Roman kopʉnaai enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ amʉranʉꞌnin; Isens (Arʉꞌpiyas mu), mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Tatiyas; <verse eid="MAT 10:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 10:4" />Saiman, Useraꞌ tukaiꞌ tesaꞌsen;<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">10:4 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Useraꞌ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">–Roman amʉꞌ enapai temoꞌka kon iꞌseroꞌ.</char></note> mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Isutas Eskariyaꞌ, eparankanin pe iyesiꞌpʉ naꞌneꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 10:4" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 10:5" />Pʉsamoro 12 kaisaron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton ennokoꞌpʉ iya toꞌ tauroꞌkaiꞌ se kasa: “Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ ton pen nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ piyaꞌ kʉtɨtʉu, mɨrɨ pe pʉra kepaꞌkatʉu Sameriya pata ton yaꞌ rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 10:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 10:6" />Eꞌtane Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ piyaꞌ entantɨꞌ, karimeru utanoꞌmasaꞌ waraino kon piyaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 10:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 10:7" />Ɨutɨ kon pe rɨ, serɨ itekare mekamatʉiꞌ: ‘Aꞌko pe Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe man,’ tukaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 10:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 10:8" />Takuruꞌkenan kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ mepiꞌtɨtʉiꞌ, iyeriꞌsaꞌ kon nɨrɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ miꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkapɨꞌtʉiꞌ. Ereꞌ pɨꞌ teꞌsan mepiꞌtɨtʉiꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨri aꞌkwarʉ ton menpaꞌkapɨꞌtʉiꞌ. Teꞌmaiꞌ pʉra eposaꞌ auyaꞌnokon kasa rɨ, teꞌmaiꞌ pʉra mʉtʉtʉiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 10:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 10:9" />Korʉ, sirʉpa, kaꞌpa rɨ kʉsatʉu ɨpokʉrʉʉi kon yau; <verse eid="MAT 10:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 10:10" />paiki, sapato, tekeꞌsen, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tuꞌke ipona ɨpon kon kʉsatʉu ayaꞌkɨrɨꞌnokon, apʉne pʉra tʉrawaso amʉꞌ pe ɨwesi kon, mɨrɨ epeꞌpʉ rɨ eporo auyaꞌnokon,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:10 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1CO 9:14">1 Koren 9:14</ref>; <ref loc="1TI 5:18">1 Temuꞌti 5:18</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 10:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 10:11" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ, “Eke iwa pata yaꞌ ɨutɨ kon aꞌtai, wakʉ pe tiwʉꞌ kon taꞌ ɨyereutanʉꞌnin kon mɨnentʉiꞌ. Itiwʉꞌ tau meꞌtʉiꞌ inɨmɨ auyaꞌnokon pona rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 10:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 10:12" />Toꞌ iwʉꞌ taꞌ ɨyewomʉ kon aꞌtai, ‘Miyarɨ,’ mʉkatʉiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 10:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 10:13" />Toꞌ uya ɨyereutanʉkʉ kon aꞌtai, tɨwɨ ‘Miyarɨ,’ taꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon nɨ neꞌnonkai toꞌ pona. Mɨrɨ kupʉ toꞌ uya pʉra iyesi aꞌtai ɨpɨꞌnokon, mʉnaꞌpotʉiꞌ toꞌ piyapai. <verse eid="MAT 10:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 10:14" />Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ wakʉ pe ɨyereutanʉkʉ kon pʉra iyesi yau, mɨrɨ pe pʉra amaimu kon eta toꞌ uya pʉra iyesi yau, aꞌta kon mʉtɨutɨpɨꞌtʉiꞌ mɨrɨ pata nɨmɨ auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 13:51">Inkupʉꞌpʉ 13:51</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 10:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 10:15" />Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, Satan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Komora uya imoronka poken parɨ iyeꞌtoꞌ oton eseru aimenka weyu aꞌtai mɨrɨ pata uya imoronka entai iyeꞌtane,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:15 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 11:24">Maꞌsiu 11:24</ref>; <ref loc="GEN 19:24-28">Iseneses 19:24-28</ref></char></note><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:7-15 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 10:4-12">Ʉruꞌ 10:4-12</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 10:15" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Kaꞌpon Amʉꞌ Uya Sises Kotaꞌmatoꞌ Oton</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 10:16" />Sises esiꞌpʉ miyarɨ rɨ 12 kaisaron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton auroꞌka pɨꞌ. Taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Ɨyennoko uya ꞌnokon serɨ ɨri ton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ koroꞌtaꞌ, karimeru ennoko kasa ɨsɨ ton, ene amʉꞌ koroꞌtau. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, emepokeꞌ pe meꞌtʉiꞌ ɨkʉi kasa, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨsɨ pe pʉra wakoꞌwa kasa meꞌtʉiꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:16 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 10:3">Ʉruꞌ 10:3</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 10:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 10:17" />Tenu ke nɨrɨ meꞌtʉiꞌ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ; toꞌ uya ɨtʉtoꞌ oton kon mɨrɨ pata epuru ton enaꞌ. Toꞌ uya nɨrɨ ayariꞌpoꞌpɨꞌtoꞌ oton kon mɨrɨ tʉusenupatoꞌ kon iwʉꞌ tauꞌne. <verse eid="MAT 10:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 10:18" />Toꞌ uya ayatoꞌ oton kon mɨrɨ kopʉna mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kin amʉꞌ piyaꞌ urɨ wenai, urɨ ekama kon pa Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ pen pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 10:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 10:19" />Eꞌtane kɨsewankamatʉu toꞌ uya ayaꞌsisaꞌ kon aꞌtai, ɨꞌrɨ ta uya, nai kasa ta uya tukaiꞌ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, amaimuꞌtɨ uya ꞌnokon mɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 10:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 10:20" />Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon pe ausaurokʉ kon pen mɨrɨ, eꞌtane ɨkʉipʉnʉ kon Aꞌkwarʉ usauroꞌtoꞌ oton mɨrɨ ayawɨrɨꞌnokon.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:17-20 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 13:9-11">Maꞌ 13:9-11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 12:11-12">Ʉruꞌ 12:11-12</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 21:12-15">21:12-15</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 10:20" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 10:21" />“Eriꞌnɨtoꞌ yaꞌ tʉrui eparankatoꞌ oton iyakon uya, ikʉipʉnʉ uya nɨrɨ tʉmʉre; mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, mʉre amʉꞌ enatoꞌ oton tʉsan kon amʉꞌ ewaꞌnoma pɨꞌ toꞌ eriꞌtoꞌ yaꞌ toꞌ tʉrʉ pɨꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:21 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 13:12">Maꞌ 13:12</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 21:16">Ʉruꞌ 21:16</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 10:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 10:22" />Urɨ wenai tuꞌkan kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya ɨyewarumaꞌtɨtoꞌ oton kon, eꞌtane kʉrɨ rɨ panaꞌ pe neꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkayaiꞌneꞌ iuꞌmatʉ pona rɨ epikaꞌtɨtoꞌ oton mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:22 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 24:9">Maꞌsiu 24:9</ref>, <ref loc="MAT 24:13">13</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 13:13">Maꞌ 13:13</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 21:17">Ʉruꞌ 21:17</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 10:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 10:23" />Toꞌ uya pata yau ɨkotaꞌma kon aꞌtai, tʉron nɨ pata yaꞌ mapʉrʉntʉiꞌ. Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ pata ton awɨrɨ ɨutɨtoꞌ kon iꞌmaꞌkasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyeꞌtane Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyeꞌtoꞌ oton,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 10:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 10:24" />Sises uya rɨ taꞌpʉ, “Tʉusenupasen esi pʉra iyesi tʉtiꞌsaai entai, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ipoitorʉ pe teꞌsen tesaꞌ entai.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:24 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 6:40">Ʉruꞌ 6:40</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 13:16">Isaan 13:16</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 15:20">15:20</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 10:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 10:25" />Tʉusenupasen eꞌtoꞌ pe iyesi tʉtiꞌsaai kasa, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoitorʉ kanan tesaꞌ kasa rɨ. Ɨutɨ esaꞌ pe teꞌsen esakʉ pe iyesi yau Pirɨsipupʉ<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">10:25 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Pirɨsipupʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">- </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Ɨutɨ epuru </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe, Makoi eseꞌ isakon.</char></note> tukaiꞌ, mɨrɨ entai kuru rɨ si toꞌ uya itiwʉꞌ tawon kon esakʉ!<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:25 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 9:34">Maꞌsiu 9:34</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 12:24">12:24</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 3:22">Maꞌ 3:22</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 11:15">Ʉruꞌ 11:15</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 10:25" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Enariꞌnʉn Nɨtoꞌ Ipɨꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 10:26" />“Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ, toꞌ pɨꞌ kenariꞌnʉntʉu. Ɨꞌrɨ pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ iwapuꞌtɨsaꞌ teꞌnɨponkasen pen, mɨrɨ pe pʉra onansaꞌ iꞌtu pʉra teꞌsen.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:26 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 4:22">Maꞌ 4:22</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 8:17">Ʉruꞌ 8:17</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 10:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 10:27" />Ewarupɨ yau kanpanaꞌtɨyatʉiꞌneꞌ ekamatɨꞌ wʉi nai; apana kon yaꞌ ɨyetarerumʉꞌpʉ kon ekamatɨꞌ ɨutɨ nakapu ponsiꞌkɨ. <verse eid="MAT 10:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 10:28" />Ɨpun kon wɨnin nan pɨꞌ kenariꞌnʉntʉu, ayaꞌkwarʉ kon wɨnin nan pen nɨ pɨꞌ. Eꞌtane ruꞌku, kʉrɨ pɨꞌ enariꞌnʉntɨꞌ, asaꞌrɨ rɨ marɨ ɨpun mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ayaꞌkwarʉ wɨnin pɨꞌ ekotaꞌman nɨtoꞌ yau. <verse eid="MAT 10:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 10:29" />Asaꞌron kon peꞌ toron amʉꞌ tekʉrʉpoꞌpomasan pen tikin nan pʉrata punuꞌpɨ kaisa rɨ? Eꞌtane tikin nan nɨ toꞌ tonpa utaꞌmoꞌka pen mɨrɨ non pona ɨkʉipʉnʉ wanmʉra. <verse eid="MAT 10:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 10:30" />Aꞌpai iꞌpoꞌ tuꞌkanoro esi tanporo iꞌtusaꞌ pe. <verse eid="MAT 10:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 10:31" />Mɨrɨ wenai, kenariꞌnʉntʉu, iꞌnʉnkenaꞌ ton ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon, tuꞌkan kon toron amʉꞌ entaino kon.<verse eid="MAT 10:31" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 10:32" />“Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ uyekamayaiꞌneꞌ, ‘Iꞌnai rɨ iyesi tukaiꞌ,’ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ rau, urɨ uya rɨ nɨrɨ ekama, ‘Iꞌnai rɨ iyesi tukaiꞌ,’ ukʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon rau. <verse eid="MAT 10:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 10:33" />Eꞌtane ɨnʉꞌ rɨ, unonkayaiꞌneꞌ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ rau, urɨ uya rɨ nɨrɨ inonka mɨrɨ ukʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon rau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:33 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2TI 2:12">2 Temuꞌti 2:12</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 10:33" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Iꞌnʉnkaꞌ Ɨtonpa Ton Iꞌnʉnka Auya Entai</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 10:34" />“Serɨ non pona tʉusewankamaiꞌ pʉra eꞌnɨtoꞌ neꞌsaꞌ uya tukaiꞌ keꞌtʉu,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya. “Tʉusewankamaiꞌ pʉra eꞌnɨtoꞌ neꞌseꞌna uyeꞌsaꞌ pen, eꞌtane supara neꞌsaꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 10:34" /><verse number="35-36" style="v" sid="MAT 10:35-36" />Apʉne pʉra uyeꞌsaꞌ rɨ tasaꞌ:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 10:35-36">“‘warawoꞌ eraꞌtɨtoꞌ pe tʉkʉipʉnʉ ewaꞌnoma pɨꞌ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 10:35-36">uriꞌsan tʉsan ewaꞌnoma pɨꞌ,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 10:35-36">ipaꞌse tewoꞌpʉ ewaꞌnoma pɨꞌ—</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 10:35-36">kaꞌpon eyaton pe itiwʉꞌ tawon kon nɨ enatoꞌ oton,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">10:35-36 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Maiꞌka 7:6</char></note>”</para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 10:35-36">tawon.<verse eid="MAT 10:35-36" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 10:37" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ, “Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ tʉkʉipʉnʉ, tʉsan iꞌnʉnkanin urɨ iꞌnʉnka tʉuya entai esi mɨrɨ upoitorʉ yeꞌ pe pʉra rɨ. Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ kʉrɨ tʉmu, mɨrɨ pe pʉra tensi iꞌnʉnkanin urɨ iꞌnʉnka tʉuya entai esi mɨrɨ upoitorʉ yeꞌ pe pʉra rɨ, <verse eid="MAT 10:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 10:38" />mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨnʉꞌ rɨ tʉkurusukuui tanʉnse upɨkɨrɨ ɨtɨpai pʉra naꞌneꞌ esi uiwanoꞌ pe pʉra.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:38 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 16:24">Maꞌsiu 16:24</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 8:34">Maꞌ 8:34</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:23">Ʉruꞌ 9:23</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 10:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 10:39" />Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ kʉrɨ tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ eporo pɨꞌ naꞌneꞌ uya tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ nonka rɨ mɨrɨ. Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ kʉrɨ tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ nonkanin nʉꞌpʉ uwenai uya tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ epotoꞌ oton mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:39 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 16:25">Maꞌsiu 16:25</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 8:35">Maꞌ 8:35</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:24">Ʉruꞌ 9:24</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 17:33">17:33</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 12:25">Isaan 12:25</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 10:39" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tepeꞌpʉ Kon Eponin Nan</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 10:40" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ miyarɨ rɨ, “Kʉrɨ ayanʉnyaiꞌneꞌ uya uyanʉmʉ rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kʉrɨ uyanʉnyaiꞌneꞌ uya kʉrɨ uyennoꞌnin nʉꞌpʉ anʉmʉ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10:40 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 9:37">Maꞌ 9:37</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:48">Ʉruꞌ 9:48</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 10:16">10:16</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 13:20">Isaan 13:20</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 10:40" /><verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 10:41" />Ɨnʉꞌ uya Papa Maimu anin ereutanʉꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, Papa Maimu anin pe iyesi pɨꞌ uya itepeꞌpʉ tonpa eporo mɨrɨ tepeꞌpʉ eporo iya aꞌtai. Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ ipokenaꞌ kaꞌpon ereutanʉꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, ipokenaꞌ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, kʉrɨ rɨ uya rɨ ipokenaꞌ kaꞌpon epeꞌpʉ tonpa eporo mɨrɨ tepeꞌpʉ eporo iya aꞌtai. <verse eid="MAT 10:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 10:42" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨnʉꞌ uya pʉsamoro sepaꞌ nan nʉꞌkwɨ rɨ oꞌpa yau komiꞌ tuna ke rʉꞌkwɨ rɨ, apʉne pʉra upoitorʉ pe toꞌ esi pɨꞌ, iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, tepeꞌpʉ nonka iya pen kuru rɨ mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 10:42" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 10" />
  <chapter number="11" style="c" sid="MAT 11" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 11:1" />12 kaisaron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton auroꞌka tʉpo, Sises utɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ pata apai itekare ekamaiꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enupaiꞌ Kiyarari poꞌnan pata ton yau.<verse eid="MAT 11:1" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Uya Isaan Paꞌtes Ekamaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 11:2" />Isaan Paꞌtes uya etasaꞌ aꞌtai parikiꞌsi tawonsiꞌkɨ Kʉrai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11:2 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya; Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe.</char></note> nʉkupʉnʉ, tʉpoitorʉ ton ennokoꞌpʉ iya <verse eid="MAT 11:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 11:3" />ekamaꞌpopɨꞌseꞌna, “Ɨmɨrɨ peꞌ kʉrɨ rɨ tʉuyeꞌton taꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, tʉron nɨ rɨ katɨ uyepʉ enupɨkɨrɨ ina eꞌtoꞌ nai?” tukaiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 11:3" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 11:4" />Sises uya toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ennaꞌpotɨꞌ, ɨnetaꞌpʉ kon mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨneneꞌpʉ kon ekamatantɨꞌ Isaan pɨꞌ; <verse eid="MAT 11:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 11:5" />tenkuꞌnaꞌ nan enasaꞌ man ennin nan pe; iseꞌmesaꞌ kon enasaꞌ man tʉusasan pe; erekʉꞌpaꞌ nan usepiꞌtɨsaꞌ man; etanin nan pen enasaꞌ man etanin pe; ekeꞌ amʉꞌ eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkasaꞌ man, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ wakʉ itekare usekamasaꞌ man entuꞌmanin nan pana yaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11:5 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 35:5-6">Aisaya 35:5-6</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 61:1">61:1</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 11:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 11:6" />Poriꞌ pe kaꞌpon esi mɨrɨ tʉutaꞌmoꞌkasen pen unkupʉnʉ uriyaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 11:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 11:7" />Isaan poitorʉ ton ennaꞌpo koroꞌtau, Sises epiyaꞌtɨꞌpʉ anpisin auroꞌka pɨꞌ Isaan pɨꞌ, “Ɨꞌrɨ enseꞌna ɨutɨꞌpʉ kon rɨmonoꞌ taꞌ? Wanaꞌ rɨ ariꞌma aꞌsetun uya enseꞌna? <verse eid="MAT 11:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 11:8" />Mɨrɨ pe pʉra iyesi yau, ɨꞌrɨ ken enseꞌna ɨutɨꞌpʉ kon? Wakʉ pe katɨ kaꞌpon epontɨpɨꞌsaꞌ enseꞌna? Kane. Kamoro rupɨ ton nin esi mɨrɨ epeꞌkenaꞌ ton ipon ton esi kin iwʉꞌ tawon kon. <verse eid="MAT 11:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 11:9" />Ɨꞌrɨ kuru ken enseꞌna ɨutɨꞌpʉ kon? Puꞌkenaꞌ katɨ? Ewaiꞌ apanaꞌtɨ uya ꞌnokon, puꞌkenaꞌ entaino rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 11:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 11:10" />Pʉse rɨ saꞌne si kʉrɨ rɨ ko iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ itekare usauroꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 11:10">“‘Umaimu ekamanin ennoko uya mɨrɨ arawɨrɨ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 11:10">ɨyeꞌma konekanin pe awapiya,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11:10 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Maraꞌkai 3:1</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 11:10">taꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 11:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 11:11" />“Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, kamo uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ nentunʉkʉꞌsan koroꞌtau pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ eke Isaan Paꞌtes entaino; mɨrɨ eꞌtane, kʉrɨ aiko pe teꞌsen Epʉn po esaꞌ wannɨ pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ yawon esi eke pe Isaan entai. <verse eid="MAT 11:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 11:12" />Isaan Paꞌtes weyu rʉꞌpʉ siꞌkɨrɨ serɨ pʉꞌkʉ pona, Epʉn po esaꞌ wannɨ pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ utaꞌtuꞌman pɨꞌ man meruntɨ pe, mɨrɨpan aꞌsi pɨꞌ meruntɨ ton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ man.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11:12 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Epʉn po esaꞌ wannɨ pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ utaꞌtuꞌman pɨꞌ man meruntɨ pe, mɨrɨpan aꞌsi pɨꞌ meruntɨ ton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ man; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Epʉn po esaꞌ wannɨ pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ uya ɨsɨ ton nɨ moronka, mɨrɨpan kon uya rɨ nin si imoꞌkasaꞌ tʉutaꞌkwarʉkaiꞌ.</char></note> <verse eid="MAT 11:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 11:13" />Tanporon kon nɨ puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Main usenupan nɨtoꞌ ipɨꞌ uya Papa Maimu ekamaꞌpʉ, Isaan Paꞌtes uyepʉ pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11:13 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 16:16">Ʉruꞌ 16:16</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 11:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 11:14" />Serɨ si toꞌ maimu anapurɨpai ɨwesi kon yau, Isaan nɨ si kʉrɨ rɨ Iraisa uyepʉ tasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11:14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAL 4:5">Maraꞌkai 4:5</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 17:10-13">Maꞌsiu 17:10-13</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 9:11-13">Maꞌ 9:11-13</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 11:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 11:15" />Kʉrɨ rɨ tʉpana ke naꞌneꞌ tɨwɨ netai,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 11:15" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 11:16" />Sises uya kanan takaaꞌpʉ, “Ɨnʉꞌ yan kasa toꞌ esi tukaiꞌ serɨ aꞌtaino kon ekama uya? Mʉre amʉꞌ ereutapɨꞌsaꞌ kʉrʉpoꞌpo pataꞌseꞌ yau naꞌneꞌ tʉukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨꞌsan tʉron kon pɨꞌ kasa toꞌ esi:<verse eid="MAT 11:16" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 11:17" />“‘Sarakuwa turunpaꞌpʉ ina uya,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 11:17">eꞌtane aumanʉnsaꞌ kon pʉra iyesi.</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 11:17">Ekeꞌ eremu pɨꞌ ina userenkaꞌpʉ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 11:17">eꞌtane tʉutaꞌkwarʉkaiꞌ aukaransaꞌ kon pʉra iyesi,’</para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 11:17">tawon nan kasa. <verse eid="MAT 11:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 11:18" />Apʉne pʉra Isaan uyeeꞌpʉ iyentaꞌna mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨꞌrɨ ensi iya pʉra, mɨrɨpan pɨꞌ, ‘Makoi esi iyau,’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 11:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 11:19" />Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyeeꞌpʉ tentaꞌnasen nɨ waain ensinin nɨ, mɨrɨpan pɨꞌ, ‘Eke pe tentaꞌnasen, teꞌtaripasen,’ taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ. ‘Pʉrata amʉranʉꞌnin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉmakooikenaꞌ nan nɨ tonpa pe iyesi,’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya. Eꞌtane Papa puꞌketʉ usiꞌtu mɨrɨ iꞌnapai rɨ inkupʉnʉ pɨkɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 11:19" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Ɨsɨ Papa Sakorooi Yawon Kon</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 11:20" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises usaurokʉꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pata yau toꞌ enoꞌma pe, eke Papa tʉrawasooi kupʉꞌpʉ tʉuya yauꞌne, apʉne pʉra tʉmakooi kon apai toꞌ eraꞌtɨ kasa pʉra. <verse eid="MAT 11:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 11:21" />“Ɨsɨ sɨ, Korasin pon kon! Ɨsɨ sɨ, Peꞌsaita pon kon! Ɨꞌkoroꞌtauꞌnokon neꞌkuꞌaiꞌneꞌ eke Papa tʉrawasooi eꞌkuꞌsaꞌ pe iyesi yau Taya mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Saitan pon kon koroꞌtau, pena rɨ toꞌ eraꞌtɨꞌpʉ nesiiꞌno tʉmakooi kon apai. Toꞌ epontɨpɨꞌsaꞌ esiꞌpʉ nesiiꞌno isaꞌkaꞌsi yaꞌ, urumɨrʉꞌpʉ yau toꞌ nesiiꞌno.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11:21 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 23:1-18">Aisaya 23:1-18</ref>; <ref loc="EZK 26:1-28:26">Isiꞌkiyerʉ 26:1–28:26</ref>; <ref loc="JOL 3:4-8">Isowerʉ 3:4-8</ref>; <ref loc="AMO 1:9-10">Emas 1:9-10</ref>; <ref loc="ZEC 9:2-4">Sakaraya 9:2-4</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 11:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 11:22" />Eꞌtane apanaꞌtɨ uya ꞌnokon Taya mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Saitan pon kon uya parɨ imoronkatoꞌ oton eseru aimenka weyu eꞌseposaꞌ aꞌtai ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon entai. <verse eid="MAT 11:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 11:23" />Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon, Kaꞌpaneyan pon kon, autanʉntoꞌ oton kon peꞌ kaꞌtakʉiꞌ? Kane! Iꞌnaꞌ autaꞌmoꞌkatoꞌ oton kon mɨrɨ taꞌmu kenan pen nɨ yaꞌ. Ɨꞌkoroꞌtauꞌnokon neꞌkuꞌaiꞌneꞌ eke Papa tʉrawasooi eꞌkuꞌsaꞌ pe iyesi yau Satan po, moro rɨ mɨrɨ pata nesiiꞌno serɨ pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11:23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 19:24-28">Iseneses 19:24-28</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 14:13-15">Aisaya 14:13-15</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 11:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 11:24" />Eꞌtane pʉra rɨ ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, Satan pon kon uya parɨ imoronkatoꞌ oton eseru aimenka weyu eꞌseposaꞌ aꞌtai ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon entai,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11:24 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 10:15">Maꞌsiu 10:15</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 10:12">Ʉruꞌ 10:12</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 11:24" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Isetaꞌkasaꞌ Kon Umoronkaꞌtoꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 11:25" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uya taꞌpʉ, “Kanyapurɨpɨꞌaiꞌ, Papai, Epʉn mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ non Epuru, apʉne pʉra serɨ ton onansaꞌ auya pɨꞌ puꞌkenaꞌ ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ isenupasaꞌ kon piyapai, mɨrɨpan enpoikasaꞌ auya pɨꞌ aiko ton mʉre amʉꞌ enaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 11:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 11:26" />Ewaiꞌ Papai, serɨ kuꞌsaꞌ auya iꞌse ɨweꞌtoꞌ awɨrɨ poriꞌ pe ɨkuꞌnin pe iyesi pɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 11:26" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 11:27" />Tʉwɨpʉrema tʉpo, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ auroꞌka pɨꞌ iyeꞌsaraꞌtɨꞌpʉ. “Tanporon nɨ esi ukʉipʉnʉ nʉnonkaꞌpʉ pe uyenaꞌ. Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ imu iꞌtu pʉra iyesi, eꞌtane ikʉipʉnʉ uya rɨken iꞌtu. Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ ikʉipʉnʉ iꞌtu pʉra iyesi, eꞌtane imu uya rɨken iꞌtu mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kamo nɨrɨ imu naꞌneꞌ eꞌtoꞌ ɨnenpoikapai itenaꞌ ton,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11:27 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 1:18">Isaan 1:18</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 3:35">3:35</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 10:15">10:15</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 11:27" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 11:28" />“Ɨsiꞌtɨꞌ ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon isetaꞌkasaꞌ kon, eꞌtapeꞌneꞌ esaꞌ pe teꞌsan, ɨumoronkapʉ kon pa ɨkuꞌtoꞌ kon pe uya. <verse eid="MAT 11:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 11:29" />Uwariꞌsarʉ apon anʉntɨꞌ ɨponaꞌnokon, ɨusenupa kon pa upɨꞌ, ɨsɨ pen nɨ urɨ, mɨ pe teꞌkuꞌsen pen nɨ uyewan yau, ayaꞌkwarʉ kon umoronkaꞌtoꞌ eporo kon pa.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11:29 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JER 6:16">Iseremaya 6:16</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 11:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 11:30" />Wakʉ rɨ mɨrɨ uwariꞌsarʉ apon, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ uwariꞌsarʉ esi asiꞌono pe,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11:30 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 6:24-30">Sairaꞌ 6:24-30</ref>; <ref loc="SIR 24:19">24:19</ref>; <ref loc="SIR 51:23-26">51:23-26</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 11:30" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 11" />
  <chapter number="12" style="c" sid="MAT 12" />
  <para style="s1">Sises Esi Sapaꞌ Epuru Pe Rɨ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 12:1" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises utɨꞌpʉ aꞌnaiꞌ eꞌkwa nawɨrɨ Sapaꞌ aꞌtai. Ipoitorʉ ton esiꞌpʉ iwan pe, mɨrɨpan kon eꞌsaraꞌtɨꞌpʉ aꞌnaiꞌ eꞌsuruupɨꞌsaꞌ iꞌkwɨꞌpɨtʉ pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya ɨkuꞌpʉ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:1 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 23:25">Isuꞌtaronomi 23:25</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 12:2" />Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ uya serɨ eꞌkupʉ ensaꞌ aꞌtai, Sises pɨꞌ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, “Apʉne enkɨ, ɨpoitorʉ ton uya Main uya tʉkuꞌsen pen Sapaꞌ aꞌtai tasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ kupʉ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 12:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 12:3" />Sises uya toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ, “Kin Tepiꞌ nʉkupʉꞌpʉ peꞌ etasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pʉra nai, tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe iwan pe tesi kon aꞌtai? <verse eid="MAT 12:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 12:4" />Iyewomʉꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ taꞌ tʉtonpa ton pokon pe mɨrɨpan kon uya ipʉremasaꞌ pʉreti ɨkuꞌpʉ, toꞌ nʉkupʉnʉ tasaꞌ pen nɨ Main uya eꞌtane. Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan yu pe rɨken teꞌsen ɨkuꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:4 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LEV 24:9">Ripaitiꞌkas 24:9</ref>; <ref loc="1SA 21:1-6">1 Sanwerʉ 21:1-6</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 12:5" />Mɨrɨ rɨken pe pʉra, ene auyaꞌnokon pʉra peꞌ iyesi Main yau Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan uya Papa iwʉꞌ tau Sapaꞌ aꞌtai Main iꞌkwɨtʉꞌpʉ teꞌtʉrawasoma kon winɨ, eꞌtane wakʉ pe rɨ toꞌ esi?<verse eid="MAT 12:5" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 12:6" />“Ɨpɨꞌnokon ekama uya serɨ; moro rɨ iyesi serɨ yau eke pe teꞌsen Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ entaino. <verse eid="MAT 12:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 12:7" />Iꞌtusaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pe iyesi yau ɨꞌrɨ ta eꞌkwa pe serɨ main esi tukaiꞌ, ‘Ɨsentuꞌkenaꞌ pe ɨwesi kon iꞌse esi, oꞌ ke ɨuseꞌma kon iꞌse esi pen,’ tawon, wakʉ ton nɨ enoꞌmasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon nesiiꞌno pen.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:7 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="HOS 6:6">Oseya 6:6</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 9:13">Maꞌsiu 9:13</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 12:8" />Apʉne pʉra Kaꞌpon, Papa winon esi Sapaꞌ Epuru pe rɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 12:8" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 12:9" />Mɨrɨ apai tʉutɨiꞌ, itɨꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ usenupatoꞌ iwʉꞌ taꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 12:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 12:10" />Mɨrɨ yau, itemiyatʉ aipʉtasaꞌ amʉrasaꞌ kaꞌpon esiꞌpʉ. Sises eseruꞌtɨtoꞌ pe tʉuyaꞌnokon, mɨrɨ yawon kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Main awɨrɨ peꞌ eꞌnɨ pe iyesi mɨrɨ, Sapaꞌ aꞌtai kaꞌpon epiꞌtɨsaꞌ aꞌtai?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 12:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 12:11" />Taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Karimeru esaꞌ pe ɨwesi kon yau mɨrɨpan utaꞌmoꞌka yau akasaꞌ yaꞌ Sapaꞌ aꞌtai, taꞌsiiꞌ peꞌ anʉmʉ auyaꞌnokon pen?<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 14:5">Ʉruꞌ 14:5</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 12:12" />Kaꞌpon esi iꞌnʉnkenaꞌ pe karimeru entai. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, Sapaꞌ aꞌtai kaꞌpon pikaꞌtɨsaꞌ esi Main awɨrɨ eꞌnɨ pe rɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 12:12" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 12:13" />Mɨrɨpan aꞌtai, “Ɨyemiyatʉ ɨnkaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya kaꞌpon pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya temiyatʉ ɨnkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan ennaꞌpoꞌpʉ tesiꞌpʉ yaꞌ, itemiyatʉ ratoi kasa rɨ marɨ. <verse eid="MAT 12:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 12:14" />Eꞌtane si Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ epaꞌkasaꞌ utɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon ekonekaꞌpʉ iwɨtoꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 12:14" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ Ipoitorʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 12:15" />Sises uya Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ ekonekasaꞌ iꞌtusaꞌ aꞌtai, itɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ pata apai. Tuꞌkan kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ utɨꞌpʉ ipɨkɨrɨ, mɨrɨ yau toꞌ koroꞌtau takuruꞌkenaꞌ nan esiꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon epiꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 12:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 12:16" />Toꞌ panamaꞌpʉ iya tʉron kon pɨꞌ kʉrɨ rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ ta toꞌ uya namaiꞌ tʉpɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 12:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 12:17" />Serɨ kupʉꞌpʉ iya puꞌkenaꞌ Aisaya yai Papa usaurokʉꞌpʉ utaꞌkuꞌtɨtoꞌ pe:<verse eid="MAT 12:17" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 12:18" />“Upoitorʉ pe, unanʉmʉꞌpʉ pʉse rɨ.</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 12:18">Ipan pe uniꞌnʉnkanʉ, mɨrɨpan pɨꞌ eporiꞌma.</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 12:18">Uyaꞌkwarʉ ennoko uya mɨrɨ ipona,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 12:18">mɨrɨpan uya wakʉ pe eꞌnɨ eseru ekamatoꞌ oton tanporon kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 12:18" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 12:19" />Mɨrɨpan usauroꞌtoꞌ oton amaꞌai;</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 12:19">eke pe asanta tau isauroꞌtoꞌ oton pen.<verse eid="MAT 12:19" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 12:20" />Iyeꞌsekeukasaꞌ wanaꞌ iꞌkwɨtʉ iya pen,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 12:20">mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ usenkʉꞌnɨ poken teꞌsen apoꞌ enkʉꞌnʉkʉ iya pen,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 12:20">wakʉ ena itentai pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 12:20" /></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 12:21" />Iteseꞌ yau tanporon kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya teꞌkuꞌtoꞌ kon tʉtoꞌ oton,”<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12:21 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Aisaya 42:1-4</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 12:21">tawon.<verse eid="MAT 12:21" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Ɨri Pe Kaꞌpon Amʉꞌ Usauroꞌtoꞌ Oton Sises Pɨꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 12:22" />Mɨrɨ yau, tʉron kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya makoi yen kaꞌpon neeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ. Kʉrɨ rɨ kaꞌpon esiꞌpʉ tenkuꞌnan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉusauroꞌsen pen. Mɨrɨpan epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ Sises uya makoi aꞌkwarʉ tenpaꞌkaiꞌ, mɨrɨpan enasaꞌ esiꞌpʉ tʉusauroꞌsen pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ennin pe. <verse eid="MAT 12:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 12:23" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ usewansiukaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya, “Tepiꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ pe peꞌ iyesi serɨ, itenupɨkɨrɨ eꞌnɨtoꞌ Meꞌsaya<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12:23 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya, </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai; Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe.</char></note>?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 12:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 12:24" />Eꞌtane Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ uya serɨ etasaꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, “Pirɨsipupʉ,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12:24 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Pirɨsipupʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">- Makoi eseꞌ isakon; v. 27 yau nɨrɨ.</char></note> makoi amʉꞌ epuru uya tʉpikaꞌtɨiꞌ makoi amʉꞌ enpaꞌkapɨtʉ pʉse rɨ uya mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:24 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 9:34">Maꞌsiu 9:34</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 10:25">10:25</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 12:24" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 12:25" />Sises uya toꞌ usenuminkatoꞌ iꞌtusaꞌ esiꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Tanporo esaꞌ wannɨ pe teꞌsan epantakapɨꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai ɨsewaꞌnomaiꞌ tiwanoꞌ kon pe rɨ, toꞌ umaꞌta mɨrɨ; pata mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨsiwʉꞌ tawon kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ epantakapɨꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai ɨsewaꞌnomaiꞌ tiwanoꞌ kon pe rɨ ukoꞌmamʉ pen nɨ mɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 12:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 12:26" />Mɨrɨ kasa si iyesi Seꞌtan<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12:26 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Seꞌtan</char><char style="ft" closed="false">–Makoi eseꞌ isakon, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Papa eseru ewarumaꞌtɨnin </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe.</char></note> uya Seꞌtan nɨrɨ enpaꞌkasaꞌ aꞌtai, tiwanoꞌ pe rɨ iyepantakasaꞌ pe iyesi ɨsewaꞌnomaiꞌ; mɨrɨ kasa iyesi aꞌtai, nai kasa ken Seꞌtan eꞌtoꞌ itesaꞌ pe ukoꞌmamʉ? <verse eid="MAT 12:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 12:27" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ makoi amʉꞌ enpaꞌka uya pe iyesi yau Pirɨsipupʉ ke, ɨnʉꞌ ke ken ɨpoitorʉ kon toꞌ enpaꞌkanin nan? Toꞌ nin si esi mɨrɨ ɨyeseru kon aimenkanin nan pe. <verse eid="MAT 12:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 12:28" />Eꞌtane makoi amʉꞌ enpaꞌka uya pe iyesi yau Papa Aꞌkwarʉ ke, Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe nin si uyeꞌsaꞌ mɨrɨ ɨponaꞌnokon.<verse eid="MAT 12:28" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 12:29" />“Mɨrɨ pe pʉra kanan, nai kasa ɨnʉꞌ rɨ ewomʉ panaꞌpan iwʉꞌ taꞌ itapuruui ton aseꞌna? Wapiya auronpɨꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai rɨ nin iyeꞌkupʉ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai nin itimamin arɨ iya itiwʉꞌ tapai.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:29 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="TOB 8:3">Topayas 8:3</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 12:29" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 12:30" />“Kʉrɨ rɨ kaꞌpon utonpa pe pʉra naꞌneꞌ esi mɨrɨ uyeyaton pe; kʉrɨ rɨ amʉranʉkʉ iya pʉra naꞌneꞌ uyaꞌkɨrɨ uya, itaꞌnʉkʉ mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:30 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 9:40">Maꞌ 9:40</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 12:31" />Ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, tanporon nɨ makoi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Papa sapema pe isauroꞌsaꞌ kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ rɨ usentuꞌman, eꞌtane Iyaꞌkwarʉ sapema pe isauroꞌsaꞌ kon pɨꞌ usentuꞌman pen nɨ. <verse eid="MAT 12:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 12:32" />Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ Kaꞌpon, Papa winon pɨꞌ ewaꞌnoma pe isauroꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ pɨꞌ usentuꞌman, eꞌtane ewaꞌnoma pe Wakʉ Aꞌkwarʉ pɨꞌ isauroꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ pɨꞌ usentuꞌman pen nɨ, serɨ aꞌtaiꞌne mɨrɨ pe pʉra serɨ entawon aꞌtaiꞌne rɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:32 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 12:10">Ʉruꞌ 12:10</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 12:32" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 12:33" />“Wakʉ pe yʉi ikuꞌkɨ; mɨrɨ aꞌtai, wakʉ pe iteperu esi mɨrɨ. Mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ɨri pe yʉi ikuꞌkɨ; mɨrɨ aꞌtai, ɨri pe rɨ iteperu esi mɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra yʉi usiꞌtu mɨrɨ iteperu winɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:33 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 27:6">Sairaꞌ 27:6</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 7:20">Maꞌsiu 7:20</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 6:44">Ʉruꞌ 6:44</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 12:34" />Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon ɨkʉi munkɨ ton! Nai kasa ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon ɨri pe teꞌsan usaurokʉ wakʉ pe? Apʉne pʉra ɨyewan kon epeꞌtɨsaꞌ apaino kuru enpaꞌka auyaꞌnokon mɨrɨ anta kon yai.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:34 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 3:7">Maꞌsiu 3:7</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 15:18">15:18</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 23:33">23:33</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:7">Ʉruꞌ 3:7</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 6:45">6:45</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 12:35" />Wakʉ kaꞌpon uya wakʉ ton enpaꞌka mɨrɨ wakʉ usentɨsaꞌ tʉyau, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨri kaꞌpon uya ɨri enpaꞌka mɨrɨ ɨri usentɨsaꞌ tʉyau. <verse eid="MAT 12:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 12:36" />Serɨ ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, Papa uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ aimenkatoꞌ oton tanporon nɨ tʉusenuminkaiꞌ pʉra rɨ toꞌ usauroꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 12:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 12:37" />Wakʉ amaimu kon winɨ ayanʉntoꞌ oton kon, ɨri amaimu kon winɨ ɨyenoꞌmatoꞌ oton kon,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 12:37" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Isona Pɨꞌ Iꞌtutoꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 12:38" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan uya taꞌpʉ Sises pɨꞌ, “Tiꞌsa, eke Papa tʉrawasooi ɨiꞌtutoꞌ ipɨkɨrɨ kupʉ auya ɨnenpai ina man,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:38 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 16:1">Maꞌsiu 16:1</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 8:11">Maꞌ 8:11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 11:16">Ʉruꞌ 11:16</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 12:38" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 12:39" />Toꞌ maimu eikʉꞌpʉ iya, “Ɨri ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyemariꞌmasaꞌ ekumankanin nan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya eke Papa tʉrawasooi iꞌtutoꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon ipɨkɨrɨ ekamaꞌpo. Ikupʉ uya pen eꞌtane Isona, puꞌkenaꞌ pɨꞌ iꞌtutoꞌ ipɨꞌ rʉꞌpʉ rɨken kupʉ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:39 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 16:4">Maꞌsiu 16:4</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 8:12">Maꞌ 8:12</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 12:40" />Apʉne pʉra Isona esiꞌpʉ osorʉwau wʉi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ osorʉwau ewarupɨ nɨrɨ eke moroꞌ ewan yau. Mɨrɨ naꞌneꞌ kasa, Kaꞌpon, Papa winon ukoꞌmantoꞌ oton osorʉwau wʉi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ osorʉwau ewarupɨ non ewan yau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:40 </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Isona 1:17</char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:40" /><verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 12:41" />Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ Ninipa pon kon eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkatoꞌ oton eseru aimenka weyu aꞌtai serɨ aꞌtaino kon pokon pe toꞌ enoꞌma pe; apʉne pʉra toꞌ eraꞌtɨꞌpʉ tʉmakooi kon apai Isona uya itekare ekama pɨꞌ. Serɨ pe eke Isona entaino man serɨ yau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:41 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JON 3:5">Isona 3:5</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 12:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 12:42" />Kwin, wʉi enu uyeꞌtoꞌ kamisi winon eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkatoꞌ oton eseru aimenka weyu aꞌtai serɨ aꞌtaino kon pokon pe toꞌ enoꞌma pe; apʉne pʉra iyeꞌsaꞌ wenai non uꞌmatʉ apai Saraman puꞌketʉ etaseꞌna. Serɨ pe eke Saraman entaino man serɨ yau,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12:42 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1KI 10:1-10">1 Kin Amʉꞌ 10:1-10</ref>; <ref loc="2CH 9:1-12">2 Kʉronoꞌkʉrʉs 9:1-12</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 12:42" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="43" style="v" sid="MAT 12:43" />“Makoi<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12:43 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">makoi, </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra </char><char style="fq" closed="false">ɨri, </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Kiriꞌ maimu yau. </char></note> aꞌkwarʉ epaꞌkasaꞌ aꞌtai kaꞌpon apai, itɨ mɨrɨ tʉꞌkenan pata yaꞌ. Tereutatoꞌ yau warinpa pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan eporo iya pʉra iyesi. <verse eid="MAT 12:43" /><verse number="44" style="v" sid="MAT 12:44" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, ‘Ennaꞌpo serɨ ɨutɨ unnɨmɨꞌpʉ taꞌ,’ ta iya. Iyeꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, eporo iya itawon pʉra, wakʉ pe akorokasaꞌ pe mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ikonekasaꞌ pe. <verse eid="MAT 12:44" /><verse number="45" style="v" sid="MAT 12:45" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, itɨ 7 kaisaron kon aꞌkwarʉ ton ɨri ton kuru tentaino kon nepʉ iya taꞌkɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan kon ewomʉ, toꞌ ukoꞌmamʉ mɨrɨ yau. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, pʉse rɨ kaꞌpon esi mɨrɨ ɨri pe kuru wapiya tesiꞌpʉ entai. Mɨrɨ naꞌneꞌ kasa, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon ɨri pe nʉkoꞌmanyaiꞌneꞌ nan serɨ aꞌtaino kon eꞌtoꞌ oton,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 12:45" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises San Mɨrɨ Awonsiꞌkɨ Iyakon Non</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="46" style="v" sid="MAT 12:46" />Anpisin auroꞌka pɨꞌ Sises esi koroꞌtau rɨ marɨ, isan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyakon non eꞌsotoꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ esiꞌpʉ pʉroroi po. Iyaꞌkɨrɨ asauroꞌpai toꞌ esiꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 12:46" /><verse number="47" style="v" sid="MAT 12:47" />Kaꞌpon uya ipanaꞌtɨꞌpʉ, “Asan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ayakon non eꞌsotoꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ man pʉroroi po. Ayauroꞌkapai toꞌ esi,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12:47 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tʉron nɨ imenukasaꞌ ton yau v. 47 pʉra iyesi.</char></note><verse eid="MAT 12:47" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="48" style="v" sid="MAT 12:48" />Eikʉꞌpʉ iya, “Ɨnʉꞌ si usan? Ɨnʉꞌ yan si uyakon non?” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 12:48" /><verse number="49" style="v" sid="MAT 12:49" />Tʉpoitorʉ ton enusimaiꞌma taꞌpʉ iya, “Pʉsamo nin usanon mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ uyakon non. <verse eid="MAT 12:49" /><verse number="50" style="v" sid="MAT 12:50" />Apʉne pʉra ɨnʉꞌ rɨ ukʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon eꞌtoꞌ iꞌse kuꞌnin esi mɨrɨ, uyakon pe, uparusi pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ usan pe,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 12:50" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 12" />
  <chapter number="13" style="c" sid="MAT 13" />
  <para style="s1">Kaꞌpon Tʉpaꞌkarakaiꞌ Teꞌpɨnsen Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 13:1" />Mɨrɨ wʉi aꞌtai si, Sises epaꞌkaꞌpʉ ɨutɨ tapai, mɨrɨpan utɨsaꞌ ereutaꞌpʉ parau kuꞌpɨri eꞌpi po. <verse eid="MAT 13:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 13:2" />Tuꞌke kuru rɨ anpisin pe kaꞌpon amʉꞌ esi pɨꞌ tʉwoi, kanau yaꞌ tekanwaꞌtɨiꞌ iyereutaꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ eꞌtane aꞌmun po.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13:2 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 5:1-3">Ʉruꞌ 5:1-3</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 13:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 13:3" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, tuꞌkan pɨꞌ rɨ toꞌ auroꞌkaꞌpʉ iya panton yai. “Umɨ pɨꞌ teꞌsen utɨꞌpʉ kiyari yeꞌ pɨnseꞌna tʉpaꞌkarakaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 13:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 13:4" />Ipaꞌkaraka iya koroꞌtau, tʉron nɨ ton utaꞌpokʉꞌpʉ asanta taꞌ. Toron amʉꞌ uyeeꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya ɨkuꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 13:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 13:5" />Tʉron nɨ utaꞌpokʉꞌpʉ tɨꞌ pe teꞌsen yaꞌ eke pe pʉra teꞌsen non yaꞌ. Iyaꞌtaꞌpʉ inke pʉra, apʉne pʉra iꞌnau pʉra non esi ke. <verse eid="MAT 13:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 13:6" />Eꞌtane wʉi enu enuꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, aꞌneꞌ pe ipuruꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan aipʉtaꞌpʉ apʉne pʉra imiꞌ utɨpɨꞌsaꞌ pʉra iyesi wenai. <verse eid="MAT 13:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 13:7" />Tʉron nɨ ton utaꞌpokʉꞌpʉ tikʉkenan nʉꞌtaꞌ, mɨrɨpan ɨmɨꞌnɨꞌta aꞌta uya ɨwɨtanʉkʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 13:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 13:8" />Mɨrɨ eꞌtane rɨ, tʉron nɨ ton utaꞌpokʉꞌpʉ wakʉ non yaꞌ, mɨrɨpan epetaꞌpʉ 100 kaisarɨ rɨ, 60 mɨrɨ pe pʉra 30 kaisarɨ rɨ iteꞌkwa ipɨmɨꞌpʉ entai rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 13:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 13:9" />Kʉrɨ rɨ tʉpana ke naꞌneꞌ tɨwɨ netai,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 13:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 13:10" />Ipoitorʉ ton uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ ekamaꞌposeꞌna, “Ɨꞌrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ auroꞌka auya panton yai?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 13:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 13:11" />Toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ iya, “Ɨnʉꞌ niꞌtunʉ pen nɨ amaꞌaino Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe iꞌtu kon pa ɨyenaꞌnokon itʉsaꞌ, eꞌtane toꞌ enaꞌ itʉsaꞌ pʉra iyesi. <verse eid="MAT 13:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 13:12" />Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ itesaꞌ pe teꞌsen repa mɨrɨ miyarɨ rɨ, mɨrɨpan eꞌtoꞌ pe eke pe itesaꞌ pe. Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ ɨꞌrɨ esaꞌ pen nɨ enapai imoꞌka mɨrɨ itenawon nʉꞌkwɨ rɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13:12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 25:29">Maꞌsiu 25:29</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 4:25">Maꞌ 4:25</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 8:18">Ʉruꞌ 8:18</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 19:26">19:26</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 13:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 13:13" />Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ toꞌ auroꞌka uya mɨrɨ panton yai:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 13:13">“Ennin pe rɨ toꞌ eꞌtane, toꞌ uya ene pʉra iyesi pɨꞌ;</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 13:13">etanin pe rɨ toꞌ eꞌtane, toꞌ uya eta mɨrɨ pe pʉra itoꞌkaꞌnʉkʉ pʉra iyesi pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 13:13" /></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 13:14" />Puꞌkenaꞌ Aisaya nekamaꞌpʉ utaꞌkuꞌtɨsaꞌ toꞌ pɨꞌ:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 13:14">“‘Eta pɨꞌ rɨ ɨweꞌtoꞌ oton eꞌtane, itoꞌkaꞌnʉkʉ auya pʉra iyeꞌtoꞌ oton;</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 13:14">ene pɨꞌ rɨ miyarɨ rɨ ɨweꞌtoꞌ oton eꞌtane, entoꞌ auya oton pen.<verse eid="MAT 13:14" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 13:15" />Pʉsamoro kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ewan enasaꞌ saꞌman pe;</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 13:15">toꞌ uya eta pʉra rɨ iyesi tʉpana kon ke,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 13:15">tenu kon aꞌkopɨꞌsaꞌ toꞌ uya,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 13:15">tenu kon ke toꞌ uya ene nesiiꞌno,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 13:15">mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉpana kon ke toꞌ netaiꞌno,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 13:15">tewan kon ke toꞌ nʉtoꞌkaꞌnʉkʉiꞌno,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 13:15">toꞌ neraꞌtɨiꞌno, mɨrɨpan kon sepiꞌtɨiꞌno,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">13:15 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Aisaya 6:9-10</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 13:15">tawon. <verse eid="MAT 13:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 13:16" />Eꞌtane wakʉ pe ɨyenu kon esi mɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra ene iya pɨꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ apana kon eta iya pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 13:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 13:17" />Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, tuꞌkan kon nɨ puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipokenaꞌ ton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ esiꞌpʉ menyatʉiꞌneꞌ ɨnenpai eꞌtane, toꞌ uya eneꞌpʉ pen; mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ metayatʉiꞌneꞌ ɨnetapai eꞌtane, toꞌ uya etaꞌpʉ pen,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13:17 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 10:23-24">Ʉruꞌ 10:23-24</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 13:17" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tʉpaꞌkarakaiꞌ Teꞌpɨnsen Pantomʉ Enpoikasaꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 13:18" />“Etatɨꞌ ɨꞌrɨ ta eꞌkwa pe tʉpaꞌkarakaiꞌ teꞌpɨnsen pantomʉ esi tukaiꞌ: <verse eid="MAT 13:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 13:19" />Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ itekare eta aꞌtai Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe pɨꞌ, eꞌtane itoꞌkaꞌnʉkʉ iya pʉra iyesi, Makoi uyepʉ itewan yaꞌ ipaꞌkarakasaꞌ moꞌkaseꞌna. Serɨ esi iteꞌ ipaꞌkarakasaꞌ asanta taꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 13:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 13:20" />Kʉrɨ rɨ iteꞌ utaꞌpoꞌsaꞌ naꞌneꞌ tɨꞌ pona kasa esi kaꞌpon Main etanin nʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya inke pʉra anʉmʉꞌpʉ poriꞌ pe esiiꞌma. <verse eid="MAT 13:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 13:21" />Eꞌtane imiꞌ pʉra iyesi wenai, inke pʉra kuru itanoꞌma. Manenpanin mɨrɨ pe pʉra kotaꞌmanin uyeꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai Main wenai, inke pʉra kuru itaꞌmoꞌka. <verse eid="MAT 13:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 13:22" />Kʉrɨ rɨ iteꞌ itaꞌpoꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ tikʉkenan nʉꞌtaꞌ esi mɨrɨ kaꞌpon Main etanin nʉꞌpʉ, eꞌtane tʉusewankamasen wakʉ pe ɨkoꞌmanpai tesi pɨꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ imaminkeꞌ pe teꞌtoꞌ pɨꞌ tʉusenkuꞌtɨsen. Mɨrɨ uya ɨwɨtanʉkʉ, tepetasen pe pʉra ikupʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 13:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 13:23" />Eꞌtane kʉrɨ rɨ iteꞌ itaꞌpoꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ wakʉ non yaꞌ esi kaꞌpon Main etanin mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itoꞌkaꞌnʉꞌnin nɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan epeta 100 kaisa rɨꞌne rɨ, 60 kaisa rɨꞌne rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra 30 kaisa rɨꞌne rɨ iteꞌkwa ipaꞌkarakasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ entai,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 13:23" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Wanaꞌ Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 13:24" />Sises uya tʉron nɨ panton ekamaꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ, “Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi kaꞌpon tʉpaꞌkarakaiꞌ wakʉ kiyari yeꞌ pɨnnin nʉꞌpʉ tʉmainarʉ yau kasa. <verse eid="MAT 13:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 13:25" />Ewarupɨ nau, kʉrɨ rɨ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoitorʉ ton eꞌnʉnsaꞌ eꞌtane, iteyaton uyeeꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya wanaꞌ eꞌ pɨmɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ rɨ umɨ yau, mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 13:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 13:26" />Emennʉꞌpʉ rɨ, kiyari yeꞌ aꞌtaꞌpʉ epetan pɨꞌ iyeꞌsaraꞌtɨꞌpʉ eꞌtane, ipoitorʉ ton uya wanaꞌ eꞌ aꞌtasaꞌ eneꞌpʉ kiyari yeꞌ koroꞌtau. <verse eid="MAT 13:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 13:27" />Ipoitorʉ ton utɨꞌpʉ tepuru kon piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya, ‘Ina epuru, wakʉ saꞌne kiyari yeꞌ pɨntai ina ko, ina apiyontɨꞌpʉ auya awɨrɨ rɨ, eꞌtane nai awon wanaꞌ eꞌ aꞌtasaꞌ?’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 13:27" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 13:28" />“Toꞌ epuru uya nin si, ‘Uyeyaton uya rɨ ipɨnsaꞌ pe iyesi mɨrɨ,’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 13:28">“‘Wanaꞌ ken peꞌ naiꞌ ina utɨ iꞌse meꞌan?’ taꞌpʉ ipoitorʉ ton uya.<verse eid="MAT 13:28" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 13:29" />“Eꞌtane, ‘Kane, wanaꞌ na auyaꞌnokon koroꞌtau, iyaꞌtai pʉra kiyari yeꞌ kanan na auyaꞌnokon esi,’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ epuru uya toꞌ pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 13:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 13:30" />‘Tɨwɨ asaꞌrɨ rɨ nʉsemoꞌkai iteperu akʉꞌpʉsaꞌ anʉmʉ weyu eꞌseporo pona rɨ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, anʉnnin nan apiyontɨtoꞌ pe uya, wapiya kuru wanaꞌ natoꞌ pe toꞌ uya, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ toꞌ uya auronpɨꞌtoꞌ pe iyepoꞌtɨpɨꞌtoꞌ pe, mɨrɨ tʉpo nin si toꞌ uya aꞌnaiꞌ iꞌkwɨꞌpɨꞌtoꞌ pe, mɨrɨpan amʉranʉꞌtoꞌ pe toꞌ uya uiꞌkiyari iwʉꞌ taꞌ,’ taꞌpʉ itepuru uya tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya anpisin kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 13:30" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Mostaꞌ Iteseꞌ Kiyari Enaꞌpɨ Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 13:31" />Tʉron nɨ panton ekamaꞌpʉ Sises uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ, “Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi kiyari yeꞌ mostaꞌ iteseꞌ enaꞌpɨ, kaꞌpon nʉpɨmɨnʉ tʉmainarʉ yau kasa. <verse eid="MAT 13:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 13:32" />Mɨrɨ enaꞌpɨ esi aiko ton kuru tʉron nɨ enaꞌpɨ pokon pe iꞌtu aꞌtai, eꞌtane eke pe isemoꞌka tʉron kon umɨ yau teꞌsen kiyari yeꞌ entai, mɨrɨpan usemoꞌka eke yʉi pe, toron amʉꞌ rɨ esi ipanta poꞌne,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 13:32" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Pʉrowa Aꞌsarutanʉꞌnin Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 13:33" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉron nɨ kanan panton ekamaꞌpʉ Sises uya, “Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi pʉrowa aꞌsarutanʉꞌnin kasa, uriꞌsan nanʉmʉnʉ, mɨrɨpan uya pʉrowa pokon pe eke pe<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">13:33 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">eke pe</char><char style="ft" closed="false">–Kiriꞌ maimu yau, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">3 sata ton </char></note> ikiꞌma, tanporo ipun yau iyena pʉꞌkʉ pona,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 13:33" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 13:34" />Sises uya tanporo serɨ ton ekamaꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ anpisin ton pɨꞌ panton yai; ɨꞌrɨ ke rɨ panton yai pʉra toꞌ auroꞌka iya pʉra iyeꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 13:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 13:35" />Serɨ kupʉꞌpʉ iya, pena rɨ Papa nekamaꞌpʉ puꞌkenaꞌ yai utaꞌkuꞌtɨtoꞌ pe:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 13:35">“Panton yai kaꞌpon amʉꞌ auroꞌkatoꞌ uya oton,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 13:35">non ekoneka aꞌtai rɨ iyeꞌsoꞌnansaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ ekamatoꞌ uya oton,”<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">13:35 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Eren 78:2</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 13:35">tawon.<verse eid="MAT 13:35" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Wanaꞌ Pantomʉ Enpoikasaꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 13:36" />Mɨrɨpan uya anpisin kaꞌpon amʉꞌ nɨmɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ itau teꞌtoꞌ ɨutɨ taꞌ. Ipoitorʉ ton utɨꞌpʉ iyaꞌkɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya, “Apʉne, ɨꞌrɨ ta eꞌkwa pe wanaꞌ umɨ yawon esi tukaiꞌ ekamaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 13:36" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 13:37" />Sises uya toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ, “Kʉrɨ wakʉ itenaꞌpɨ pɨnnin nʉꞌpʉ tʉpaꞌkarakaiꞌ esi Kaꞌpon, Papa winon. <verse eid="MAT 13:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 13:38" />Umɨ esi kaꞌpon amʉꞌ serɨ non po teꞌsan, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ wakʉ kiyari yeꞌ esi esaꞌ wannɨ pe eꞌnɨ munkɨ amʉꞌ; wanaꞌ esi Makoi munkɨ amʉꞌ ekamanin pe, <verse eid="MAT 13:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 13:39" />mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ eyaton, wanaꞌ pɨnnin nʉꞌpʉ esi Makoi. Kiyari akʉꞌpʉsaꞌ anʉmʉ esi non weyu uꞌmaꞌsaꞌ aꞌtaino, kiyari anʉnnin nan esi inserʉ amʉꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 13:39" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 13:40" />“Wanaꞌ na mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoꞌtɨ kasa, mɨrɨ kasa si iyeꞌtoꞌ oton pata weyu uꞌmaꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai. <verse eid="MAT 13:40" /><verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 13:41" />Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uya tinserʉʉi ton ennoꞌtoꞌ oton serɨ non pona, mɨrɨpan kon uya ɨri kuꞌnin nʉꞌsan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉtonpa kon eꞌmakoima emapuꞌtɨnin nʉꞌsan amʉranʉꞌtoꞌ oton Papa pataꞌseꞌ yapai, <verse eid="MAT 13:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 13:42" />mɨrɨpan kon enoꞌmatoꞌ toꞌ uya oton apoꞌ yaꞌ. Mɨrɨ yau, toꞌ ukarantoꞌ oton, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉyɨ kon kɨtɨtɨiꞌmatoꞌ oton toꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 13:42" /><verse number="43" style="v" sid="MAT 13:43" />Eꞌtane ipokenaꞌ ton eꞌweiꞌtɨtoꞌ oton wʉi enu kasa tʉkʉipʉnʉ kon eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yau. Kʉrɨ rɨ tʉpana ke naꞌneꞌ tɨwɨ netai,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13:43 </char><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Estʉras 7:97</char></note><verse eid="MAT 13:43" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Iꞌnʉnkenaꞌ Mamin Pantomʉ Ekamaꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="44" style="v" sid="MAT 13:44" />Miyarɨ rɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enupaꞌpʉ Sises uya, “Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi iꞌnʉnkenaꞌ mamin umɨ yau onansaꞌ teꞌsen kasa. Mɨrɨpan eposaꞌ kaꞌpon uya aꞌtai, iuꞌnaꞌtɨkapʉ iya kanan, mɨrɨpan esi poriꞌ pe, mɨrɨpan uya tanporo timamin kʉrʉpoꞌpoma, mɨrɨpan epeꞌpʉ ke mɨrɨ non eꞌma iya.<verse eid="MAT 13:44" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="45" style="v" sid="MAT 13:45" />“Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi epeꞌkenaꞌ mokon pun tʉneꞌmanʉ ton warinpa kʉrʉpoꞌpo pokon uya naꞌneꞌ kasa. <verse eid="MAT 13:45" /><verse number="46" style="v" sid="MAT 13:46" />Mɨrɨpan eposaꞌ tʉuya aꞌtai, itɨ tanporo timamin kʉrʉpoꞌpomaiꞌ, mɨrɨpan epeꞌpʉ pʉrata ke mɨrɨ mokon pun eꞌmatoꞌ pe tʉuya.<verse eid="MAT 13:46" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Punwe Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="47" style="v" sid="MAT 13:47" />“Se kasa kanan Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi punwe esi naꞌneꞌ kasa kaꞌpon amʉꞌ nʉtʉrʉnʉ parau kuꞌpɨri kaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya ɨꞌsiꞌtau rɨ moroꞌ amʉꞌ aꞌsi. <verse eid="MAT 13:47" /><verse number="48" style="v" sid="MAT 13:48" />Punwe epeꞌtɨsaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ uya ipiꞌsikʉ makʉiꞌ. Tereutaiꞌ, tansan pe teꞌsan menkatoꞌ pe tʉuyaꞌnokon paꞌsikiꞌti yaꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tansan pen maꞌkɨrɨiꞌma. <verse eid="MAT 13:48" /><verse number="49" style="v" sid="MAT 13:49" />Serɨ kasa si iyeꞌtoꞌ oton pata weyu uꞌmaꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai. Inserʉ amʉꞌ uyeꞌtoꞌ oton, mɨrɨpan kon uya ɨri ton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ menkatoꞌ oton ipokenaꞌ ton piyapai, <verse eid="MAT 13:49" /><verse number="50" style="v" sid="MAT 13:50" />mɨrɨpan kon uya ɨri ton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enoꞌmatoꞌ oton apoꞌ yaꞌ. Toꞌ ukarantoꞌ oton, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉyɨ kon kɨtɨtɨiꞌmatoꞌ oton toꞌ uya mɨrɨ yau,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 13:50" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Uya Tʉusauroꞌtoꞌ Enukaꞌnʉkʉꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="51" style="v" sid="MAT 13:51" />“Usaurokʉineꞌ ipɨꞌ peꞌ mʉtoꞌkaꞌnʉꞌtʉu?” taꞌpʉ Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 13:51">Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ, “Ewaiꞌ, ina uya itoꞌkaꞌnʉꞌsaꞌ man,” taꞌpʉ ipoitorʉ ton uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 13:51" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="52" style="v" sid="MAT 13:52" />Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ taꞌpʉ iya, “Tanporon kon Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan usenupasaꞌ Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe pɨꞌ esi mɨrɨ, kaꞌpon tiwʉꞌ tawon emennaꞌ ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ penaroꞌ ton timamin enpaꞌkapɨꞌnin kasa,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 13:52" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Nasareꞌ Pon Kon Uya Sises Ewarumaꞌtɨꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="53" style="v" sid="MAT 13:53" />Panton amʉꞌ iꞌmaꞌkasaꞌ tʉuya aꞌtai, Sises utamaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ apai. <verse eid="MAT 13:53" /><verse number="54" style="v" sid="MAT 13:54" />Mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ tʉpataꞌseꞌ yaꞌ. Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enupa pɨꞌ iyeꞌsaraꞌtɨꞌpʉ toꞌ usenupatoꞌ iwʉꞌ tau. Mɨrɨpan kon usewansiukaꞌpʉ. “Nai yau si tʉpuꞌketʉ eporoꞌpʉ iya tʉusauroꞌtoꞌ pe mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉpanaꞌpano eke Papa tʉrawasooi kuꞌnin pe teꞌtoꞌ pe?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 13:54" /><verse number="55" style="v" sid="MAT 13:55" />“Kiyaꞌpinta mu pen peꞌ pʉse rɨ? Meri pen peꞌ isan eseꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Isens, Isoseꞌ, Saiman, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Isutas pokon peꞌ yakon non pen? <verse eid="MAT 13:55" /><verse number="56" style="v" sid="MAT 13:56" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tanporo pʉra peꞌ iparusi ton nai upiyauꞌnokon? Nai yau ken si serɨ ton epopɨtʉꞌpʉ iya?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 13:56" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="57" style="v" sid="MAT 13:57" />Mɨrɨpan kon ɨkɨnʉmʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, eꞌtane Sises uya toꞌ maimu eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ipataꞌseꞌ yau rɨken mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itonpa ton uya puꞌkenaꞌ nama pʉra iyesi,”<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13:57 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 4:44">Isaan 4:44</ref></char></note> taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 13:57" /><verse number="58" style="v" sid="MAT 13:58" />Tuꞌke eke Papa tʉrawasooi kupʉ Sises uya pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ yau, apʉne pʉra apurɨtoꞌ toꞌ uya pʉra iyesi pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 13:58" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 13" />
  <chapter number="14" style="c" sid="MAT 14" />
  <para style="s1">Serɨ Si Serɨ Isaan Paꞌtes Umaꞌtaꞌpʉ Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 14:1" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, kopʉna Eraꞌ uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ nekamanʉ etaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ kupʉ Sises uya tukaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 14:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 14:2" />Mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ tʉpiyawon kon pɨꞌ, “Isaan Paꞌtes kʉrɨ rɨ. Iyeꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkasaꞌ terikʉꞌpʉ apai; mɨrɨ wenai, eke Papa tʉrawasooi kupʉ iya mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 14:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 14:3" />Eraꞌ uya Isaan aꞌsisaꞌ mɨrɨpan auronpɨꞌsaꞌ tʉsaꞌ parikiꞌsi taꞌ esiꞌpʉ, Eratiyas, Piriꞌ takon noꞌpʉ wenai,<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">14:3 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LEV 18:16">Ripaitiꞌkas 18:16</ref>; <ref loc="LEV 20:21">20:21</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:19-20">Ʉruꞌ 3:19-20</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 14:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 14:4" />apʉne pʉra Isaan uya ta esiꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ: “Main awɨrɨ ɨwesi pe pʉra iyesi kʉrɨ rɨ anʉnsaꞌ auya naꞌneꞌ,” ta. <verse eid="MAT 14:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 14:5" />Eraꞌ esiꞌpʉ Isaan ɨnwɨpai, eꞌtane iyenariꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ, apʉne pʉra Isaan iꞌtu toꞌ uya pɨꞌ puꞌkenaꞌ pe.<verse eid="MAT 14:5" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 14:6" />Eraꞌ uya tentuꞌpʉ weyu rʉꞌpʉ kupʉ esiꞌpʉ iyentaꞌnatoꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Eratiyas mʉre umanumʉꞌpʉ toꞌ iwanoꞌ pe. Serɨ uya Eraꞌ kupʉꞌpʉ ipan pe rɨ poriꞌ pe, <verse eid="MAT 14:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 14:7" />mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ, “Ɨꞌrɨ rɨ ekamaꞌpo auya aꞌtai, ɨrepa uya kuru rɨ mɨrɨ,” tukaiꞌ isaurokʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 14:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 14:8" />Isan uya imaimuꞌtɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ ekamaꞌpokɨ tukaiꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya, “Isaan Paꞌtes iꞌpai rʉꞌpʉ ke urepakɨ serɨ yau parapi po,” taꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 14:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 14:9" />Kin upokoitaꞌpʉ tʉusaurokʉꞌpʉ pɨꞌ ipan pe, eꞌtane ikupʉ uya kuru mɨrɨ tasaꞌ tʉuya rʉꞌpʉ pɨꞌ entaꞌnaiꞌ tʉnkɨꞌmaꞌsan pana yai rɨ ikupʉ iya rɨ esiꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya tʉsoisaai amʉꞌ apiyoꞌmaꞌpʉ inesakʉꞌpʉ kuꞌtoꞌ pe toꞌ uya, <verse eid="MAT 14:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 14:10" />mɨrɨpan kon uya Isaan iꞌpairʉkaꞌpʉ parikiꞌsi tau. <verse eid="MAT 14:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 14:11" />Iꞌpai rʉꞌpʉ neeꞌpʉ toꞌ uya parapi po, mɨrɨpan kon uya itʉrʉꞌpʉ uriꞌsan enaꞌ, mɨrɨpan arɨꞌpʉ iya tʉsan enaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 14:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 14:12" />Isaan poitorʉ rʉꞌsan uyeeꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya itekepu arɨꞌpʉ iuꞌnaꞌtɨtoꞌ pe tʉuyaꞌnokon, mɨrɨpan kon utɨꞌpʉ Sises panaꞌtɨiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 14:12" /></para>
  <para style="s1">5,000 Kaisaron Kon Ewekʉꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 6:30-44">Maꞌ 6:30-44</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:10-17">Ʉruꞌ 9:10-17</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 6:1-14">Isaan 6:1-14</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 14:13" />Iyeꞌkuꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ etasaꞌ tʉuya aꞌtai, Sises ekanwaꞌtɨꞌpʉ kanau yaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon utɨꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe tʉꞌkenaꞌpɨ yaꞌ. Tuꞌkan kon nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya serɨ etaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon utɨꞌpʉ tʉꞌta kon po Sises pɨkɨrɨ pata ton apaiꞌne. <verse eid="MAT 14:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 14:14" />Sises ekanwakasaꞌ uya tuꞌke anpisin pe kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ensaꞌ aꞌtai, ipan pe rɨ toꞌ pɨꞌ isentuꞌmaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya rɨ toꞌ koroꞌtau takuruꞌkeꞌne teꞌsan epiꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 14:14" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 14:15" />Koꞌmamʉ pe rɨ iyenakaꞌtane, ipoitorʉ ton uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Ɨnnon saꞌne serɨ pata ko, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ pata kanan ukoꞌmankaꞌsaꞌ. Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ipanaꞌtɨꞌ tiwanoꞌ kon pe tiꞌkiyari kon eposeꞌna toꞌ utɨtoꞌ pe eke iwa ton pata ponaꞌne,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 14:15" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 14:16" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Toꞌ kʉsennoꞌtʉu. Toꞌ aꞌreꞌtɨtɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 14:16" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 14:17" />“Ina piyau 5 kaisaron nɨken itekiino pʉreti mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ asaꞌron kon nʉꞌkwɨ moroꞌ amʉꞌ esi,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 14:17" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 14:18" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Pʉreti mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ moroꞌ amʉꞌ ineꞌtɨꞌ uyenaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 14:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 14:19" />Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ, “Ereutapɨꞌtɨꞌ wanaꞌ ponaꞌne,” taꞌpʉ iya. Mɨrɨ tʉpo, 5 kaisaron itekiino pʉreti mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ moroꞌ amʉꞌ anʉmʉꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan uya tenu anʉmʉꞌpʉ kaꞌ winɨkʉiꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya pʉreti, moroꞌ amʉꞌ iꞌkwɨꞌpɨtʉiꞌma tenki taꞌpʉ Papa pɨꞌ. Mɨrɨ tʉpo, itʉrʉꞌpʉ iya tʉpoitorʉ ton enaꞌ, mɨrɨpan ekamʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 14:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 14:20" />Tanporon kon nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ entaꞌnaꞌpʉ taꞌwetapɨꞌse, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoitorʉ ton uya kiyari punuꞌpɨ eꞌnonkasaꞌ ke 12 kaisaron paꞌsikiꞌti arʉꞌtɨꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 14:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 14:21" />Mɨrɨ yau si 5,000 eꞌtoꞌ airɨ warawotiꞌsi amʉꞌ tuꞌkanoro esiꞌpʉ. Uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ, mʉre amʉꞌ nɨrɨ esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ yau toꞌ pokon pe pʉra toꞌ iꞌtusaꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 14:21" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Usarɨꞌpʉ Tuna Po</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 14:22" />Inke pʉra tʉpoitorʉ ton ekanwaꞌtɨtoꞌ pe kanau yaꞌ ikuuꞌpʉ Sises uya, toꞌ utɨtoꞌ pe tʉrawɨrɨ iratoi pona, anpisin ennoꞌtane tʉuya. <verse eid="MAT 14:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 14:23" />Toꞌ ennoko tʉpo, Sises utɨꞌpʉ wʉꞌ pona tikin sarɨ ɨpʉremaseꞌna Papa pɨꞌ. Pata ukoꞌmansaꞌ aꞌtai, tikin sarɨ rɨ mɨrɨ yau iyesiꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 14:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 14:24" />Eꞌtane ipoitorʉ ton eꞌtoꞌ yau kanau esiꞌpʉ ɨnnɨ rɨ iteꞌpi piyapai. Eke pe rɨ sipaꞌsipa esiꞌpʉ kanau rɨ tʉwɨpɨꞌse, apʉne pʉra aꞌsetun uyeeꞌpʉ ɨsɨ pe toꞌ winɨkʉiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 14:24" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 14:25" />Awanakʉiꞌ kuru, pata emakʉ wapiya, Sises epaꞌkaꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton piyaꞌ. Parau kuꞌpɨri po itɨꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 14:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 14:26" />Parau kuꞌpɨri po iyepʉ ene tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, ipan pe rɨ toꞌ etʉipɨtʉꞌpʉ. “Aꞌkwarʉꞌpʉ rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ!” tukaiꞌ toꞌ ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ tetʉipɨtʉ kon pe.<verse eid="MAT 14:26" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 14:27" />Sises uya inke pʉra rɨ toꞌ pɨꞌ taꞌpʉ, “Meruntɨ pe eꞌtɨꞌ! Urɨ rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ! Ketʉipɨꞌtʉu!” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 14:27" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 14:28" />Piꞌta uya taꞌpʉ, “Uyepuru, ɨmɨrɨ pe iyesi yau, ukɨꞌmakɨ ɨpiyaꞌ utɨtoꞌ pe tuna pʉroꞌpo!” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 14:28" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 14:29" />Sises uya, “Ɨsiꞌkɨ si upiyaꞌ!” taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 14:29">Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ Piꞌta ekanwakaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ tuna pʉroꞌpo Sises piyaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 14:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 14:30" />Eꞌtane mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Piꞌta uya eke rɨ sipaꞌsipa, aꞌsetun nɨrɨ eneꞌpʉ. Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ iyenariꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan eꞌsaraꞌtɨꞌpʉ eꞌsʉnkan pɨꞌ tuna kaꞌ, mɨrɨpan ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ, “Uyepuru, upikaꞌtɨꞌ!” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 14:30" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 14:31" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, inke pʉra rɨ Sises uya temiyatʉ ɨnkaꞌpʉ aꞌsiseꞌna, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ Piꞌta pɨꞌ, “Aiko pe kuru apurɨtoꞌ auya man! Ɨꞌrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ ikasimaꞌpʉ auya?” taꞌpʉ iya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 14:31" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 14:32" />Kanau yaꞌ toꞌ ekanwaꞌtɨsaꞌ aꞌtai rɨ, aꞌsetun ereutaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 14:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 14:33" />Kamoro nin si kanau yawon kon uya apurɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, “Iꞌnapairɨ rɨ Papa Mumu pe ɨwesi,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 14:33" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 14:34" />Toꞌ ɨꞌkwɨrɨꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ eꞌteꞌkaꞌpʉ Kenesareꞌ airɨ. <verse eid="MAT 14:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 14:35" />Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ mɨrɨ yau teꞌsan uya Sises toꞌkaꞌnʉꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ uya si tʉmaimu kon ennoꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ aꞌko paꞌnan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya si tanporo takuruꞌkenaꞌ nan neeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 14:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 14:36" />Ipan pe Sises pawanaꞌtɨꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, “Tɨwɨ takuruꞌkenaꞌ nan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ɨpon eꞌpi aꞌpɨꞌpɨtʉi,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, mɨrɨpan tanporo kon aꞌpɨꞌpɨꞌnin nʉꞌsan usepiꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 14:36" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 14" />
  <chapter number="15" style="c" sid="MAT 15" />
  <para style="s1">Wakʉ Mɨrɨ Awonsiꞌkɨ Wakʉ Pen</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 7:1-23">Maꞌ 7:1-23</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 15:1" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan tonpa ton utɨꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ Surusiran poi, mɨrɨpan kon uya, <verse eid="MAT 15:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 15:2" />“Ɨꞌrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ ɨpoitorʉ ton uya ina epuru ton eseru rʉꞌpʉ iꞌkwɨtʉ? Temiyatʉ kon korʉka toꞌ uya pʉra iyesi tentaꞌna kon rawɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 15:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 15:3" />Sises uya toꞌ maimu eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ pe ken iyesi pɨꞌ Papa Maimu iꞌkwɨtʉ auyaꞌnokon, ɨyeseru kon awɨrɨ ɨwesiiꞌmaꞌnokon? <verse eid="MAT 15:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 15:4" />Apʉne pʉra Papa uya, ‘Asanon kon inamatɨꞌ,’ tasaꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ, ‘Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ tʉsanon paꞌnʉꞌnin wɨtoꞌ pe kuru rɨ iyesi,’ tasaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">15:4 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 20:12">Eꞌsotas 20:12</ref>; <ref loc="EXO 21:17">21:17</ref>; <ref loc="LEV 20:9">Ripaitiꞌkas 20:9</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 5:16">Isuꞌtaronomi 5:16</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 15:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 15:5" />Eꞌtane ta auyaꞌnokon, kaꞌpon uya rɨ tʉkʉipʉnʉ pɨꞌ mɨrɨ pe pʉra tʉsan pɨꞌ, ‘Ɨpikaꞌtɨtoꞌ pe ɨneporonʉ uwinɨ tʉsaꞌ man Papa enaꞌ,’ ta yau, <verse eid="MAT 15:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 15:6" />mɨrɨ ke tʉkʉipʉnʉ namatoꞌ iya pʉra iyesi. Mɨrɨ kasa si ipʉra Papa maimu kupʉ auyaꞌnokon ɨyeseru kon pɨkɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 15:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 15:7" />Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan! Iꞌnapai rɨ kuru rɨ Aisaya usaurokʉꞌpʉ man ɨpɨꞌnokon:<verse eid="MAT 15:7" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 15:8" />“‘Pʉsamoro uya unama tʉnta kon ke rɨ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 15:8">eꞌtane ɨnnɨ rɨ toꞌ ewan esi upiyapai.<verse eid="MAT 15:8" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 15:9" />Toꞌ ɨpʉrema upɨꞌ, ɨꞌrɨ epoton kon kasa rɨ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 15:9">toꞌ usenupatoꞌ esi kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya rɨken toꞌ enupaꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ toꞌ eꞌtoꞌ yawɨrɨ pe,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">15:9 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Aisaya 29:13 (LXX)</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 15:9">tawon,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 15:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 15:10" />Anpisin ton kɨꞌmaꞌpʉ Sises uya tʉpiyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya, “Umaimu etatɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itoꞌkaꞌnʉꞌtɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 15:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 15:11" />Ɨꞌrɨ rɨ kaꞌpon mʉta yaꞌ nʉtɨyaiꞌneꞌ uya wakʉ pe pʉra kaꞌpon kupʉ pen; eꞌtane kaꞌpon mʉta yai nepaꞌkayaiꞌneꞌ uya kuru wakʉ pe pʉra kaꞌpon kupʉ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 15:11" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 15:12" />Sises poitorʉ ton uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya, “Miꞌtuyan peꞌ serɨ pe kuru masaurokʉineꞌ uya Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ ɨkɨnʉnpaꞌpʉ?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 15:12" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 15:13" />Toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ iya, “Tanporon nɨ iteꞌ tʉnpɨmɨꞌpʉ pen kuruꞌkatoꞌ oton ukʉipʉnʉ Epʉn po naꞌneꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 15:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 15:14" />Tɨwɨ kamoro itepuru ton nesii, itenu pʉra toꞌ esi mɨrɨ. Tenkuꞌnan uya tenkuꞌnan arɨ aꞌtai, asaꞌrɨ rɨ toꞌ utaꞌmoꞌka mɨrɨ akasaꞌ yaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">15:14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 6:39">Ʉruꞌ 6:39</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 15:14" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 15:15" />Piꞌta uya Sises ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ ta eꞌkwa pe serɨ panton esi?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 15:15" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 15:16" />Sises uya, “Itoꞌkaꞌnʉꞌnin nan pe pʉra rɨ marɨ peꞌ ɨwesi kon mɨrɨ?” taꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 15:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 15:17" />“Ene auyaꞌnokon pʉra peꞌ iyesi ɨꞌrɨ rɨ mʉta yaꞌ newonyaiꞌneꞌ utɨ ewan yaꞌ, mɨrɨpan epaꞌka pun apai? <verse eid="MAT 15:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 15:18" />Eꞌtane ɨri main kaꞌpon mʉta yai nepaꞌkayaiꞌneꞌ uyepʉ itewan yapai. Serɨ ton uya kaꞌpon kupʉ mɨrɨ ɨri pe.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">15:18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 12:34">Maꞌsiu 12:34</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 15:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 15:19" />Apʉne pʉra kaꞌpon ewan yapai ɨri pɨꞌ isenuminkatoꞌ uyepʉ; eꞌwɨn, tʉron kon noꞌpʉ aꞌkɨrɨ teꞌsen pe, tʉnmariꞌmaꞌpʉ pen nɨ aꞌkɨrɨ tekumasen pe, amaꞌ eꞌ pe rɨ, kasi yeꞌ pe rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨri pe tʉron kon pɨꞌ tʉusauroꞌsen pe. <verse eid="MAT 15:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 15:20" />Serɨ ton uya kaꞌpon kupʉ mɨrɨ ɨri pe, temiyatʉ tʉkorʉkaiꞌ pʉra iyentaꞌna uya pen,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 15:20" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Uriꞌsan Mʉre Epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 7:24-30">Maꞌ 7:24-30</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 15:21" />Mɨrɨ pata tʉnɨnse, Sises utɨꞌpʉ Kiyarari ponsiꞌkɨ Taya mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Saitan iteseꞌ ton nono yaꞌne. <verse eid="MAT 15:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 15:22" />Mɨrɨ yawon, uriꞌsan, Esuwerʉ pe pʉra teꞌsen uyeeꞌpʉ ɨkɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨtʉiꞌma Sises piyaꞌ, “Uyepuru, kin Tepiꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ, upɨꞌ ɨsentuꞌmaꞌ! Makoi aꞌkwarʉ yen pe umʉre esi ekotaꞌman pɨꞌ man ipan pe,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 15:22" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 15:23" />Eꞌtane Sises uya imaimu eikʉ pʉra iyesi pɨꞌ, ipoitorʉ ton uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ mɨrɨpan kon uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Ennoꞌkɨ, apʉne pʉra ɨkɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨtʉiꞌma uyeꞌmaꞌpʉkapɨtʉ kon pɨꞌ man,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 15:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 15:24" />Sises uya nin si eikʉꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, “Papa uya uyennoꞌsaꞌ serɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ piyaꞌ rɨken, itanoꞌmasaꞌ kon karimeru amʉꞌ kasa teꞌsan piyaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 15:24" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 15:25" />Uriꞌsan uyeeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan eꞌsekunkaꞌpʉ ipiyau, mɨrɨpan uya, “Uyepuru, upikaꞌtɨꞌ!” taꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 15:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 15:26" />Eikʉꞌpʉ iya, “Ipoken pʉra iyesi mʉre amʉꞌ yu pʉreti enoꞌma toꞌ ikʉn non pero amʉꞌ enaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 15:26" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 15:27" />“Ewaiꞌ, Epuru, eꞌtane tesaꞌ iꞌkiyari punuꞌpɨ utaꞌpoꞌsaꞌ tepʉrʉ poi pɨꞌ rɨ tʉutaꞌreꞌtɨsan kamoro pero amʉꞌ,” taꞌpʉ uriꞌsan uya.<verse eid="MAT 15:27" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 15:28" />Mɨrɨpan pɨꞌ, “Eke pe kuru apurɨtoꞌ auya man! Tɨwɨ si ɨnekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ neꞌkupʉi,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya ipɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan mʉre enaꞌpʉ wakʉ pe mɨrɨ aꞌtai rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 15:28" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tuꞌkan Kon Nɨ Kaꞌpon Amʉꞌ Epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 15:29" />Mɨrɨ tʉpo, Sises uya mɨrɨ pata nɨmɨꞌpʉ; parau kuꞌpɨri Kiyarari eꞌpi poro itɨꞌpʉ. Wʉꞌ pona iyenukuꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan ereutaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 15:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 15:30" />Mɨrɨ yau, anpisin pe kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya tʉusasan pen mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tenkuꞌnaꞌ nan neeꞌpʉ taꞌkɨrɨꞌnokon; tʉron kon neeꞌpʉ toꞌ uya iseꞌmepɨꞌsaꞌ kon mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉusauroꞌsan pen, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉron kon nɨ eꞌneꞌ pe teꞌsan, mɨrɨpan kon nonkapɨtʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya Sises piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya tanporo rɨ toꞌ epiꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 15:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 15:31" />Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ usewansiukaꞌpʉ, tʉusauroꞌsan pen kaꞌpon amʉꞌ usaurokʉ tetase, tʉron kon ipuꞌtɨkaꞌsaꞌ kon usepiꞌtɨsaꞌ tense, tʉusasan pen usarɨ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tenkuꞌnaꞌ nan enasaꞌ ennin pe tense. Mɨrɨ tense Papa apurɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ ɨpʉrematoꞌ ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 15:31" /></para>
  <para style="s1">4,000 Kaisaron Kon Ewekʉꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 15:32" />Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton kɨꞌmaꞌpʉ tʉpiyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ, “Pʉsamoro kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ usentuꞌmayaiꞌ, apʉne pʉra osorʉwau wʉi upiyauꞌnokon toꞌ ukoꞌmansaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon entaꞌnatoꞌ ipɨꞌ pʉra iyesi toꞌ ɨnennoꞌpai pʉra esi iwan pe, yai toꞌ utɨ esi tʉutɨ kon koroꞌtau,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 15:32" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 15:33" />Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ ipoitorʉ ton uya, “Nai yau rɨ eke pe pʉreti eporo ina uya pʉsamoro kaꞌpon amʉꞌ aꞌreꞌtɨtoꞌ ike serɨ ɨnnon nɨ pata yau?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 15:33" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 15:34" />Sises uya toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ kaisa rɨ pʉreti nai ɨpiyauꞌnokon?” tukaiꞌ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 15:34">Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ, “7 pe rɨken mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tuꞌkan kon pen aiko ton moroꞌ amʉꞌ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 15:34" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 15:35" />Anpisin auroꞌkaꞌpʉ iya toꞌ ereutatoꞌ pe non pona. <verse eid="MAT 15:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 15:36" />Mɨrɨpan uya 7 kaisaron pʉreti mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tuꞌkan kon pen moroꞌ amʉꞌ anʉmʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya tenki taꞌpʉ tʉuya rʉꞌpʉ pe iꞌkwɨꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ. Tʉpoitorʉ ton enaꞌ itʉpɨtʉꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan kon uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enaꞌ ekamʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 15:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 15:37" />Tanporo toꞌ entaꞌnaꞌpʉ taꞌwetapɨꞌse. Mɨrɨ tʉpo, ipʉꞌkʉ rʉꞌsan eꞌnonkasaꞌ amʉranʉkʉꞌpʉ ipoitorʉ ton uya, 7 kaisaron paꞌsikiꞌti tʉpeꞌkeꞌne. <verse eid="MAT 15:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 15:38" />Kamoro iyentaꞌnasaꞌ kon tuꞌkanoro esiꞌpʉ 4,000 kaisa rɨ, uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ mʉre amʉꞌ pokon tiꞌtuiꞌ pʉra.<verse eid="MAT 15:38" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 15:39" />Anpisin kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ennoko tʉpo, Sises ekanwaꞌtɨꞌpʉ kanau yaꞌ tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe, mɨrɨpan kon utɨꞌpʉ Makatan iteseꞌ pʉꞌkʉ pona.<verse eid="MAT 15:39" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 15" />
  <chapter number="16" style="c" sid="MAT 16" />
  <para style="s1">Iꞌtutoꞌ Ipɨkɨrɨ Ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 8:11-13">Maꞌ 8:11-13</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 12:54-56">Ʉruꞌ 12:54-56</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 16:1" />Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Satuꞌsi amʉꞌ uyeeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ iꞌtupɨꞌseꞌna tiꞌtutoꞌ ipɨkɨrɨ Epʉn poino kuꞌtoꞌ pe iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:1 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 12:38">Maꞌsiu 12:38</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 11:16">Ʉruꞌ 11:16</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 16:1" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 16:2" />Entakanomaꞌpʉ iya,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">16:2 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Wapiyaroꞌ ton imenukasaꞌ ton yau 2b pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ 3 pʉra kuru rɨ nin iyesi.</char></note> “Koꞌmamʉ pe kuru pata enasaꞌ aꞌtai, ‘Tuna uyepʉ pen mɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra isuweyu pe kaꞌ man,’ ta auyaꞌnokon, <verse eid="MAT 16:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 16:3" />mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ awanakʉiꞌ, ‘Serɨ pe tuna pokon pe aꞌsetun pe pata esi mɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra isuweyu pe kaꞌ esi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ewarupɨ pe,’ ta auyaꞌnokon. Kaꞌ winɨ rɨ ɨꞌrɨ rɨ enpoikanin pe ɨwesi kon, eꞌtane si pata weyu iꞌtutoꞌ ipɨꞌ enpoika auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi. <verse eid="MAT 16:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 16:4" />Ɨri ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyemariꞌmasaꞌ ekumankanin nan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ esi eke Papa tʉrawasooi iꞌtutoꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon ipɨkɨrɨ kupʉ uya iꞌse. Ikupʉ uya pen, eꞌtane Isona pɨꞌ iꞌtutoꞌ ipɨꞌ rʉꞌpʉ naꞌneꞌ rɨken kupʉ uya,” taꞌpʉ iya. Mɨrɨpan kon tʉnɨnse Sises utɨꞌpʉ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:4 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 12:39">Maꞌsiu 12:39</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 11:29">Ʉruꞌ 11:29</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 16:4" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Pariꞌsi Amʉꞌ Mɨrɨ Awonsiꞌkɨ Satuꞌsi Amʉꞌ Uya Enupan Nɨtoꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 8:14-21">Maꞌ 8:14-21</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 16:5" />Parau kuꞌpɨri ratoi pona toꞌ ɨꞌkwɨrɨꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, pʉreti arɨ toꞌ uya pʉra ipoitorʉ ton upuꞌtɨkaaꞌpʉ esiꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 16:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 16:6" />“Tiꞌtuiꞌ eꞌtɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “teꞌmainanpaiꞌ eꞌtɨꞌ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Satuꞌsi amʉꞌ uya pʉrowa aꞌsarutanʉꞌtoꞌ ike namaiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:6 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 12:1">Ʉruꞌ 12:1</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 16:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 16:7" />Toꞌ usaurokʉꞌpʉ tiwanoꞌ kon pe, “Apʉne pʉra pʉreti neꞌsaꞌ kasa pʉra isaurokʉ mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 16:7" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 16:8" />Toꞌ usauroꞌtoꞌ iꞌtu tʉuya pɨꞌ, Sises uya toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon aiko rʉꞌkwɨ apurɨtoꞌ iya ton! Ɨꞌrɨ pɨꞌ ausaurokʉ kon pʉreti pʉra ɨwesi kon pɨꞌ? <verse eid="MAT 16:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 16:9" />Itoꞌkaꞌnʉkʉ auyaꞌnokon pʉra rɨ marɨ peꞌ iyesi? Ɨyenu kon yau peꞌ ikupʉ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi 5 kaisaron pʉreti 5,000 kaisaron kon iwanoꞌ rʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ paꞌsikiꞌti ton peꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon?<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:9 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 14:17-21">Maꞌsiu 14:17-21</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 16:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 16:10" />Mɨrɨ pe pʉra, 7 kaisaron pʉreti 4,000 kaisaron kon iwanoꞌ, ɨꞌrɨ kaisa rɨ paꞌsikiꞌti mamʉranʉꞌtaꞌtʉi?<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:10 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 15:34-38">Maꞌsiu 15:34-38</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 16:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 16:11" />Nai pe itoꞌkaꞌnʉkʉ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi pʉreti pɨꞌ ayauroꞌka uya ꞌnokon pen tukaiꞌ? Eꞌtane Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Satuꞌsi amʉꞌ uya pʉreti aꞌsarutanʉꞌtoꞌ namaiꞌ ɨyeꞌmainanpa kon pa,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 16:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 16:12" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, toꞌ uya itoꞌkaꞌnʉkʉꞌpʉ pʉrowa aꞌsarutanʉꞌnin itisu pen nɨ pɨꞌ kenʉꞌ Sises usaurokʉꞌpʉ tukaiꞌ, eꞌtane Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Satuꞌsi amʉꞌ uya enupan nɨtoꞌ pɨꞌ kenʉꞌ tukaiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 16:12" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Piꞌta Uya Sises Ekamaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 8:27-30">Maꞌ 8:27-30</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:18-21">Ʉruꞌ 9:18-21</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 16:13" />Sises mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoitorʉ ton uya Sisariya Piriꞌpai nono eposaꞌ aꞌtai, tʉpoitorʉ ton ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ iya, “Ɨnʉꞌ pe Kaꞌpon, Papa winon esi tukaiꞌ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ nʉsauroꞌan?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 16:13" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 16:14" />Toꞌ uya entakanomaꞌpʉ, “Tʉron kon uya Isaan Paꞌtes ta ɨpɨꞌ; tʉron kon uya kanan puꞌkenaꞌ Iraisa ta; tʉron kon uya rɨ marɨ Iseremaya mɨrɨ pe pʉra tʉron kon puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ tonpa ton ta ɨpɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 14:1-2">Maꞌsiu 14:1-2</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 6:14-15">Maꞌ 6:14-15</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:7-8">Ʉruꞌ 9:7-8</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 16:14" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 16:15" />“Eꞌtane si, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon, ɨnʉꞌ pe ken si esi mʉkayatʉu?” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 16:15" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 16:16" />Saiman Piꞌta uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ɨmɨrɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Kʉrai,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">16:16 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya; Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe; v. 20 yau nɨrɨ.</char></note> nurɨne teꞌsen Papa Mumu,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:16 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 6:68-69">Isaan 6:68-69</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 16:16" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 16:17" />Sises uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Poriꞌ rɨ ɨmɨrɨ, Saiman, Isona mu, iꞌnapairon serɨ uyeꞌsaꞌ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ winɨ pen eꞌtane tʉmɨrɨ pe Papa uya ekamasaꞌ ɨpɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 16:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 16:18" />Ekama uya serɨ, Piꞌta pe ɨyeseꞌ esi, Tɨꞌ ta eꞌkwa pe. Usoꞌsii nin si amɨ uya, ɨmɨrɨ tɨꞌ po, iyeriꞌsaꞌ kon utɨtoꞌ yaꞌ pata mʉraꞌtaai enatoꞌ oton pen itentai. <verse eid="MAT 16:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 16:19" />Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yau kii ke ɨrepa uya; serɨ non po ɨꞌrɨ rɨ auronsaꞌ auya pe iyesi aꞌtai, Papa uya kanan auromʉ mɨrɨ Epʉn po; mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ serɨ non po ɨꞌrɨ rɨ eukasaꞌ auya pe iyesi aꞌtai, Papa uya kanan euka mɨrɨ Epʉn po,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:19 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 18:18">Maꞌsiu 18:18</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 20:23">Isaan 20:23</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 16:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 16:20" />Mɨrɨpan uya tʉpoitorʉ ton panamaꞌpʉ ɨnʉꞌ rɨ panaꞌtɨ toꞌ uya namaiꞌ Kʉrai pe iyesi, tukaiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 16:20" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tʉumaꞌtatoꞌ Ekamaꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 8:31-9:1">Maꞌ 8:31–9:1</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:22-27">Ʉruꞌ 9:22-27</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 16:21" />Mɨrɨ siꞌkɨrɨ, Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ ekamaꞌpʉ Surusiran pona tʉutɨtoꞌ oton nɨ, mɨrɨ yau tuꞌkan yau rɨ itepuru ton uya, Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan uya rɨ tʉkotaꞌmatoꞌ oton, mɨrɨpan kon uya tʉwɨtoꞌ oton, mɨrɨpan teꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkatoꞌ oton itosorʉwano wʉi aꞌtai tʉukoꞌmanton pe ekamaꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 16:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 16:22" />Piꞌta uya Sises arɨꞌpʉ, ɨnnɨ kuru pʉra rɨ tʉron kon ipoitorʉ ton piyapai eseremeꞌseꞌna. “Mɨrɨ kasa kasaurokʉi! Serɨ kʉseꞌkuꞌnin ɨpɨꞌ, uyepuru!” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 16:22" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 16:23" />Sises eraꞌtɨꞌpʉ Piꞌta winɨkʉiꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya, “Atamakɨ, Seꞌtan<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">16:23 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Seꞌtan</char><char style="ft" closed="false">–Makoi eseꞌ isakon, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Papa eseru ewarumaꞌtɨnin </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe.</char></note>!” taꞌpʉ. “Uyeꞌma tau uwaꞌkʉꞌpɨꞌnin tɨꞌ pe meꞌaiꞌ; kaꞌpon usenuminkatoꞌ kasa ɨusenuminka, Papa usenuminkatoꞌ kasa pʉra,” taꞌpʉ iya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 16:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 16:24" />Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ taꞌpʉ, “Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ upoitorʉ pe eꞌpai naꞌneꞌ, tɨwɨ teseru nonkai mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tekotaꞌmatoꞌ kurusuꞌ anʉmʉi, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ upɨkɨrɨ tʉuyeꞌtoꞌ pe.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:24 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 10:38">Maꞌsiu 10:38</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 14:27">Ʉruꞌ 14:27</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 16:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 16:25" />Apʉne pʉra ɨnʉꞌ rɨ serɨ yau tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ ɨnnonkapai pʉra naꞌneꞌ uya epotoꞌ oton pen nɨ, eꞌtane ɨnʉꞌ rɨ serɨ yau tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ nonkanin uya, urɨ wenai, epotoꞌ oton.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:25 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 10:39">Maꞌsiu 10:39</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 17:33">Ʉruꞌ 17:33</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 12:25">Isaan 12:25</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 16:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 16:26" />Ɨꞌrɨ wakʉ esi kaꞌpon pɨꞌ serɨ po tanporon nɨ eposaꞌ iya yau taꞌkwarʉ nonkaiꞌma? Mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ɨꞌrɨ tʉrʉ iya taꞌkwarʉ entakanoꞌ pe? <verse eid="MAT 16:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 16:27" />Apanaꞌtɨ uya ꞌnokon serɨ; Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyeꞌtoꞌ oton tʉkʉipʉnʉ meruntɨrʉ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itinserʉʉi ton pokon pe. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, toꞌ epeꞌpʉ ke kaꞌpon amʉꞌ eꞌmatoꞌ iya oton toꞌ nʉkupʉꞌpʉ pɨkɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">16:27 </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Eren 62:12; <ref loc="MAT 25:31">Maꞌsiu 25:31</ref>; <ref loc="ROM 2:6">Ron 2:6</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 16:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 16:28" />Iꞌnapairon kuru ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, serɨ yau iyeꞌsotoꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ naꞌneꞌ nan tonpa ton eriꞌtoꞌ oton pen, Kaꞌpon Papa winon uyepʉ esaꞌ wannɨ pe teꞌtoꞌ yau ene tʉuyaꞌnokon rawɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 16:28" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 16" />
  <chapter number="17" style="c" sid="MAT 17" />
  <para style="s1">Sises Utaꞌkwakaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 9:2-13">Maꞌ 9:2-13</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:28-36">Ʉruꞌ 9:28-36</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 17:1" />6 kaisa rɨ wʉi tʉpo, Sises uya Piꞌta, Isens, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyakon Isaan pokon nɨken arɨꞌpʉ taꞌkɨrɨ wʉꞌ nakapu pona. <verse eid="MAT 17:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 17:2" />Mɨrɨ yau, tʉron nɨ pe iyenaꞌpʉ, itemʉꞌ eꞌweiꞌtɨꞌpʉ wʉi enu kasa, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipon enaꞌpʉ aimuꞌne, enkenaꞌ pe. <verse eid="MAT 17:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 17:3" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai kuru si mɨrɨ yau, Mosiꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Iraisa usenpoikaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya Sises auroꞌka esiꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 17:3" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 17:4" />Piꞌta uya taꞌpʉ Sises pɨꞌ, “Uyepuru! Wakʉ rɨ pan pe serɨ yau ina man! Iꞌse ɨwesi yau, osorʉwau ɨiwʉꞌ kon amɨ uya mɨrɨ; tikin nɨ ɨiwanoꞌ pe, Mosiꞌ iwanoꞌ pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Iraisa iwanoꞌ pe,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 17:4" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 17:5" />Piꞌta usaurokʉ koroꞌtau, enkenaꞌ kapuruꞌ uya toꞌ nɨpontɨꞌpʉ. Main kapuruꞌ yawon uya taꞌpʉ, “Umu pʉse rɨ, Uniꞌnʉnkanʉ, ipɨꞌ poriꞌ pe eꞌaiꞌ ipan pe; imaimu etatɨꞌ!” tawon.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">17:5 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 22:2">Iseneses 22:2</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 18:15">Isuꞌtaronomi 18:15</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 2:7">Eren 2:7</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 42:1">Aisaya 42:1</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 3:17">Maꞌsiu 3:17</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 1:11">Maꞌ 1:11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:22">Ʉruꞌ 3:22</ref>; <ref loc="2PE 1:17-18">2 Piꞌta 1:17-18</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 17:5" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 17:6" />Ipoitorʉ ton uya serɨ main etasaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ etʉipɨtʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon utaꞌmoꞌkaꞌpʉ non pona itemʉꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 17:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 17:7" />Eꞌtane Sises uyeeꞌpʉ toꞌ aꞌpɨꞌseꞌna, “Eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkatɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya, “Ketʉipɨꞌtʉu,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 17:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 17:8" />Tenu kon anʉnsaꞌ toꞌ uya aꞌtai, ɨnʉꞌ eneꞌpʉ toꞌ uya pen nɨ, Sises rɨken eneꞌpʉ toꞌ uya tikin sarɨ.<verse eid="MAT 17:8" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 17:9" />Wʉꞌ ponsiꞌkɨ ɨuꞌtɨiꞌma rɨ, Sises uya toꞌ panamaꞌpʉ, “Ɨnʉꞌ pɨꞌ rɨ ɨneneꞌpʉ kon kʉsekamatʉu, Kaꞌpon, Papa winon eriꞌsaꞌ eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkasaꞌ pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 17:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 17:10" />Ipoitorʉ ton uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ pe ken si iyesi pɨꞌ Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan uya Iraisa kuru uyeꞌtoꞌ oton wapiya ta?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">17:10 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAL 4:5">Maraꞌkai 4:5</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 17:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 17:11" />Sises uya toꞌ entakanomaꞌpʉ, “Iꞌnapairɨ rɨ Iraisa uyeꞌtoꞌ oton ta toꞌ uya, tanporon nɨ konekaiꞌ iyesiꞌpʉ yaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">17:11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 48:10">Sairaꞌ 48:10</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 17:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 17:12" />Eꞌtane nin si ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, Iraisa uyeꞌkaaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan iꞌtu toꞌ uya pʉra rɨ iyesiꞌpʉ, eꞌtane iꞌse teꞌtoꞌ kon awɨrɨ ɨri eseru kupʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ. Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ Kaꞌpon, Papa winon ekotaꞌmatoꞌ oton toꞌ enau,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">17:12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 11:14">Maꞌsiu 11:14</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 17:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 17:13" />Iraisa pɨꞌ Sises usaurokʉ aꞌtai, Isaan Paꞌtes pɨꞌ isaurokʉ tukaiꞌ ipoitorʉ ton uya iꞌtuꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 17:13" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Warawoꞌ Mʉre Epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 9:14-29">Maꞌ 9:14-29</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:37-43a">Ʉruꞌ 9:37-43a</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 17:14" />Anpisin ton koroꞌtaꞌ toꞌ uyeꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, kaꞌpon uyeeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan eꞌsekunkaꞌpʉ ipiyau. <verse eid="MAT 17:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 17:15" />Taꞌpʉ iya Sises pɨꞌ, “Uyepuru, umu pɨꞌ ɨsentuꞌmakɨ. Yai itɨpɨtʉ, ipan pe iyekotaꞌma. Apoꞌ yaꞌ, tuna kaꞌ rɨ itaꞌmoꞌkapɨꞌpɨtʉ. <verse eid="MAT 17:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 17:16" />Ɨpoitorʉ ton piyaꞌ ineeꞌpʉ uya, eꞌtane toꞌ uya epiꞌtɨ poken pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ,” taꞌpʉ iya Sises pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 17:16" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 17:17" />“Ɨri sɨ! Ɨri ton nɨ, apurɨnin nan pen nɨ serɨ aꞌtaino kon! Ɨꞌrɨ pʉꞌkʉ pona usetaꞌka pʉra ukoꞌmamʉ ɨpiyauꞌnokon? Ɨꞌrɨ pʉꞌkʉ pona ayaꞌkɨrɨꞌnokon esi? Ineꞌtɨꞌ upiyaꞌ!” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 17:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 17:18" />Sises uya makoi aꞌkwarʉ eseremekʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan epaꞌkaꞌpʉ warawoꞌ mʉre apai. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai rɨ, isepiꞌtɨꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 17:18" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 17:19" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises piyaꞌ ipoitorʉ ton uyeeꞌpʉ amaꞌai, mɨrɨpan kon uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ ina uya enpaꞌka pʉra iyesi?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 17:19" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 17:20" />Sises uya toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ, “Apʉne pʉra aiko pe rʉꞌkwɨ apurɨtoꞌ auyaꞌnokon esi. Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; aiko rʉꞌkwɨ mostaꞌ enaꞌpɨ kasa apurɨtoꞌ auyaꞌnokon esi yau, wʉꞌ pɨꞌ, ‘Atamakɨ mɨ airɨ!’ tasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, itama rɨ. Ɨꞌrɨ rɨ kupʉ auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, saꞌman pe pʉra rɨ iyesi ɨponaꞌnokon.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">17:20 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 21:21">Maꞌsiu 21:21</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 11:23">Maꞌ 11:23</ref>; <ref loc="1CO 13:2">1 Koren 13:2</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 17:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 17:21" />Eꞌtane serɨ rupɨ epaꞌka pʉra iyesi ɨpʉreman mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ useruman tʉutaꞌreꞌtɨiꞌ pʉra uya rɨken enpaꞌka,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">17:21 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tʉron nɨ imenukasaꞌ ton yau v. 21 pʉra iyesi.</char></note><verse eid="MAT 17:21" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Usaurokʉꞌpʉ Iyakon Iteꞌkwa Pe Tʉumaꞌtatoꞌ Pɨꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 17:22" />Tanporo toꞌ amʉrasaꞌ aꞌtai Kiyarari pona, Sises uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Kaꞌpon, Papa winon eparankatoꞌ oton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 17:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 17:23" />Toꞌ uya iwɨtoꞌ oton, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itosorʉwano wʉi aꞌtai iyeꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkatoꞌ oton tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ yaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan poitorʉ ton upokoitaꞌpʉ ipan pe.<verse eid="MAT 17:23" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Esuwerʉ Amʉꞌ Useꞌmatoꞌ, Ɨpʉrematoꞌ Iwʉꞌ Taꞌ Teꞌmasen</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 17:24" />Sises mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoitorʉ ton uya Kaꞌpaneyan pata eposaꞌ aꞌtai, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ taꞌ teꞌmasen amʉranʉꞌnin nan uyeeꞌpʉ Piꞌta piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨtiꞌsaai kon peꞌ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ taꞌ tʉuseꞌmasen?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">17:24 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 30:13">Eꞌsotas 30:13</ref>; <ref loc="EXO 38:26">38:26</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 17:24" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 17:25" />Piꞌta uya toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ewaiꞌ, eꞌmanin kʉrɨ rɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 17:25">Mɨrɨpan Piꞌta utɨꞌpʉ ɨutɨ taꞌ. Sises usaurokʉꞌpʉ wapiya kuru, mɨrɨpan uya Piꞌta ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ tukaiꞌ mɨsenuminkayan Saiman? Ɨnʉꞌ yan rupɨ winɨpai kin amʉꞌ uya pʉrata amʉranʉꞌtoꞌ pe iyesi? Patawon amʉꞌ mɨrɨ pe pʉra kaꞌkʉran amʉꞌ winɨpai katɨ?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 17:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 17:26" />Piꞌta uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Kaꞌkʉran amʉꞌ winɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 17:26">“Patawon amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ pe pʉra iyesi,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya. <verse eid="MAT 17:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 17:27" />“Eꞌtane pʉsamoro kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ɨnɨkɨntanʉꞌpai pʉra eꞌnɨ. Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ, konoiꞌ pɨꞌ enta parau kuꞌpɨri kaꞌ, mɨrɨpan wapiya kuru anmaꞌpʉ moroꞌ inta nau pʉrata pun eporo auya mɨrɨ, asakɨrɨꞌne wʉi eꞌtʉrawasoman nɨsaꞌ epeꞌpʉ airon nɨ, mɨrɨpan ke eꞌmaseꞌna mɨtɨiꞌ uiwanoꞌ pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨiwanoꞌ pe nɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 17:27" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 17" />
  <chapter number="18" style="c" sid="MAT 18" />
  <para style="s1">Ɨnʉꞌ Esi Eke Pe Kuru?</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 9:33-37">Maꞌ 9:33-37</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:46-48">Ʉruꞌ 9:46-48</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 18:1" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises poitorʉ ton uyeeꞌpʉ ekamaꞌpoiꞌ, “Ɨnʉꞌ kuru si eꞌtoꞌ oton eke pe Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yau?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">18:1 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 22:24">Ʉruꞌ 22:24</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 18:1" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 18:2" />Sises uya mʉre rʉꞌkwɨ kɨꞌmaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan sotoꞌkaꞌpʉ iya toꞌ koroꞌtau, <verse eid="MAT 18:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 18:3" />mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ, “Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; ɨusensima kon aꞌtai rɨken mʉre amʉꞌ pe tenaiꞌ, ɨyepaꞌka kon Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">18:3 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 10:15">Maꞌ 10:15</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 18:17">Ʉruꞌ 18:17</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 18:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 18:4" />Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ esi mɨ pe teꞌkuꞌsen pe pʉra mʉre naꞌneꞌ kasa esi mɨrɨ eke pe Papa pona. <verse eid="MAT 18:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 18:5" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ, ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ aiko rʉꞌkwɨ mʉre pʉse rɨ warai ereutanʉkʉ aꞌtai, uyeseꞌ yau, uyereutanʉkʉ iya pe rɨ iyesi.<verse eid="MAT 18:5" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Kaꞌpon Amʉꞌ Umakoita Emapuꞌtɨ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 9:42-48">Maꞌ 9:42-48</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 17:1-2">Ʉruꞌ 17:1-2</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 18:6" />“Eꞌtane ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ pʉsamoro uyapurɨnin nan aiko ton nʉꞌkwɨ tonpa eꞌmakoima emapuꞌtɨsaꞌ yau, wakʉ iwa pe rɨ iyesi kʉrɨ rɨ kaꞌpon iꞌmʉ pɨꞌ eke aꞌnaiꞌ eꞌpatoꞌ ike tɨꞌ ewaꞌtɨsaꞌ aꞌtai, mɨrɨpan enoꞌmatoꞌ pe parau kaꞌ iyaputatoꞌ pe. <verse eid="MAT 18:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 18:7" />Ɨsɨ sɨ, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ non pon kon, apʉne pʉra kaꞌpon amʉꞌ umakoita emapuꞌtɨ toꞌ uya pɨꞌ. Mɨrɨ warai ton nɨ eꞌkuꞌtoꞌ pe iyesi eꞌtane, ɨsɨ yau kʉrɨ man iyeꞌkupʉ emapuꞌtɨnin. <verse eid="MAT 18:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 18:8" />Ɨyemiyatʉ mɨrɨ pe pʉra aꞌta uya ɨyeꞌmakoima emapuꞌtɨ pe iyesi yau, aꞌtɨkɨ enoꞌma pa; wakʉ iwa pe iyesi itemiyatʉ pʉra mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iꞌta pʉra esiiꞌma tɨwɨrɨ rɨ ɨukoꞌmantoꞌ yaꞌ ɨyepaꞌka aꞌtai, tanporo ɨpun enoꞌma apoꞌ, tɨwɨroꞌ rɨ yaꞌ entai.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">18:8 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 5:30">Maꞌsiu 5:30</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 18:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 18:9" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨyenu uya ɨyeꞌmakoima emapuꞌtɨ pe iyesi yau, imoꞌkaꞌ enoꞌma pa; wakʉ iwa pe iyesi tikin nɨ itenu esiiꞌma tɨwɨrɨ rɨ ɨukoꞌmantoꞌ yaꞌ ɨyepaꞌka aꞌtai, asaꞌrɨ itenu apoꞌ, iyaꞌmu pʉn yaꞌ ɨyenoꞌma entai,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">18:9 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 5:29">Maꞌsiu 5:29</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 18:9" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Karimeru Utanoꞌmaꞌpʉ Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 15:3-7">Ʉruꞌ 15:3-7</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 18:10" />Miyarɨ rɨ Sises esiꞌpʉ usauroꞌnɨ pɨꞌ, “Pʉsamoro aiko ton nʉꞌkwɨ kʉsenpɨꞌtʉu. Ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, toꞌ inserʉʉi ton esi ukʉipʉnʉ emʉꞌ ennin nan pe tɨwɨrɨ rɨ Epʉn po.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">18:10 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="TOB 12:15">Topayas 12:15</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 18:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 18:11" />Serɨ ta uya ɨpɨꞌnokon apʉne pʉra Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyeꞌsaꞌ itanoꞌmasaꞌ kon pikaꞌtɨiꞌ.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">18:11 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tʉron nɨ imenukasaꞌ ton yau v. 11 pʉra iyesi.</char></note><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">18:11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 19:10">Ʉruꞌ 19:10</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 18:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 18:12" />Ɨꞌrɨ tukaiꞌ mɨsenuminkayan? Kaꞌpon esi yau 100 kaisaron kon karimeru amʉꞌ esaꞌ pe, mɨrɨpan kon tonpa utanoꞌmasaꞌ yau, 99 pan kon peꞌ karimeru amʉꞌ nɨmɨ iya pen wʉꞌ po itanoꞌmasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ warinpaseꞌna tʉutɨtoꞌ pe? <verse eid="MAT 18:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 18:13" />Mɨrɨpan eposaꞌ tʉuya yau, iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; poriꞌ pe kuru iyesi tikin nan itanoꞌmasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ karimeru pɨꞌ 99 pan kon itanoꞌmasaꞌ kon pen karimeru amʉꞌ pɨꞌ poriꞌ pe tesi entai. <verse eid="MAT 18:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 18:14" />Mɨrɨ naꞌneꞌ kasa, ɨkʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon esi pʉsamoro aiko ton nʉꞌkwɨ uyapurɨnin nan utanoꞌma iꞌse pʉra,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 18:14" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Ɨtonpa Eꞌmakoimasaꞌ Aꞌtaino</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 18:15" />Miyarɨ rɨ Sises esiꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton auroꞌka pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ, “Ɨri pe ɨtonpa uya ɨkuꞌsaꞌ yau, ɨri inkupʉꞌpʉ ekama ta ipɨꞌ, asaꞌken esiiꞌma. Amaimu etasaꞌ iya yau, mɨrɨ nin si ɨtonpa pe inaꞌposaꞌ auya. <verse eid="MAT 18:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 18:16" />Eꞌtane amaimu eta iya pʉra iyesi yau, tikin nɨ mɨrɨ pe pʉra asaꞌrɨ rɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ akɨ ayaꞌkɨrɨ auroꞌkakaꞌseꞌna. Pʉsamoro asaꞌron kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ esi, ‘auroꞌka pɨꞌ ɨpikaꞌtɨnin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨri pe ɨweꞌsaꞌ esi iꞌnapai rɨ tawon nan pe ipɨꞌ.’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">18:16 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Isuꞌtaronomi 19:15</char></note> <verse eid="MAT 18:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 18:17" />Eꞌtane toꞌ ɨnetapai pʉra kanan iyesi yau, ekamatɨꞌ soꞌsi tawon kon pɨꞌ, eꞌtane ɨnetapai pʉra kanan iyesi yau, inonkatɨꞌ Papa apurɨnin pen mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ pʉrata amʉranʉꞌnin kasa iyeꞌtoꞌ pe.<verse eid="MAT 18:17" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 18:18" />“Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; serɨ non po ɨꞌrɨ rɨ auronsaꞌ auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, Epʉn po kanan Papa uya auromʉ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ serɨ non po ɨꞌrɨ rɨ eukasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, Papa uya kanan euka Epʉn po.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">18:18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 16:19">Maꞌsiu 16:19</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 20:23">Isaan 20:23</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 18:18" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 18:19" />“Se kanan ekama uya etatɨꞌ: Asaꞌrɨ tekonekaiꞌ serɨ non po ɨꞌrɨ rɨ ɨnekamaꞌponʉ kon pɨꞌ, ukʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon uya rɨ amaimu kon eikʉ. <verse eid="MAT 18:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 18:20" />Asaꞌron kon, osorʉwawon kon nʉꞌkwɨ rɨ amʉrasaꞌ aꞌtai, uyeseꞌ yau, toꞌ piyau rɨ esi,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 18:20" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tʉusentuꞌmasen Pen Ipoitorʉ Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 18:21" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Piꞌta uyeeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ ekamaꞌposeꞌna, “Uyepuru, ɨꞌrɨ kaisa rɨ iteꞌkwa utonpa eꞌmakoimasaꞌ upɨꞌ pɨꞌ usentuꞌma? 7 kaisa rɨ iteꞌkwa peꞌ?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 18:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 18:22" />Sises uya Piꞌta eikʉꞌpʉ, “7 kaisa rɨ iteꞌkwa pen eꞌtane, 70 kaisa rɨ 7 iteꞌkwa kuru<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">18:22 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">70 kaisa rɨ 7 iteꞌkwa kuru; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">77 kaisa rɨ iteꞌkwa</char></note>,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">18:22 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 4:24">Iseneses 4:24</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 17:3-4">Ʉruꞌ 17:3-4</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 18:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 18:23" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uya panton ekamaꞌpʉ Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe eseru pɨꞌ. “Se naꞌneꞌ kasa Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe eseru esi: Kin esiꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ tʉpʉrataai koꞌmanʉꞌpɨꞌnin nan winɨ tʉpʉrataai amʉranʉkʉ pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 18:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 18:24" />Iyepiyaꞌtɨ koroꞌtau, ipoitorʉ uya eke kuru rɨ ipʉrataai koꞌmanʉꞌpɨꞌnin neeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 18:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 18:25" />Ipʉrataai pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ tepuru eꞌmatoꞌ iya ike. Kin uya taꞌpʉ, ‘Ikʉrʉpoꞌpomatɨꞌ, inoꞌpʉ, imunkɨ amʉꞌ pokon pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itimamin ton nɨ, mɨrɨpan epeꞌpʉ uya inkoꞌmanʉꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ eꞌmatoꞌ pe,’ taꞌpʉ kin uya.<verse eid="MAT 18:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 18:26" />“Mɨrɨpan poitorʉ utaꞌmoꞌkaꞌpʉ irau teseꞌmu po tenaiꞌ, ‘Apʉne parɨ, ɨyeꞌma uya rɨ mɨrɨ tanporo,’ taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 18:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 18:27" />Mɨrɨ wenai, kin usentuꞌmaꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, iyeꞌwomasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ rɨ nin si tʉkukaiꞌ, ennokoꞌpʉ iya mɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 18:27" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 18:28" />“Eꞌtane pʉse rɨ utɨꞌpʉ aiko rʉꞌkwɨ rɨ nin tʉpʉrataai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">18:28 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">aiko rʉꞌkwɨ rɨ nin tʉpʉrataai </char><char style="ft" closed="false">—100 pʉrata pun, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">tenariyas </char><char style="ft" closed="false">iteseꞌ</char></note> koꞌmanʉꞌpɨꞌnin piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌsiiꞌ iꞌmʉ pɨꞌ, iꞌmʉ kʉtʉtʉꞌkaꞌpʉ. ‘Inke pʉra upʉrataai itʉkɨ!’ taiꞌma. <verse eid="MAT 18:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 18:29" />Mɨrɨpan nʉꞌkwɨ saꞌne utaꞌmoꞌkaꞌpʉ irau temʉꞌ po, ‘Apʉne saꞌne, ɨyeꞌma uya rɨ mɨrɨ,’ taiꞌma. <verse eid="MAT 18:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 18:30" />Eꞌtane, ewaiꞌ ta iya pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ, aꞌsiꞌpʉ iya parikiꞌsi taꞌ tʉnkoꞌmanʉkʉꞌpʉ eꞌma iya pʉꞌkʉ pona. <verse eid="MAT 18:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 18:31" />Tʉron kon ipoitorʉ ton uya ensaꞌ aꞌtai, inkupʉnʉ tense ipan pe toꞌ upokoitaꞌpʉ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, toꞌ utɨꞌpʉ tepuru kon pɨꞌ ekamaseꞌna tanporo inkupʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 18:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 18:32" />Mɨrɨpan epuru uya ikɨꞌmaꞌpʉ, ‘Ɨmɨrɨ ɨri rɨ,’ taꞌpʉ iya ipɨꞌ. ‘Tɨwɨ rɨ si nesii, taꞌpʉ uya ɨpɨꞌ, apʉne pʉra ipan pe rɨ autaꞌkwarʉka pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 18:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 18:33" />Ɨsentuꞌmapai pʉra peꞌ ɨwesi mɨ ɨtonpa pɨꞌ, usentuꞌmataineꞌ kasa ɨpɨꞌ?’ taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 18:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 18:34" />Tʉusakorotaiꞌ itepuru uya itʉrʉꞌpʉ pʉresiman amʉꞌ enaꞌ toꞌ uya aꞌsitoꞌ pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipantaꞌmapɨꞌtoꞌ pe toꞌ uya, tanporo tʉpʉrataai naꞌpo iya pona rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 18:34" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 18:35" />“Mɨrɨ naꞌneꞌ kasa kuru Epʉn pon, ukʉipʉnʉ uya ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon, ɨtonpa kon pɨꞌ ɨyewan kon yau tʉusentuꞌmasan pen, kuꞌtoꞌ oton,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 18:35" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 18" />
  <chapter number="19" style="c" sid="MAT 19" />
  <para style="s1">Noꞌpʉ Nonkatoꞌ Ekareei Ekamaꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 10:1-12">Maꞌ 10:1-12</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 19:1" />Serɨ ton ta tʉuya eꞌnonkasaꞌ aꞌtai, Sises uya Kiyarari nɨmɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ Isutiya nono, Isotan tuna ratoi pona. <verse eid="MAT 19:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 19:2" />Tuꞌkan kon anpisin utɨꞌpʉ ipɨkɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan kon epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ iya mɨrɨ yau.<verse eid="MAT 19:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 19:3" />Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ tonpa ton uyeeꞌpʉ iꞌtupɨꞌseꞌna. Toꞌ uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Main awɨrɨ rɨ eꞌnɨ pe rɨ peꞌ iyesi kaꞌpon uya tʉnoꞌpʉ nonkatoꞌ ɨꞌrɨ rɨ wenai?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 19:3" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 19:4" />“Ene auyaꞌnokon pʉra peꞌ neꞌpɨꞌan kareta yau?” taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ. “Pena iyepiyaꞌtɨ aꞌtai, ‘Kaꞌnin uya warawoꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ uriꞌsan nɨrɨ konekaꞌpʉ.’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">19:4 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Iseneses 1:27; 5:2</char></note> <verse eid="MAT 19:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 19:5" />Taꞌpʉ iya, ‘Mɨrɨ wenai, warawoꞌ uya tʉkʉipʉnʉ, tʉsan nɨrɨ nɨntoꞌ pe iyesi, mɨrɨpan utaꞌsikʉ tʉnoꞌpʉ yaꞌ, mɨrɨpan asaꞌron kon ena tikin nɨ ipun.’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">19:5 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Iseneses 2:24</char></note> <verse eid="MAT 19:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 19:6" />Mɨrɨ kasa, asaꞌrɨ toꞌ esi pen, eꞌtane tikin nɨ. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, Papa naꞌsikʉꞌsan ɨsipona, moꞌka kaꞌpon uya kʉseꞌnin,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 19:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 19:7" />Toꞌ uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ pe ken si iyesi pɨꞌ eꞌnonkan nɨtoꞌ karetaai tʉmenukaiꞌ ɨnoꞌpʉ inonkakɨ tasaꞌ Mosiꞌ uya?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">19:7 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 24:1-4">Isuꞌtaronomi 24:1-4</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 5:31">Maꞌsiu 5:31</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 19:7" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 19:8" />Sises uya toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ, “Mosiꞌ uya ɨnoꞌpʉ kon amʉꞌ inonkatɨꞌ tasaꞌ, saꞌman pe rɨ ɨyewan kon esi wenai, mɨrɨpan pen nin pena iyepiyaꞌtɨꞌpʉ siꞌkɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 19:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 19:9" />Ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; ɨnʉꞌ rɨ tʉnoꞌpʉ nonkayaiꞌneꞌ, iyekumasaꞌ pen nɨ eꞌtane, mɨrɨpan uya tʉron nɨ uriꞌsan mariꞌma, iyekuma pe iyesi mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">19:9 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 5:32">Maꞌsiu 5:32</ref>; <ref loc="1CO 7:10-11">1 Koren 7:10-11</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 19:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 19:10" />Ipoitorʉ ton uya taꞌpʉ, “Mɨrɨ naꞌneꞌ kasa iyesi yau, tɨwɨ uriꞌsan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ warawoꞌ emariꞌma eꞌpai pʉra rɨ nin si man,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 19:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 19:11" />Sises uya toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ, “Tanporon kon pɨꞌ ta pen nɨ mɨrɨ, eꞌtane kamo rɨken anʉnnin nʉꞌsan nɨ. <verse eid="MAT 19:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 19:12" />Tʉron kon entusaꞌ temariꞌmasen yeꞌ pe pʉra rɨ, tʉron kon konekasaꞌ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya temariꞌmasen yeꞌ pe pʉra rɨ, tʉron kon nɨrɨ eꞌkuꞌsaꞌ tiwanoꞌ kon pe temariꞌmasen yeꞌ pe pʉra teꞌtoꞌ kon pe, Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe uriyaꞌ. Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ kʉrɨ tikin sarɨ eꞌpaino eꞌtoꞌ pe rɨ iyesi,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 19:12" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Mʉre Amʉꞌ Pʉremaꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 10:13-16">Maꞌ 10:13-16</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 18:15-17">Ʉruꞌ 18:15-17</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 19:13" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, mʉre amʉꞌ neeꞌpʉ toꞌ uya Sises piyaꞌ temiyatʉ tʉtoꞌ pe iya toꞌ pona mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyɨpʉrematoꞌ pe toꞌ pona, eꞌtane ipoitorʉ ton uya kamoro toꞌ neꞌnin nʉꞌsan eseremekʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 19:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 19:14" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ, “Tɨwɨ mʉre amʉꞌ nʉyepʉi upiyaꞌ; toꞌ kʉsereutanʉꞌtʉu, apʉne pʉra pʉsamoro waraino kon kuru iwanoꞌ mɨrɨ Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 19:14" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 19:15" />Temiyatʉ tʉrʉ tʉpo toꞌ pona, itɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ apai.<verse eid="MAT 19:15" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Imaminkeꞌ Moineriꞌpɨ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 10:17-31">Maꞌ 10:17-31</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 18:18-30">Ʉruꞌ 18:18-30</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 19:16" />Mɨrɨpan aꞌtai, kaꞌpon uyeeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ ekamaꞌposeꞌna, “Tiꞌsa, ɨꞌrɨ wakʉ kuꞌtoꞌ uya pe iyesi tɨwɨrɨ rɨ ukoꞌmantoꞌ epotoꞌ pe uya?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 19:16" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 19:17" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Ɨꞌrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ wakʉ pɨꞌ uyekamaꞌpo auya? Mɨrɨ yau iyesi mɨrɨ tikin nan nɨ wakʉ. Ukoꞌman nɨtoꞌ yaꞌ epaꞌkapai ɨwesi yau, Mosiꞌ nʉmenukaꞌpʉ ton awɨrɨ eꞌkɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 19:17" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 19:18" />Mɨrɨpan uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Nai ton?” tukaiꞌ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 19:18">Sises uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ kʉꞌwɨnɨi, iyemariꞌmasaꞌ uriꞌsan kʉsekumankai, amaꞌ pe kesii, kasi pe kaꞌpon pɨꞌ kasaurokʉi,<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">19:18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 20:13-16">Eꞌsotas 20:13-16</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 5:17-20">Isuꞌtaronomi 5:17-20</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 19:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 19:19" />ɨkʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ asan nɨrɨ inamakɨ, ɨtonpa tiꞌnʉnkaiꞌ eꞌkɨ, mɨsiꞌnʉnkayaiꞌneꞌ kasa,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">19:19 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 20:12">Eꞌsotas 20:12</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 5:16">Isuꞌtaronomi 5:16</ref>; <ref loc="LEV 19:18">Ripaitiꞌkas 19:18</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 19:19" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 19:20" />“Tanporo mɨrɨ ton kuꞌsaꞌ uya man. Ɨꞌrɨ kuru ken eꞌkuꞌsaꞌ nai?” taꞌpʉ moineriꞌpɨ uya.<verse eid="MAT 19:20" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 19:21" />Sises uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Wakʉ pe eꞌpai ɨwesi yau, itɨkɨ ɨimamin kʉrʉpoꞌpomaseꞌna, mɨrɨ tʉpo entuꞌmanin nan mʉrepaiꞌ itepeꞌpʉ pʉrata ke. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Epʉn po imaminkeꞌ pe ɨwesi mɨrɨ. Mɨrɨ kuꞌsaꞌ auya tʉpo, upɨkɨrɨ si ɨsiꞌkɨ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya. <verse eid="MAT 19:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 19:22" />Moineriꞌpɨ uya serɨ etasaꞌ aꞌtai, pokoi pe rɨ esiiꞌma itɨꞌpʉ, apʉne pʉra eke pe kuru itimamin esiꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 19:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 19:23" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uya taꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ, “Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; saꞌman pe kuru iyesi imaminkeꞌ epaꞌka poken pʉra Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 19:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 19:24" />Ekamakapʉ uya kanan; saꞌman pe pʉra rɨ kiyamerʉ epaꞌka akusa enu euta awɨrɨ, imaminkeꞌ epaꞌka Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yaꞌ entai” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 19:24" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 19:25" />Ipoitorʉ ton uya serɨ etasaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ usewansiukaꞌpʉ ipan pe. Toꞌ uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨnʉꞌ kuru ken si epikaꞌtɨ?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 19:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 19:26" />Toꞌ eneiꞌma, Sises uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Kaꞌpon pona saꞌman pe iyesi, eꞌtane Papa pona tanporo saꞌman pe pʉra iyesi,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 19:26" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 19:27" />Piꞌta uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Tanporon nɨ nɨnsaꞌ ina uya man ɨpɨkɨrɨ tʉutɨtoꞌ kon pe. Ɨꞌrɨ ken si eꞌtoꞌ oton ina iwanoꞌ pe?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 19:27" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 19:28" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; Papa uya emennaꞌ pe tanporon nɨ koneka aꞌtai, Kaꞌpon, Papa winon ereuta aꞌtai aꞌkwa tapon po, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon upɨkɨrɨ iyeꞌsaꞌ kon nɨrɨ ereutatoꞌ oton 12 kaisaron aponoꞌ po 12 kaisaron kon Esuwerʉ pon kon eseru aimenka pɨꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">19:28 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 25:31">Maꞌsiu 25:31</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:30">Ʉruꞌ 22:30</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 19:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 19:29" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tanporon kon kamoro tiwʉꞌ kon, takon kon nɨ, tʉparusi kon nɨ, tʉkʉipʉnʉ kon nɨ, tʉsan kon nɨ, tʉmunkɨ kon nɨ, tʉmainarʉ kon nɨ nɨnnin nʉꞌsan urɨ wenai uya 100 kaisa rɨꞌne iteꞌkwa epotoꞌ oton, mɨrɨpan kon uya tɨwɨrɨ rɨ ukoꞌman nɨtoꞌ epotoꞌ oton. <verse eid="MAT 19:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 19:30" />Eꞌtane tuꞌkan kon wapiyaroꞌ kon nʉꞌsan eꞌtoꞌ oton iuꞌmatʉ pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tuꞌkan kon iuꞌmatʉ pe iyeꞌsaꞌ kon nʉꞌsan eꞌtoꞌ oton wapiyaroꞌ pe,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">19:30 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 20:16">Maꞌsiu 20:16</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 13:30">Ʉruꞌ 13:30</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 19:30" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 19" />
  <chapter number="20" style="c" sid="MAT 20" />
  <para style="s1">Umɨ Yau Teꞌtʉrawasomasan Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 20:1" />“Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi non esaꞌ kasa. Awanakʉiꞌ itɨꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ anʉnseꞌna tʉmainarʉ yau teꞌtʉrawasoma ton kon. <verse eid="MAT 20:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 20:2" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, toꞌ pokon pe iyekonekaꞌpʉ toꞌ eꞌmatoꞌ pe tʉuya tikin nɨ wʉi eꞌtʉrawasoman epeꞌ pʉrata pun<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">20:2 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">pʉrata pun </char><char style="ft" closed="false">—tenariyas iteseꞌ; v. 9-10, 13 yau rɨ nɨrɨ.</char></note> ke, mɨrɨpan kon ennokoꞌpʉ iya tʉmainarʉ yaꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 20:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 20:3" />“Awanakʉiꞌ, 9 aꞌkʉraꞌ aꞌtai, itɨꞌpʉ kʉrʉpoꞌpo pɨꞌ eꞌnɨtoꞌ pataꞌseꞌ yaꞌ. Mɨrɨ yau, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ eꞌsotoꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ eneꞌpʉ iya, ɨꞌrɨ kupʉ pɨꞌ pʉra rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 20:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 20:4" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, toꞌ auroꞌkaꞌpʉ iya, ‘Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon nɨ marɨ, itɨtɨꞌ umainarʉ yaꞌ eꞌtʉrawasomaiꞌ. Ɨyeꞌma uya ꞌnokon mɨrɨ iyeꞌtoꞌ awɨrɨ rɨ,’ taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 20:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 20:5" />Mɨrɨpan kon utɨꞌpʉ umɨ yaꞌ eꞌtʉrawasomaseꞌna.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 20:5">“Non esaꞌ kanan utɨkaaꞌpʉ kʉrʉpoꞌpo pɨꞌ eꞌnɨtoꞌ pataꞌseꞌ yaꞌ 12 aꞌkʉraꞌ aꞌtai, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ 3 aꞌkʉraꞌ kanan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ anʉnseꞌna toꞌ eꞌtʉrawasomatoꞌ pe tʉmainarʉ yau. <verse eid="MAT 20:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 20:6" />Mɨrɨ tʉpo, non esaꞌ utɨꞌpʉ kʉrʉpoꞌpo pɨꞌ eꞌnɨtoꞌ pataꞌseꞌ yaꞌ koꞌmamʉ pe 5 aꞌkʉraꞌ aꞌtai. Mɨrɨ yau, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ eꞌsotoꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ eneꞌpʉ iya. Toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ iya, ‘Ɨꞌrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ ɨyeꞌsotoꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ kon teꞌtʉrawasomaiꞌ pʉra rɨ?’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 20:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 20:7" />“‘Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ ina anʉnsaꞌ pʉra iyesi,’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 20:7">“Taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, ‘Itɨtɨꞌ eꞌtʉrawasomatantɨꞌ umainarʉ yaꞌ,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 20:7" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 20:8" />“Koꞌmamʉ pe, non esaꞌ uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ epuru pɨꞌ, ‘Tʉrawaso amʉꞌ ikɨꞌmakɨ toꞌ eꞌma pa toꞌ epeꞌpʉ ke,’ taꞌpʉ iya. ‘Iuꞌmatʉ pe anʉnsaꞌ kon tʉrawaso pe meꞌmaiꞌ wapiya, iyepiyaꞌtɨ pe anʉnsaꞌ kon eꞌma pa iuꞌmatʉ pe,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">20:8 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LEV 19:13">Ripaitiꞌkas 19:13</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 24:15">Isuꞌtaronomi 24:15</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 20:8" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 20:9" />“Tʉrawaso amʉꞌ iyeꞌsaraꞌtɨsaꞌ kon eꞌtʉrawasoman pɨꞌ 5 aꞌkʉraꞌ aꞌtai uyeeꞌpʉ tʉpʉrataai kon ipun si eposeꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 20:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 20:10" />Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ wapiya iyeꞌsaraꞌtɨsaꞌ kon tʉrawaso pe uyeeꞌpʉ tepeꞌpʉ kon eposeꞌna. Toꞌ eꞌkupʉꞌpʉ eke pe parɨ pʉrata eporo tʉuyaꞌnokon tukaiꞌ, eꞌtane toꞌ uya tikin nɨ rɨ marɨ pʉrata pun eporoꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 20:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 20:11" />Pʉrata eporo tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, toꞌ entarumʉꞌpʉ non esaꞌ pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 20:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 20:12" />‘Pʉsamoro kaꞌpon amʉꞌ iyeꞌtʉrawasomasaꞌ kon akaꞌneꞌ pe rɨ eꞌmasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon, ina kaisarɨ rɨ marɨ, saꞌman pe rɨ ina eꞌtʉrawasomasaꞌ eꞌtane aꞌneꞌ rɨ wʉi yau,’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 20:12" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 20:13" />“Eꞌtane tikin nan toꞌ tonpa eikʉꞌpʉ iya, ‘Utonpa, wakʉ pe rɨ iyesi serɨ pɨꞌ eꞌtʉrawasoma rɨ, tikin nan nɨ pʉrata pun pɨꞌ, taꞌpʉ auya. <verse eid="MAT 20:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 20:14" />Ɨyepeꞌpʉ anʉnkɨ, itɨkɨ. Eꞌkupʉꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ eꞌmatoꞌ pe uya iuꞌmatʉ pe unanʉmʉꞌsan kɨnyeꞌmayaiꞌneꞌ kasa rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 20:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 20:15" />Upʉrataai ke peꞌ iꞌse eꞌtoꞌ rɨ kupʉ uya pen? Upɨꞌ rɨ katɨ ɨyɨkɨnta amʉreꞌmʉra esi pɨꞌ?’ taꞌpʉ iya,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 20:15" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 20:16" />Sises uya tʉpantomʉ iꞌmaꞌkaꞌpʉ se kasa: “Mɨrɨ kasa iuꞌmatʉ pe iyeꞌsaꞌ kon eꞌtoꞌ oton iyepiyaꞌtɨ pe; kamoro iyepiyaꞌtɨ pe iyeꞌsaꞌ kon eꞌtoꞌ oton iuꞌmatʉ pe,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">20:16 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 19:30">Maꞌsiu 19:30</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 10:31">Maꞌ 10:31</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 13:30">Ʉruꞌ 13:30</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 20:16" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Uya Kanan, “Umaꞌtatoꞌ Oton Mɨrɨ,” Taꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 20:17" />Sises utɨ koroꞌtau Surusiran pona, 12 kaisaron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton pantakaꞌpʉ iya mɨ airɨ. Taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, <verse eid="MAT 20:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 20:18" />“Surusiran pona utɨꞌnokon serɨ, Kaꞌpon, Papa winon eparankatoꞌ oton useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan enaꞌ, toꞌ uya enoꞌmatoꞌ oton imaꞌtatoꞌ yaꞌ, <verse eid="MAT 20:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 20:19" />mɨrɨpan tʉtoꞌ oton toꞌ uya Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ pen enaꞌ toꞌ uya isapematoꞌ pe, ariꞌpoꞌpɨꞌtoꞌ pe, ipokapɨꞌtoꞌ pe kurusuꞌ pona. Itosorʉwano wʉi aꞌtai, iyeꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkatoꞌ oton ukoꞌman nɨtoꞌ yaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 20:19" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Ɨnʉꞌ Kuru Eꞌtoꞌ Oton Eke Pe Uyepuru Kon Pe Sises Aꞌkɨrɨ?</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 10:35-45">Maꞌ 10:35-45</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 20:20" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sepiti munkɨ amʉꞌ san uyeeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ tʉmunkɨ amʉꞌ pokon pe, mɨrɨpan eꞌsekunkasaꞌ uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, wakʉ kuꞌtoꞌ pe iya tiwanoꞌ pe.<verse eid="MAT 20:20" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 20:21" />Sises uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ iꞌse meꞌan?” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 20:21">Mɨrɨpan eikʉꞌpʉ iya, “Pʉsamoro asaꞌron kon umunkɨ amʉꞌ ikuꞌkɨ toꞌ ereutatoꞌ pe ɨyenwoꞌnetʉ winɨ, tʉron nɨ akamisi winɨ esaꞌ wannɨ pe ɨweꞌtoꞌ yau,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 20:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 20:22" />“Iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi mekamaꞌpoyatʉiꞌneꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya toꞌ pɨꞌ. “Ɨyekotaꞌma kon poken ken peꞌ nai ekotaꞌmatoꞌ oton naꞌneꞌ kasa?” taꞌpʉ Sises uya toꞌ pɨꞌ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 20:22">“Ewaiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 20:22" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 20:23" />“Iꞌnapairɨ rɨ ɨyekotaꞌma kon urɨ ekotaꞌmatoꞌ oton kasa rɨ, eꞌtane umeruntɨrʉ pʉra man ikuꞌtoꞌ pe uya, ɨnʉꞌ ereutatoꞌ pe uyenwoꞌnetʉ winɨ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ukamisi winɨ nɨrɨ. Serɨ pata ton esi mɨrɨ kamoro ukʉipʉnʉ uya toꞌ pata pe ikonekasaꞌ naꞌneꞌ iwanoꞌ pe iyesi,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 20:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 20:24" />10 kaisaron kon uya asaꞌron kon tʉtonpa kon maimu etasaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ usakorotaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 20:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 20:25" />Sises uya tanporo toꞌ tʉkɨꞌmaiꞌ toꞌ amʉranʉkʉꞌpʉ. Taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ pen epuru ton esi toꞌ esaꞌ pe, mɨrɨpan eke ton uya tʉmeruntɨrʉ kon apurɨ toꞌ pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 20:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 20:26" />Mɨrɨ kasa ɨwesi kon pen. Eꞌtane ruꞌku, ɨnʉꞌ rɨ esi yau eke pe enapai ɨꞌkoroꞌtauꞌnokon eꞌtoꞌ pe iyesi ɨpoitorʉ kon pe,<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">20:26 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 22:25-26">Ʉruꞌ 22:25-26</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 20:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 20:27" />mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨnʉꞌ rɨ esi yau wapiyaroꞌ eꞌ pe eꞌpai, tɨwɨ nesii ɨpoitorʉ kon pe.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">20:27 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 23:11">Maꞌsiu 23:11</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 9:35">Maꞌ 9:35</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:26">Ʉruꞌ 22:26</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 20:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 20:28" />Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyeꞌsaꞌ naꞌneꞌ kasa rɨ tapiyoꞌ pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ pe pen, eꞌtane iyapiyoꞌ pe eꞌse, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉukoꞌmantoꞌ tʉseꞌna, tuꞌkan kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ epeꞌ pe,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 20:28" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tenkuꞌnaꞌ Nan Epiꞌtɨꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 10:46-52">Maꞌ 10:46-52</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 18:35-43">Ʉruꞌ 18:35-43</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 20:29" />Sises mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipoitorʉ ton uya Iseriꞌko nɨmɨ koroꞌtau, anpisin kaꞌpon amʉꞌ utɨꞌpʉ ipɨkɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 20:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 20:30" />Asaꞌron kon tenkuꞌnaꞌ nan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ereutasaꞌ esiꞌpʉ asanta kaꞌta po. Sises utɨ etasaꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, toꞌ ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨtʉꞌpʉ, “Ina epuru, Tepiꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ, ina pɨꞌ ɨsentuꞌmakɨ!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 20:30" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 20:31" />Tuꞌkan kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya toꞌ eseremekʉꞌpʉ, “Eꞌpana eꞌtɨꞌ!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, eꞌtane rɨ eke pe parɨ toꞌ ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨtʉꞌpʉ, “Ina epuru, Tepiꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ, ina pɨꞌ ɨsentuꞌmakɨ!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 20:31" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 20:32" />Sises uya toꞌ etasaꞌ aꞌtai, teꞌtakʉꞌkaiꞌ toꞌ kɨꞌmaꞌpʉ iya. Toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ iya, “Ɨꞌrɨ kupʉ uya iꞌse meꞌatʉu ɨiwanoꞌ kon pe?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 20:32" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 20:33" />Toꞌ uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ina epuru, ennin pe eꞌpai ina esi,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 20:33" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 20:34" />Sises usentuꞌmaꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ. Toꞌ enu aꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ iya. Inke pʉra rɨ, ennin pe toꞌ enaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon eꞌsaraꞌtɨꞌpʉ ipɨkɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 20:34" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 20" />
  <chapter number="21" style="c" sid="MAT 21" />
  <para style="s1">Sises Epaꞌkaꞌpʉ Surusiran Pona</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 11:1-11">Maꞌ 11:1-11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 19:28-40">Ʉruꞌ 19:28-40</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 12:12-19">Isaan 12:12-19</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 21:1" />Toꞌ uya Surusiran eporo koroꞌtau, Peꞌpake yaꞌ si toꞌ uyeꞌkaaꞌpʉ Areꞌ Wʉpʉ pon. Sises uya asaꞌron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton ennokoꞌpʉ, <verse eid="MAT 21:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 21:2" />taiꞌma toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Entantɨꞌ ɨyentauꞌnokon naꞌneꞌ eke iwa pata yaꞌ. Mɨrɨ yau, inke pʉra rɨ isaꞌkaꞌsi ewaꞌtɨsaꞌ eporo auyaꞌnokon mɨrɨ, imʉre ipiyau, mɨrɨpan kon teukaiꞌ, toꞌ mʉneꞌtʉiꞌ upiyaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 21:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 21:3" />Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ ɨꞌrɨ rɨ ta yau ɨpɨꞌnokon, ‘Itepuru esi toꞌ iꞌse,’ mʉkatʉiꞌ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai nin si, toꞌ uya toꞌ ennoko mɨrɨ inke pʉra rɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 21:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 21:4" />Serɨ si puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ awɨrɨ isetasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ utaꞌkuꞌtɨ:<verse eid="MAT 21:4" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 21:5" />“Surusiran pon kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ ekamatɨꞌ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 21:5">‘Kin, ɨiwanoꞌ kon uyeꞌnɨ pɨꞌ man,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 21:5">mɨ pe teꞌkuꞌse rɨ iyepʉ pen,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 21:5">iyepʉ isaꞌkaꞌsi mʉre po,’”<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">21:5 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Sakaraya 9:9</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 21:5">tawon.<verse eid="MAT 21:5" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 21:6" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, ipoitorʉ ton utɨꞌpʉ Sises uya taꞌpʉ awɨrɨ rɨ ikuꞌseꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 21:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 21:7" />Toꞌ uya isaꞌkaꞌsi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ imʉre neꞌkaaꞌpʉ. Toꞌ uya tʉpon kon tʉpɨtʉꞌpʉ toꞌ pona, mɨrɨpan po Sises ereutaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 21:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 21:8" />Anpisin ton kuru kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya tʉpon kon taꞌnʉkʉꞌpʉ asanta tawɨrɨ Sises utɨtoꞌ pe ipo. Tʉron kon uya yʉi panta ton aꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan taꞌnʉkʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya asanta tawɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 21:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 21:9" />Anpisin ton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ irawɨrɨ tʉutɨsan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipɨkɨrɨ teꞌsan ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨtʉꞌpʉ,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 21:9">“Usana!<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">21:9 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Usana! </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Ipuru amʉꞌ maimu, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Pikaꞌtɨꞌ! </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa iyenasaꞌ apurɨpɨꞌnɨtoꞌ yai pe; 15 airon iteꞌma yau rɨ marɨ iyesi.</char></note> Kin Tepiꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ apurɨpɨtʉ serɨ!”</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 21:9">“Poriꞌ pe kʉrɨ esi mɨrɨ Itepuru eseꞌ yau nʉyeꞌaiꞌneꞌ!”</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 21:9">“Usana kaꞌ entawon yau!”</para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 21:9">taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">21:9 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 118:25-26">Eren 118:25-26</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 21:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 21:10" />Surusiran pona Sises epaꞌkasaꞌ aꞌtai, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ eke pata pon kon eꞌtʉrʉnkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya, “Ɨnʉꞌ pʉse rɨ?” taꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 21:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 21:11" />Anpisin ton uya toꞌ maimu eikʉꞌpʉ, “Sises pʉse rɨ, puꞌkenaꞌ Nasareꞌ winon, Kiyarari pon!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 21:11" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Utɨꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ Amʉꞌ Useꞌmatoꞌ, Ɨpʉrematoꞌ Iwʉꞌ Taꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 11:15-19">Maꞌ 11:15-19</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 19:45-48">Ʉruꞌ 19:45-48</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 2:13-22">Isaan 2:13-22</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 21:12" />Sises ewomʉꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ pʉꞌkʉ taꞌ, mɨrɨ yau teꞌsan kaꞌpon amʉꞌ usennan pɨꞌ, kʉrʉpoꞌpo pɨꞌ teꞌsan enpaꞌkaꞌpʉ iya. Pʉrata ensimanin nan tepʉrʉʉi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ wakoꞌwa amʉꞌ kʉrʉpoꞌpomanin nan apon ton nɨ rawoipɨtʉꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 21:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 21:13" />Taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ, ‘Uiwʉꞌ eꞌtoꞌ oton ɨpʉreman iwʉꞌ,’ tukaiꞌ eꞌtane ‘amaꞌ amʉꞌ en pe rɨ’ mʉkuꞌatʉiꞌ!”<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">21:13 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 56:7">Aisaya 56:7</ref>; <ref loc="JER 7:11">Iseremaya 7:11</ref></char></note> taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 21:13" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 21:14" />Tenkuꞌnaꞌ nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iseꞌmesaꞌ kon uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ taꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon epiꞌtɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 21:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 21:15" />Useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan uya wakʉ kupʉ iya ensaꞌ aꞌtai, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ mʉre amʉꞌ ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨtʉ, “Usana! Kin Tepiꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ apurɨpɨtʉ serɨ!” tawon etasaꞌ aꞌtai, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru ton usakorotaꞌpʉ ipan pe mɨrɨ pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 21:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 21:16" />“Toꞌ maimu peꞌ metayan?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya Sises pɨꞌ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 21:16">“Ewaiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya. “Iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ peꞌ ene auyaꞌnokon pʉra nai:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 21:16">“‘Apurɨpɨꞌnin pe eke ton nʉꞌkwɨ</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 21:16">mʉre amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ manaꞌ pokon kon mʉre amʉꞌ kuꞌsaꞌ,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">21:16 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Eren 8:2 (LXX)</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 21:16">tawon?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 21:16" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 21:17" />Mɨrɨ tʉpo si, Sises uya toꞌ nɨmɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ Peꞌtani pona. Mɨrɨ yau, pata tʉrʉꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 21:17" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Yʉi Paꞌnʉkʉꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 11:12-14">Maꞌ 11:12-14</ref>, <ref loc="MRK 11:20-24">20-24</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 21:18" />Awanakʉiꞌ kuru, iyennaꞌpo koroꞌtau eke pata pona, iwan pe iyesiꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 21:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 21:19" />Asanta piyau tʉnaꞌsen yeꞌ, piꞌ tukaiꞌ tesaꞌsen ene tʉuya pɨꞌ, itekare pɨꞌ itɨꞌpʉ, eꞌtane ɨꞌrɨ eporoꞌpʉ iya pen nɨ ipo, iyare ton nɨken, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Tɨwɨ si tepetasen pe pʉra eꞌkɨ!” taꞌpʉ iya. Inke pʉra rɨ yʉi useketaꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 21:19" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 21:20" />Ipoitorʉ ton uya serɨ ensaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ usewansiukaꞌpʉ, toꞌ uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Nai kasa si piꞌ eꞌ useketa inke pʉra rɨ?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 21:20" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 21:21" />“Iꞌnapairon ekama uya serɨ ɨpɨꞌnokon,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya. “Apurɨtoꞌ auyaꞌnokon esi aꞌtai, tʉkasimaiꞌ pʉra, mɨrɨ piꞌ eꞌ pɨꞌ ikuꞌsaꞌ naꞌneꞌ rɨken kupʉ auyaꞌnokon pen eꞌtane, ‘Ataꞌmoꞌkakɨ tuna kaꞌ,’ ta auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai wʉꞌ pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan nɨ eꞌkupʉ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">21:21 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 17:20">Maꞌsiu 17:20</ref>; <ref loc="1CO 13:2">1 Koren 13:2</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 21:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 21:22" />Apurɨ auya pe iyesi yau, eporo auya rɨ ɨnekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ ɨwɨpʉrematoꞌ yau,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 21:22" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Ekamaꞌpopɨtʉꞌpʉ Toꞌ Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 11:27-33">Maꞌ 11:27-33</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:1-8">Ʉruꞌ 20:1-8</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 21:23" />Sises ewomʉꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ pʉꞌkʉ taꞌ. Mɨrɨ yau, toꞌ enupa pɨꞌ iyesi koroꞌtau, Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ epuru ton uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ. “Ɨꞌrɨ meruntɨrʉ winɨ serɨ ton kupʉ auya? Ɨnʉꞌ uya serɨ meruntɨ ke ɨrepaꞌpʉ?” tukaiꞌ toꞌ uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 21:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 21:24" />Sises uya entakanomaꞌpʉ, “Tikin nan pɨꞌ rɨ marɨ ɨyekamaꞌpo uya ꞌnokon nɨ nɨrɨ mɨrɨ. Umaimu eiꞌsaꞌ auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, ekama uya rɨ nɨrɨ mɨrɨ ɨpɨꞌnokon, ɨnʉꞌ uya umeruntɨrʉꞌtɨsaꞌ serɨ ton kuꞌtoꞌ pe uya tukaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 21:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 21:25" />Isaan uya paꞌtaisiman nɨtoꞌ—nai winɨ iyeꞌsaꞌ? Epʉn winɨ peꞌ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra kaꞌpon amʉꞌ winɨ katɨ?” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 21:25">Mɨrɨpan kon usaurokʉꞌpʉ tiwanoꞌ kon pe, “‘Epʉn winɨ’ ta pe iyesi yau, uyekamaꞌpo iya ꞌnokon, ‘Ɨꞌrɨ pe ken iyesi pɨꞌ Isaan apurɨ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ?’ tukaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 21:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 21:26" />Eꞌtane ‘kaꞌpon amʉꞌ winɨ’ ta yau, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya enariꞌpan, apʉne pʉra Isaan esi puꞌkenaꞌ tukaiꞌ toꞌ uya apurɨꞌpʉ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 21:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 21:27" />Sises nin si eikʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya mɨrɨ, “Ina uya iꞌtu pʉra man,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 21:27">Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, taꞌpʉ iya, “Ekamasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi ke, ekama uya nɨrɨ pen nɨ serɨ mɨrɨ meruntɨrʉ winɨ serɨ ton kupʉ uya tukaiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 21:27" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Asaꞌron Kon Imunkɨ Amʉꞌ Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 21:28" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uya taꞌpʉ, “Ɨꞌrɨ tukaiꞌ se pɨꞌ mɨsenuminkayatʉu? Kaꞌpon esiꞌpʉ asaꞌron kon imunkɨ amʉꞌ. Wapiyaroꞌ tʉmu piyaꞌ itɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya, ‘Mooi, eꞌtʉrawasomaiꞌ enta kʉreꞌ iteseꞌ kiyari eꞌkwa naꞌ,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 21:28" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 21:29" />“Eꞌtane imu uya, ‘Kane,’ tukaiꞌ imaimu eikʉꞌpʉ. Mɨrɨ ta tʉpo, teseru ensimaꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 21:29" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 21:30" />“Mɨrɨ rɨ marɨ taseꞌna ikʉipʉnʉ utɨꞌpʉ tʉmu, isakon pɨꞌ. ‘Mooi, serɨ pe eꞌtʉrawasomata kʉreꞌ kiyari eꞌkwa naꞌ,’ taꞌpʉ iya. ‘Ewaiꞌ, utɨ rɨ,’ taꞌpʉ iya, eꞌtane itɨꞌpʉ pen.<verse eid="MAT 21:30" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 21:31" />“Nai kʉrɨ rupɨ uya tʉkʉipʉnʉ eꞌtoꞌ iꞌse kupʉꞌpʉ tukaiꞌ, miꞌtuyatʉu?” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 21:31">“Wapiyaroꞌ uya kuru,” tukaiꞌ toꞌ uya imaimu eikʉꞌpʉ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 21:31">Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uya taꞌpʉ, “Iꞌnapairon ekama uya serɨ ɨpɨꞌnokon; pʉsamoro pʉrata amʉranʉꞌnin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ ɨri pe iteseru ikoꞌmansaꞌ rʉꞌsan uya Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe epotoꞌ oton arawɨrɨꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 21:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 21:32" />Wakʉ pe eꞌnɨ eseru enpoikaseꞌna Isaan uyeeꞌpʉ ɨpiyaꞌnokon eꞌtane, apurɨ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ, pʉrata amʉranʉꞌnin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ ɨri pe iteseru ikoꞌmansaꞌ kon nʉꞌpʉ uya rɨken apurɨꞌpʉ. Mɨrɨ rɨ si ene tʉpo amakooi kon apai ɨyeraꞌtɨ kon pʉra rɨ iyesi, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ apurɨ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya toꞌ pɨꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">21:32 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 3:12">Ʉruꞌ 3:12</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 7:29-30">7:29-30</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 21:32" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Tʉmainarʉ Tʉnin Ɨri Ton Enaꞌ Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 12:1-12">Maꞌ 12:1-12</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:9-19">Ʉruꞌ 20:9-19</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 21:33" />“Tʉron nɨ kanan panton etatɨꞌ: Moro non esaꞌ kaꞌpon esiꞌpʉ kiyari yeꞌ siꞌnaꞌ pe teꞌsen patamaꞌpʉ iya. Iwoi iwaꞌkʉtʉi pe iwekupiriꞌtɨꞌpʉ iya. Non akaꞌpʉ iya tʉmainarʉ yau ikasuꞌkatoꞌ yai, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipaꞌsimatoꞌ ponsiꞌkɨ kaꞌtawon sotoꞌpan ɨutɨ amɨꞌpʉ iya. Mɨrɨpan uya umɨ pɨꞌ teꞌsan enaꞌ tʉmainarʉ tʉrʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ ɨnnon pata yaꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 21:33" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 21:34" />“Kiyari akʉꞌpʉsaꞌ weyu eꞌseposaꞌ aꞌtai, tʉpoitorʉ ton ennokoꞌpʉ iya umɨ tʉrʉꞌpʉ tʉuya itenaꞌ ton piyaꞌ tiwanoꞌ oton eposeꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 21:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 21:35" />Umɨ esanon uya ipoitorʉ ton aꞌsiꞌpʉ. Tikin nan pantaꞌmaꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, tʉron nɨ wɨnɨꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, toꞌ osorʉwano wɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya tɨꞌ ke. <verse eid="MAT 21:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 21:36" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai tʉron kon nʉꞌsan tʉpoitorʉ ton ennokoꞌpʉ iya wapiyaroꞌ ennokoꞌpʉ tʉuya entai, umɨ esanon uya mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ toꞌ kupʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 21:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 21:37" />Tanporon kon uꞌmatʉ pe, tʉmu nin si ennokoꞌpʉ iya toꞌ piyaꞌ. ‘Toꞌ uya kuru umu nama mɨrɨ,’ taꞌpʉ iya, <verse eid="MAT 21:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 21:38" />eꞌtane imu ensaꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya tʉtonpa kon pɨꞌ, ‘Pʉse rɨ kuru pʉse rɨ kiyari pataꞌseꞌ anʉnton. Apʉne, iwɨpaiꞌnokon, inanʉmʉnʉ anʉntoꞌ kon pe,’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 21:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 21:39" />Mɨrɨpan tanʉnse toꞌ uya enoꞌmaꞌpʉ kiyari eꞌkwa yapai, mɨrɨpan wɨnɨꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 21:39" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 21:40" />“Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, kiyari eꞌkwa esaꞌ uyeꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, ɨꞌrɨ ken si kupʉ iya itenaꞌ tʉnonkaꞌsan pɨꞌ?” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 21:40" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 21:41" />“Toꞌ maꞌtanʉkʉ iya, kamoro ɨri ton, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉron kon nʉꞌsan enaꞌ nin si kiyari eꞌkwa tʉrʉ iya tʉrepanin nan nin si enaꞌ, umɨ winɨ tʉneporonʉ kon yapai,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 21:41" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 21:42" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ itekare yau ennin nan pen peꞌ ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon:</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 21:42">“‘Tɨꞌ, ɨutɨ amɨnin nan nenoꞌmaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 21:42">enasaꞌ itekun airon tɨꞌ pe;</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 21:42">serɨ kuꞌsaꞌ Itepuru uya,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 21:42">mɨrɨpan esi wakʉ pe kuru uyenu kon yau,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">21:42 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Eren 118:22-23</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 21:42">tawon?<verse eid="MAT 21:42" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="43" style="v" sid="MAT 21:43" />“Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe emoꞌkatoꞌ oton ɨpiyapaiꞌnokon, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ wakʉ pe epetanʉꞌnin nan enaꞌ iyeꞌtʉtoꞌ oton. <verse eid="MAT 21:43" /><verse number="44" style="v" sid="MAT 21:44" />Kʉrɨ serɨ tɨꞌ pona nʉtaꞌmoꞌkayaiꞌneꞌ utakitiꞌkwa mɨrɨ, eꞌtane kʉrɨ tɨꞌ nʉtaꞌmoꞌkayaiꞌneꞌ ipona utaꞌsiꞌkɨrɨ mɨrɨ ipʉra rɨ nin,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">21:44 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tʉron nɨ imenukasaꞌ ton yau v. 44 pʉra iyesi.</char></note><verse eid="MAT 21:44" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="45" style="v" sid="MAT 21:45" />Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ uya Sises pantomʉ toꞌkaꞌnʉꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai tʉpɨꞌnokon isaurokʉ tukaiꞌ, <verse eid="MAT 21:45" /><verse number="46" style="v" sid="MAT 21:46" />aꞌsitoꞌ ipɨkɨrɨ warinpa pɨꞌ toꞌ esiꞌpʉ, eꞌtane anpisin kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ toꞌ enariꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ, apʉne pʉra kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya apurɨ pɨꞌ puꞌkenaꞌ pe iyesi tukaiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 21:46" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 21" />
  <chapter number="22" style="c" sid="MAT 22" />
  <para style="s1">Emariꞌman Iꞌkiyari Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 14:15-24">Ʉruꞌ 14:15-24</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 22:1" />Sises uya kanan toꞌ auroꞌkakaaꞌpʉ panton yai. Taꞌpʉ iya: <verse eid="MAT 22:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 22:2" />“Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe esi kin, tʉmu emariꞌma iꞌkiyari konekanin nʉꞌpʉ kasa, <verse eid="MAT 22:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 22:3" />mɨrɨpan uya tʉpoitorʉ ton ennokoꞌpʉ tʉnkɨꞌmaꞌsan panaꞌtɨseꞌna toꞌ uyeꞌtoꞌ pe, eꞌtane ɨsiꞌpai pʉra toꞌ esiꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 22:3" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 22:4" />“Serɨ rɨken pe tʉpoitorʉ ton ennokoꞌpʉ iya, ‘Apʉne enkɨ! Tanporon nɨ ekonekakaꞌsaꞌ man. Paka amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ekaꞌnʉꞌsaꞌ ton paka munkɨ amʉꞌ wɨkaꞌsaꞌ ekonekasaꞌ man. Ɨsiꞌtɨꞌ si emariꞌman iꞌkiyari pɨꞌ entaꞌnaiꞌ!’ taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 22:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 22:5" />Eꞌtane tetaiꞌ pʉra toꞌ utɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan tikin nan utɨꞌpʉ tʉmainarʉ yaꞌ, tʉron nɨ tʉnkupʉnʉ rɨ kuꞌseꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 22:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 22:6" />Tʉron kon uya ipoitorʉ ton aꞌsiꞌpʉ, ipan pe rɨ toꞌ kotaꞌmaꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ toꞌ wɨnɨꞌpʉ rɨ toꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 22:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 22:7" />Kin usakorotaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya tʉsoisaai amʉꞌ ennokoꞌpʉ kamoro toꞌ wɨnin nʉꞌsan maꞌtanʉꞌseꞌna, toꞌ pataꞌseꞌ rɨ poꞌtɨpɨꞌseꞌna.<verse eid="MAT 22:7" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 22:8" />“Mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ, ‘Emariꞌman iꞌkiyari rɨ eꞌnonkasaꞌ man eꞌtane, kamoro unkɨꞌmaꞌsan uyeꞌtoꞌ pe pʉra rɨ kenʉꞌ iyesiꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 22:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 22:9" />Entantɨꞌ asanta kaꞌta pona rɨ, ɨneporoꞌpʉ kon nɨ mʉkɨꞌmatʉiꞌ,’ taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 22:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 22:10" />Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ ipoitorʉ ton utɨꞌpʉ asanta kaꞌta pona kaꞌpon amʉꞌ tʉneporonʉ kon nɨ amʉranʉꞌseꞌna, asaꞌrɨ rɨ, wakʉ ton, ɨri ton nɨ, mɨrɨpan emariꞌman nɨtoꞌ itau ɨutɨ epeꞌtɨꞌpʉ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ke.<verse eid="MAT 22:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 22:11" />“Eꞌtane kin uyeꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai toꞌ enseꞌna, eneꞌpʉ iya moro kaꞌpon emariꞌman pon pe pʉra ipon. <verse eid="MAT 22:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 22:12" />‘Utonpa, nai kasa ɨuyeꞌsaꞌ emariꞌman pon yau pʉra rɨ?’ tukaiꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ iya. Isauroꞌtoꞌ pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 22:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 22:13" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, kin uya taꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ, ‘Auronpɨꞌtɨꞌ, itemiyatʉ pɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iꞌta pɨꞌ enoꞌma kon pa pʉroroi pona ewarupɨ yaꞌ. Mɨrɨ yau ikarantoꞌ pe, tʉyɨ kɨtɨtɨiꞌmatoꞌ pe iya,’ taꞌpʉ kin uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">22:13 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 8:12">Maꞌsiu 8:12</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 25:30">25:30</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 13:28">Ʉruꞌ 13:28</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 22:13" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 22:14" />“Tuꞌkan kon nɨ kɨꞌma eꞌtane, tuꞌke pʉra toꞌ anʉmʉ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">22:14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2ES 8:3">2 Estʉras 8:3</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 22:14" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Esuwerʉ Amʉꞌ Uya Rɨ Peꞌ Pʉrata Nonka Pata Esaꞌ Enaꞌ?</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 12:13-17">Maꞌ 12:13-17</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:20-26">Ʉruꞌ 20:20-26</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 22:15" />Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ utɨꞌpʉ nai kasa ipoken pʉra isauroꞌtoꞌ pe ikupʉꞌnokon kaꞌseꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 22:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 22:16" />Toꞌ uya tʉpoitorʉ kon ennokoꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ. Kin pe teꞌsen, Eraꞌ pɨkɨron kon pokon pe rɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya taꞌpʉ Sises pɨꞌ, “Tiꞌsa, ina iꞌtupɨꞌ man iꞌnapairon yeꞌ pe ɨwesi tukaiꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Papa eseru pɨꞌ enupan auya iꞌnapairon awɨrɨ. Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ rɨ nensimanʉ pe pʉra ɨyeseru esi, apʉne pʉra ɨnʉꞌ pe rɨ toꞌ esi pɨꞌ teꞌnamasen pe pʉra ɨwesi. <verse eid="MAT 22:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 22:17" />Ina pɨꞌ ekamakɨ; ɨꞌrɨ ta auya se pɨꞌ; ipoken peꞌ iyesi Sisa enaꞌ pʉrata tʉtʉsen eꞌma aꞌtai, kane katɨ?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 22:17" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 22:18" />Eꞌtane, ɨri kupʉ pɨꞌ toꞌ eꞌkuꞌtoꞌ iꞌtu tʉuya ke Sises uya taꞌpʉ. “Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan, ɨꞌrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ usaꞌmapai ɨwesi kon? <verse eid="MAT 22:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 22:19" />Apʉne, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ ike enpoikatɨꞌ uyenaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya. Mɨrɨpan kon uya pata esaꞌ apon pʉrata pun<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">22:19 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">pʉrata pun </char><char style="ft" closed="false">—tenariyas iteseꞌ</char></note> neeꞌpʉ itenaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 22:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 22:20" />Mɨrɨpan uya toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Ɨnʉꞌ nai ipɨꞌ, ɨnʉꞌ eseꞌ nai ipɨꞌ?” taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 22:20" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 22:21" />“Sisa,” tukaiꞌ toꞌ uya imaimu eikʉꞌpʉ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 22:21">Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Sisa iwanoꞌ itʉtɨꞌ itenaꞌ rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Papa iwanoꞌ rɨ itʉtɨꞌ Papa enaꞌ rɨ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 22:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 22:22" />Serɨ tawon eta tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, toꞌ usewansiukaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon utɨꞌpʉ ipiyapai.<verse eid="MAT 22:22" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Eriꞌnɨ Tʉpo Eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkan Nɨtoꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 12:18-27">Maꞌ 12:18-27</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:27-40">Ʉruꞌ 20:27-40</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 22:23" />Mɨrɨ wʉi yau rɨ, Satuꞌsi amʉꞌ, eriꞌnɨ tʉpo eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkan pʉra iyesi tawon nan uyeeꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ ekamaꞌposeꞌna.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">22:23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 23:8">Inkupʉꞌpʉ 23:8</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 22:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 22:24" />Taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, “Tiꞌsa, Mosiꞌ uya tasaꞌ upɨꞌnokon, tʉumuꞌtaiꞌ pʉra kaꞌpon eriꞌsaꞌ yau, iyakon nʉꞌpʉ uya inoꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ mariꞌmatoꞌ pe iyesi imuꞌtanʉꞌtoꞌ pe tʉuya itiwanoꞌ pe.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">22:24 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 25:5">Isuꞌtaronomi 25:5</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 22:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 22:25" />Moro 7 kaisaron kon ɨsirunan esiꞌpʉ ina koroꞌtau. Wapiyaroꞌ emariꞌmaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan erikʉꞌpʉ, tʉmunkɨ ke pʉra tʉnoꞌpʉ tʉnonkaiꞌ, mɨrɨpan noꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ eꞌnonkaꞌpʉ iyakon enaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 22:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 22:26" />Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, iyakon nʉꞌpʉ erikʉꞌpʉ imʉre pʉra rɨ. Toꞌ osorʉwano esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ kasa rɨ. Tanporo 7 pe teꞌtoꞌ kon kaisa rɨ toꞌ eriꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 22:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 22:27" />Kamoro eriꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ pataꞌpʉ pe, toꞌ noꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ erikʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 22:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 22:28" />Eriꞌnɨ tʉpo, eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkan aꞌtai, ɨnʉꞌ kuru noꞌpʉ pe ken si iyesi, 7 kaisaron kon koroꞌtapai, apʉne pʉra 7 kaisaron kon uya imariꞌmasaꞌ pɨꞌ?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 22:28" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 22:29" />Sises uya toꞌ maimu eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon esi ipoken pʉra, apʉne pʉra iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ itekare mɨrɨ pe pʉra Papa meruntɨrʉ iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 22:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 22:30" />Eriꞌnɨ tʉpo eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkan aꞌtai, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ emariꞌmatoꞌ oton pen nɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra toꞌ eꞌtʉrʉ pen nɨ emariꞌman nɨtoꞌ yau; inserʉ amʉꞌ, Epʉn pon kon kasa rɨ toꞌ eꞌtoꞌ oton.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">22:30 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PRO 5:5">Ipuꞌketʉ 5:5</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 22:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 22:31" />Eꞌtane eriꞌnɨ tʉpo eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkan nɨtoꞌ ensaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pʉra peꞌ nai Papa uya ayauroꞌkaꞌpʉ kon ipɨꞌ? <verse eid="MAT 22:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 22:32" />‘Papa urɨ, Epʉraꞌan, Aisiꞌ, Sekoꞌ eꞌtoꞌ iteseꞌ ipɨꞌ,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">22:32 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Eꞌsotas 3:6</char></note> tawon. Papa, iyeriꞌsaꞌ kon eꞌtoꞌ iteseꞌ pɨꞌ pen eꞌtane nurɨnan kon,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 22:32" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 22:33" />Serɨ tawon eta tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, toꞌ usewansiukaꞌpʉ tenupatoꞌ iya ꞌnokon pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 22:33" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Eke Kuru Iyawɨrɨ Eꞌnɨtoꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 12:28-43">Maꞌ 12:28-43</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 10:25-28">Ʉruꞌ 10:25-28</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 22:34" />Sises uya Satuꞌsi amʉꞌ maimuꞌkasaꞌ tense, Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ amʉraꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 22:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 22:35" />Toꞌ tonpa, ipan pe Main iꞌtunin uya Sises ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ iꞌtupɨtʉ pe, <verse eid="MAT 22:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 22:36" />“Tiꞌsa, nai kuru esi eke pe iyawɨrɨ eꞌnɨtoꞌ pe Main, Mosiꞌ winon yau?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 22:36" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 22:37" />Sises uya eikʉꞌpʉ, “‘Papa iꞌnʉnkakɨ tanporo ɨyewan pokon pe, ayaꞌkwarʉ pokon pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨusenuminkatoꞌ pokon pe.’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">22:37 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Isuꞌtaronomi 6:5</char></note> <verse eid="MAT 22:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 22:38" />Serɨ serɨ wapiyaroꞌ, eke kuru iyawɨrɨ eꞌnɨtoꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 22:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 22:39" />Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipɨkɨron esi iwaraino rɨ marɨ: ‘Ɨtonpa iꞌnʉnkakɨ mɨsiꞌnʉnkayaiꞌneꞌ kasa,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">22:39 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Ripaitiꞌkas 19:18</char></note> tawon. <verse eid="MAT 22:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 22:40" />Serɨ si asaꞌron iyawɨrɨ eꞌnɨtoꞌ po, tanporo Main mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ esi mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">22:40 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 10:25-28">Ʉruꞌ 10:25-28</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 22:40" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Ɨnʉꞌ Pa Rʉꞌpʉ Pe Kʉrai Esi?</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 12:35-37">Maꞌ 12:35-37</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:41-44">Ʉruꞌ 20:41-44</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 22:41" />Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ amʉrasaꞌ koroꞌtau, Sises uya toꞌ ekamaꞌpopɨtʉꞌpʉ, <verse eid="MAT 22:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 22:42" />“Ɨnʉꞌ pe rɨ Kʉrai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">22:42 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya; Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe.</char></note> esi tukaiꞌ miꞌtuyatʉu? Ɨnʉꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ pe iyesi?” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 22:42">“Tepiꞌ pa rʉꞌpʉ,” tukaiꞌ toꞌ uya eikʉꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 22:42" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="43" style="v" sid="MAT 22:43" />Taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Ɨꞌrɨ pe ken iyesi pɨꞌ Tepiꞌ usaurokʉ Iyaꞌkwarʉ yau uya esakʉ, ‘Uyepuru,’ tukaiꞌ? Apʉne pʉra ta iya,<verse eid="MAT 22:43" /></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="44" style="v" sid="MAT 22:44" />“‘Itepuru uya taꞌpʉ uyepuru pɨꞌ:</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 22:44">“Uyenwoꞌnetʉ winɨ ereutakɨ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 22:44">ɨyeyaton non tʉrʉ uya pʉkʉ pona aꞌta oꞌkoiꞌ,”’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">22:44 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Eren 110:1</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 22:44">tasaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 22:44" /><verse number="45" style="v" sid="MAT 22:45" />Tepiꞌ uya, ‘Uyepuru,’ tukaiꞌ esakʉ pe iyesi yau, nai kasa nɨrɨ ipa rʉꞌpʉ pe nesiiꞌno?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 22:45" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="46" style="v" sid="MAT 22:46" />Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ imaimu entakanoma poken pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ, mɨrɨ wʉi awonsiꞌkɨ ɨnʉꞌ rɨ esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ entaꞌ ɨnekamaꞌpopɨꞌpai pʉra.<verse eid="MAT 22:46" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 22" />
  <chapter number="23" style="c" sid="MAT 23" />
  <para style="s1">Panaman Main Pɨꞌ Enupanin Nan Pɨꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 12:38-39">Maꞌ 12:38-39</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 11:43">Ʉruꞌ 11:43</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 11:46">46</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:45-46">20:45-46</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 23:1" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uya taꞌpʉ iyamʉrasaꞌ kon pɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ: <verse eid="MAT 23:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 23:2" />“Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ esi mɨrɨ Mosiꞌ pataꞌpʉ akan pe. <verse eid="MAT 23:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 23:3" />Toꞌ maimu awɨrɨ meꞌtʉiꞌ, ɨꞌrɨ rɨ tasaꞌ toꞌ uya naꞌneꞌ ɨpɨꞌnokon mʉkuꞌtʉiꞌ, eꞌtane toꞌ nʉkupʉnʉ kʉꞌkuꞌtʉu, apʉne pʉra tʉusauroꞌtoꞌ kon kuꞌnin nan pen kamoro. <verse eid="MAT 23:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 23:4" />Kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ekamaꞌpo toꞌ uya itekare kuꞌtoꞌ pe toꞌ uya saꞌman pe rɨ teꞌsen, eꞌtane ɨꞌrɨ rɨ kupʉ toꞌ uya pʉra rɨ iyesi tʉnauroꞌkapʉ kon pikaꞌtɨnin pe.<verse eid="MAT 23:4" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 23:5" />“Tanporon nɨ toꞌ nʉkupʉꞌpʉ pe naꞌneꞌ esi mɨrɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya tentoꞌ kon ipɨꞌ pe: tʉwɨpʉrematoꞌ kon yen konepɨtʉ toꞌ uya eke ton pe ikaꞌta, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉpon kon sousowʉ pe teꞌsen kanan ɨnkapɨtʉ toꞌ uya kusan ton pe.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:5 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 6:8">Isuꞌtaronomi 6:8</ref>; <ref loc="NUM 15:38">Nonpa 15:38</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 6:1">Maꞌsiu 6:1</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 23:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 23:6" />Eke ton ereutatoꞌ pataꞌseꞌ yau kuru ereutapaino kon entaꞌnan aꞌtaiꞌne mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ usenupatoꞌ iwʉꞌ tau. <verse eid="MAT 23:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 23:7" />Anpisin kaꞌpon amʉꞌ kʉrʉpoꞌpo pataꞌseꞌ iyawon kon uya, ‘Miyarɨ,’ ta iꞌse teꞌsan tʉnama kon pe, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya, ‘Rapai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">23:7 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Rapai, Tiꞌsa </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe </char></note>,’ ta iꞌse kuru toꞌ esi tʉpɨꞌnokon.<verse eid="MAT 23:7" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 23:8" />“Eꞌtane ɨusesaꞌtoꞌ kon pʉra iyesi ‘Tiꞌsa’ tukaiꞌ, apʉne pʉra tikin nan nɨ esi ɨyepuru kon pe, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨsitonpa pe rɨ nin ɨwesi kon. <verse eid="MAT 23:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 23:9" />Mɨrɨpan ɨnʉꞌ rɨ kʉsesaꞌtʉu, ‘Ukʉipʉnʉ,’ tukaiꞌ serɨ non po, apʉne pʉra tikin nan nɨ ɨkʉipʉnʉ kon esi, Epʉn pon. <verse eid="MAT 23:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 23:10" />Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ esaꞌtoꞌ pʉra rɨ iyesi, ‘Tiꞌsa,’ tukaiꞌ, apʉne pʉra tikin nan nɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Tiꞌsa; Kʉrai.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">23:10 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya; Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe.</char></note> <verse eid="MAT 23:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 23:11" />Eke pe naꞌneꞌ ɨꞌkoroꞌtauꞌnokon esi mɨrɨ ayapiyoꞌ kon pe rɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 20:26-27">Maꞌsiu 20:26-27</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 9:35">Maꞌ 9:35</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 10:43-44">10:43-44</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:26">Ʉruꞌ 22:26</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 23:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 23:12" />Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ eke pe teꞌkuꞌsen ena mɨrɨ se pe rɨ; mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ se pe rɨ teꞌkuꞌsen ena mɨrɨ eke pe,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 14:11">Ʉruꞌ 14:11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 18:14">18:14</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 23:12" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Uya 7 Kaisaron Ɨsɨ Ton Ekamaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 12:40">Maꞌ 12:40</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 11:39-42">Ʉruꞌ 11:39-42</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 11:44">44</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 11:52">52</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:47">20:47</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 23:13" />“Ɨsɨ sɨ, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan! Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yaꞌ rɨ ɨtɨpaino kon waꞌkʉꞌsaꞌ auyaꞌnokon man. Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon pe rɨ epaꞌkapai pʉra ɨwesi kon, mɨrɨ pe pʉra epaꞌkapai naꞌneꞌ nan epaꞌkatoꞌ pe ikupʉ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi.<verse eid="MAT 23:13" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 23:14" />“Ɨsɨ sɨ, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan! Itaanꞌpʉ iyeriꞌsaꞌ kon nʉꞌsan iwʉꞌ maꞌtanʉkʉ auyaꞌnokon, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨwɨpʉrema kon kusan pe, ‘Wakʉ ton,’ tatoꞌ pe ɨpɨꞌnokon. Mɨrɨ wenai, ipan pe rɨ Papa uya ɨkotaꞌmatoꞌ oton kon.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">23:14 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tʉron nɨ imenukasaꞌ ton yau v. 14 pʉra iyesi.</char></note><verse eid="MAT 23:14" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 23:15" />“Ɨsɨ sɨ, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan! Siya rɨ tʉutɨsan ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon non poro, parau kau rɨ, tikin nan nɨ konekaiꞌ. Ɨtonpa pe ikonekasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, ikupʉ auyaꞌnokon asaꞌ iteꞌkwa iyeꞌtoꞌ airɨ akasaꞌnokon, iyeriꞌsaꞌ kon utɨtoꞌ yaꞌ ekotaꞌmaiꞌ itɨtoꞌ pe.<verse eid="MAT 23:15" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 23:16" />“Ɨsɨ sɨ, tenkuꞌne esiiꞌma kaꞌpon esanon! Ta auyaꞌnokon, ‘Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ usauroꞌsaꞌ yau, ikuꞌtoꞌ pe uya tukaiꞌ Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ, ɨpʉreman nɨtoꞌ iwʉꞌ tesaꞌpɨꞌse uya ikuꞌtoꞌ kuru pe pʉra rɨ iyesi, eꞌtane ɨnʉꞌ rɨ usauroꞌsaꞌ pe iyesi yau, ikuꞌtoꞌ pe tʉuya tukaiꞌ, korʉ tesaꞌpɨꞌse Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ, ɨpʉreman nɨtoꞌ iwʉꞌ tawon uya kuru nin si ikuꞌtoꞌ pe iyesi,’ ta auyaꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 23:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 23:17" />Tenu aꞌkwarʉkenaꞌ nan pen! Nai esi eke pe kuru: korʉ, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ katɨ–korʉ kuꞌnin wakʉ pe? <verse eid="MAT 23:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 23:18" />Ta auyaꞌnokon kanan, ‘Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ usauroꞌsaꞌ yau, ikuꞌtoꞌ pe uya tukaiꞌ Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ apon tesaꞌpɨꞌse uya ikuꞌtoꞌ pe kuru pʉra rɨ iyesi, eꞌtane ɨnʉꞌ rɨ usauroꞌsaꞌ pe iyesi yau, ikuꞌtoꞌ pe tʉuya tukaiꞌ tʉntʉrʉnʉ Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ apon tesaꞌpɨꞌse ikupʉ uya tukaiꞌ, tʉusaurokʉꞌpʉ kuꞌtoꞌ iya pe kuru rɨ iyesi,’ ta auyaꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 23:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 23:19" />Itenu pʉnon! Nai esi eke pe kuru: tʉtʉsen, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ apon katɨ–tʉtʉsen kuꞌnin wakʉ pe? <verse eid="MAT 23:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 23:20" />Mɨrɨ wenai, tʉusauroꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ kupʉ iya pe iyesi Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ apon tesaꞌpɨꞌse, mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ iyesi ta tʉuya pe iyesi yau, tʉusauroꞌsaꞌ ikuꞌtoꞌ pe uya ta tʉuya aꞌtai, tanporon nɨ Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ apon tesaꞌpɨꞌse. <verse eid="MAT 23:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 23:21" />Kʉrɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ tesaꞌpɨꞌse ikupʉ uya tukaiꞌ, Papa, itau naꞌneꞌ eseꞌ yau isauroꞌsaꞌ naꞌneꞌ, Papa uya wakʉ nonkatoꞌ tʉmunkɨ amʉꞌ pona iwʉꞌ, mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ iyesi tʉusauroꞌsaꞌ kupʉ iya pe iyesi yau, Papa eseꞌ tesaꞌpɨꞌse Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ, ɨpʉreman nɨtoꞌ iwʉꞌ tawon. <verse eid="MAT 23:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 23:22" />Kʉrɨ Epʉn tesaꞌpɨꞌse ikuꞌtoꞌ pe uya tukaiꞌ tʉusauroꞌsen, usaurokʉ mɨrɨ Papa apon tesaꞌpɨꞌse mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipo teꞌsen.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:22 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 66:1">Aisaya 66:1</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 5:34">Maꞌsiu 5:34</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 23:22" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 23:23" />“Ɨsɨ sɨ, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan! 1/10 eꞌtoꞌ airɨ kiyari kɨꞌnʉnpanin—min, tirʉ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kumin tatoꞌ tʉnin. Eꞌtane eke ton pe kuru teꞌsen Main yau—ɨsiꞌkaisa rɨ kaꞌpon kuꞌtoꞌ, ɨsentuꞌkeꞌ pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ usauroꞌnɨꞌpʉ awɨrɨ eꞌnɨtoꞌ. Emen iwa pe naꞌneꞌ kupʉ pɨꞌ ɨwesiꞌpʉ kon nesiiꞌno, iwapiyaroꞌ tenoꞌmaiꞌ pʉra.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LEV 27:30">Ripaitiꞌkas 27:30</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 23:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 23:24" />Tenkuꞌne esiiꞌma kaꞌpon esanon! Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon esi weruwe eisikaiꞌma ɨuku kon apai, ɨikʉn kon eke rɨ kiyamerʉ tatoꞌ enkoꞌmaiꞌma.<verse eid="MAT 23:24" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 23:25" />“Ɨsɨ sɨ, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan! Iyaꞌpoi pɨꞌ aꞌsawʉ kon, aparapii kon korʉka auyaꞌnokon, eꞌtane eke pe rɨ iyau mentai eꞌnɨtoꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ amʉreꞌ pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ esi. <verse eid="MAT 23:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 23:26" />Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon tenkuꞌnaꞌ nan, Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ! Wapiya kuru iyau aꞌsawʉ kon, aparapii kon ikorʉkakaꞌtɨꞌ. Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, iyaꞌpoi esi mɨrɨ wakʉ pe rɨ nɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 23:26" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 23:27" />“Ɨsɨ sɨ, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan! Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon esi aimuꞌne ikorʉkasaꞌ tɨꞌ akasaꞌ uruwaiꞌ pe kasa, wakʉ pe tʉusensen kɨpoꞌpo, eꞌtane eke pe rɨ iyeriꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ kon ɨꞌpʉ rʉꞌsan esi iyau, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ɨri ton nɨ esi.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:27 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 23:3">Inkupʉꞌpʉ 23:3</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 23:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 23:28" />Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ, ɨusene kon ipokenaꞌ pe tʉron kon pona, eꞌtane ɨyewan kon yau makoi pe ɨwesi kon wakʉ pe ɨyeꞌkupʉ kon.<verse eid="MAT 23:28" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 23:29" />“Ɨsɨ sɨ, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan! Puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ uruwasii oton tɨꞌ akapɨtʉꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ipokenaꞌ ton uruwasii ipʉrʉꞌtɨpɨtʉ auyaꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 23:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 23:30" />‘Pena ina tamokori ton aꞌtai, ina ukoꞌmamʉ pe iyesi yau, toꞌ pikaꞌtɨꞌpʉ nesiiꞌno pen nɨ puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ tʉꞌka pɨꞌ,’ ta auyaꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 23:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 23:31" />Eꞌtane ɨiwanoꞌ kon pe ɨusekama kon kamoro puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ tʉꞌkanin nʉꞌsan payan nʉꞌsan pe. <verse eid="MAT 23:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 23:32" />Ikuꞌtɨꞌ rɨ si atamokori kon amʉꞌ nʉsaraꞌtɨꞌpʉ, Papa uya ɨkotaꞌmatoꞌ kon pe iwenai!” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 23:32" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Papa Uya Makoi Epuru Ton Kotaꞌma</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 23:33" />Sises uya kanan taꞌpʉ, “Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon, ɨkʉi amʉꞌ kasa teꞌsan, ayainʉmʉ kon peꞌ Papa uya ɨkotaꞌmatoꞌ kon taꞌmu kenan pen nɨ ekotaꞌman nɨtoꞌ yapai?<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:33 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 3:7">Maꞌsiu 3:7</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 12:34">12:34</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:7">Ʉruꞌ 3:7</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 23:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 23:34" />Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, ɨꞌkoroꞌtaꞌnokon puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ, taꞌkwarʉkenaꞌ nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tiꞌsa amʉꞌ ennoko uya toꞌ tonpa ton tʉꞌkatoꞌ auyaꞌnokon oton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉron kon pokapɨꞌtoꞌ auyaꞌnokon oton kurusuꞌ pona mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉron kon nɨ ariꞌpoꞌpɨꞌtoꞌ auyaꞌnokon oton ɨusenupatoꞌ kon iwʉꞌ tau, mɨrɨpan kon nɨ eꞌmaꞌpʉkapɨꞌtoꞌ auyaꞌnokon oton tʉron nɨ pata yapaiꞌne tʉron nɨ pata yaꞌne. <verse eid="MAT 23:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 23:35" />Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon pona serɨ eꞌmoronkatoꞌ oton ipokenaꞌ ton mʉnʉ ennoꞌsaꞌ auyaꞌnokon wenai serɨ non po, ipokenaꞌ Eperʉ mʉnʉ awonsiꞌkɨ, Sakaraya, Pereꞌkaya mu pe teꞌsen mʉnʉ pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ, ɨnwɨnɨꞌpʉ kon ɨpʉreman nɨtoꞌ iwʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ apon kaꞌsanau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:35 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 4:8">Iseneses 4:8</ref>; <ref loc="2CH 24:20-21">2 Kʉronoꞌkʉrʉs 24:20-21</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 23:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 23:36" />Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; tanporo serɨ eꞌmoronka mɨrɨ serɨ aꞌtaino kon pona,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 23:36" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 23:37" />“Aiko sɨ! Surusiran pon kon, Surusiran pon kon! Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ tʉꞌkanin nʉꞌsan, tɨꞌ ke ɨpiyaꞌnokon ennoꞌsaꞌ kon wɨpɨꞌnin nʉꞌsan. Inke rɨ ɨmunkɨ amʉꞌ amʉranʉkʉ iꞌse esiꞌpʉ, kɨrɨtɨkɨ uya tʉmunkɨ amʉꞌ amʉranʉkʉ kasa tapiri oꞌkoiꞌ, eꞌtane mɨrɨ kupʉ uya iꞌse pʉra ɨwesiꞌpʉ kon. <verse eid="MAT 23:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 23:38" />Entɨꞌ si! Ɨiwʉꞌ kon eꞌnonkasaꞌ ɨyenaꞌnokon iyarʉ pʉra!<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:38 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JER 22:5">Iseremaya 22:5</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 23:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 23:39" />Apʉne pʉra ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; uyentoꞌ auyaꞌnokon oton pen nɨ kanan serɨ entaꞌ, ‘Poriꞌ pe rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ nʉyeꞌaiꞌneꞌ Itepuru eseꞌ yau esi,’<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">23:39 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 118:26">Eren 118:26</ref></char></note> ta auyaꞌnokon pʉꞌkʉ pona,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 23:39" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 23" />
  <chapter number="24" style="c" sid="MAT 24" />
  <para style="s1">Pata Weyu Uꞌmatʉ Iꞌtutoꞌ Ipɨꞌ Ton</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 24:1" />Sises utɨ esiꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ iwʉꞌ tawonsiꞌkɨ, ipoitorʉ ton iyaꞌkɨron kon uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Apʉne enkɨ, wakʉ pe rɨ amɨsaꞌ ɨutɨ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 24:1" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 24:2" />“Tanporo rɨ peꞌ serɨ ton menyatʉu? Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, tikin nɨ rɨ tɨꞌ eꞌnonkatoꞌ oton pen nɨ mɨrɨ ɨsipʉroꞌpo; tanporon nɨ utaꞌpoꞌtoꞌ oton,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 24:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 24:3" />Sises ereutasaꞌ koroꞌtau Areꞌ Wʉpʉ po, ipoitorʉ ton uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ amaꞌai ekamaꞌposeꞌna, “Ina pɨꞌ ekamaꞌ ɨꞌrɨ aꞌtai serɨ eꞌkuꞌtoꞌ oton, ɨꞌrɨ eꞌtoꞌ oton ɨuyepʉ entoꞌ ipɨꞌ pe, pata weyu uꞌmatʉ ekamanin pe?” tukaiꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:3 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2ES 4:51-5:19">2 Estʉras 4:51–5:19</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 24:3" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 24:4" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Tenu ke eꞌtɨꞌ ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ ɨyenkuꞌtɨ kon namaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 24:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 24:5" />Apʉne pʉra tuꞌkan kon nɨ uyeꞌtoꞌ oton uyeseꞌ yau, ‘Kʉrai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">24:5 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya; Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe; v. 23 yau nɨrɨ.</char></note> urɨ,’ tukaiꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya tuꞌkan kon nɨ enkuꞌtɨtoꞌ oton. <verse eid="MAT 24:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 24:6" />Ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon uya etatoꞌ oton tʉusewaꞌnomasan, usewaꞌnoman man tawon nɨ, eꞌtane serɨ ton pɨꞌ rɨ ketʉipɨꞌtʉu. Serɨ waraiꞌnan nɨ eꞌkuꞌtoꞌ pe iyesi, eꞌtane apʉne rɨ pata weyu uꞌmaꞌtoꞌ uyeꞌtane rɨ iyesi. <verse eid="MAT 24:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 24:7" />Tʉpataron kon uya tʉpataron kon nɨ nɨrɨ ewaꞌnomatoꞌ oton, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ esaꞌ wannɨ pe teꞌsan esaꞌ wannɨ pe teꞌsan nɨ nɨrɨ ewaꞌnomatoꞌ oton. Iwankan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉrʉꞌpʉnʉ eꞌtoꞌ oton pata ton yauꞌne.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:7 </char><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Estʉras 13:31</char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 24:8" />Tanporo serɨ ton esi mɨrɨ eꞌtinkan entun nɨtoꞌ pe kasa.<verse eid="MAT 24:8" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 24:9" />“Mɨrɨ aꞌtai ɨtʉtoꞌ oton kon ɨkotaꞌmatoꞌ kon pe mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ umaꞌtan nɨtoꞌ yaꞌ. Tanporo tʉpataron kon uya ɨyewarumaꞌtɨtoꞌ oton kon urɨ uriyaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:9 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 10:22">Maꞌsiu 10:22</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 24:10" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, tuꞌkan kon nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uyapurɨ pɨꞌ teꞌsan eꞌnonkatoꞌ oton, tuꞌkan kon nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya tʉtonpa kon eparankatoꞌ oton, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ toꞌ ewarumaꞌtɨtoꞌ oton. <verse eid="MAT 24:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 24:11" />Mɨrɨ yau si, tuꞌke rɨ enkuꞌtɨnin nan puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ usenpoikatoꞌ oton, mɨrɨpan kon uya tuꞌkan kon nɨ enkuꞌtɨtoꞌ oton. <verse eid="MAT 24:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 24:12" />Apʉne pʉra eke pe rɨ ɨri epamʉ uriyaꞌ, tuꞌkan kon nɨ usiꞌnʉnkatoꞌ eꞌnɨꞌpantoꞌ oton. <verse eid="MAT 24:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 24:13" />Eꞌtane kʉrɨ rɨ panaꞌ pe teꞌsen tʉnapurɨnʉ yau iuꞌmatʉ pʉꞌkʉ pona, kʉrɨ rɨ si epikaꞌtɨtoꞌ oton.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:13 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 10:22">Maꞌsiu 10:22</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 24:14" />Serɨ Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe ekareei usekamatoꞌ oton pata emʉꞌ kaisa rɨ, ennin nʉꞌsan uya ekama tanporo kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ, mɨrɨ aꞌtai kuru nin si, iuꞌmatʉ eꞌseporo mɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 24:14" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 24:15" />“‘Ɨri Kuru Nuirapanin Umaꞌtan Emapuꞌtɨnin’ eꞌsotoꞌkasaꞌ wakʉ pata yau ene auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai si, puꞌkenaꞌ Taniyerʉ nekamaꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ — tɨwɨ serɨ ennin nʉtoꞌkaꞌnʉkʉi —<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:15 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DAN 9:27">Taniyerʉ 9:27</ref>; <ref loc="DAN 11:31">11:31</ref>; <ref loc="DAN 12:11">12:11</ref>; <ref loc="1MA 1:54">1 Maꞌkapis 1:54</ref>; <ref loc="1MA 6:7">6:7</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 24:16" />tɨwɨ si kamoro Isutiya pon kon nainʉmʉi wʉꞌ ton ponaꞌne. <verse eid="MAT 24:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 24:17" />Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ tiwʉꞌ nakapu po teꞌsen kʉuꞌtɨnin ɨꞌrɨ rɨ anʉnseꞌna tiwʉꞌ tapai. <verse eid="MAT 24:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 24:18" />Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ tʉmainarʉ yau teꞌsen kʉꞌtɨnin tiwʉꞌ taꞌ tʉpon eposeꞌna.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 17:31">Ʉruꞌ 17:31</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 24:19" />Mɨrɨ wʉi aꞌtaiꞌne, ɨsɨ pe kuru rɨ uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ, monoꞌ pe teꞌsan pona iyeꞌtoꞌ oton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ manaꞌ pokon kon imunkɨ pona! <verse eid="MAT 24:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 24:20" />Ɨpʉrematɨꞌ ɨutɨtoꞌ kon esi namaiꞌ komiꞌ pata weyu aꞌtai, mɨrɨ pe pʉra Sapaꞌ aꞌtai. <verse eid="MAT 24:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 24:21" />Apʉne pʉra mɨrɨ aꞌtai eke rɨ usewankaman eꞌtoꞌ oton pena pata epiyaꞌtɨꞌpʉ siꞌkɨrɨ iyeꞌkuꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ kasa pʉra rɨ serɨ pʉꞌkʉ pona, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ mɨrɨ kasa iyeꞌtoꞌ oton pen nɨ kanan serɨ entaꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:21 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DAN 12:1">Taniyerʉ 12:1</ref>; <ref loc="REV 7:14">Isenpoikasaꞌ 7:14</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 24:22" />Mɨrɨ weyu uꞌtɨsaꞌ pʉra iyesi yau inke pʉra, ɨnʉꞌ neꞌnonkaiꞌno pen nɨ moro, eꞌtane kamoro, Papa nanʉmʉꞌsan pɨkɨrɨ iweyu toꞌkenaꞌmatoꞌ iya oton. <verse eid="MAT 24:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 24:23" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ ta pe iyesi yau ɨpɨꞌnokon, ‘Kʉrai man serɨ yau,’ mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ‘Mɨrɨ yau man,’ ta aꞌtai ɨpɨꞌnokon, kʉsapurɨtʉu. <verse eid="MAT 24:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 24:24" />Apʉne pʉra enkuꞌtɨnin nan kʉrai amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ enkuꞌtɨnin nan puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ usenpoikatoꞌ oton, eke ton nɨ iꞌtutoꞌ ipɨꞌ ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ eke Papa tʉrawasooi ton kuꞌtoꞌ oton toꞌ uya, Papa nanʉmʉꞌsan enkuꞌtɨnin pe—ikupʉ tʉuyaꞌnokon pe iyesi yau. <verse eid="MAT 24:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 24:25" />Entɨꞌ ayauroꞌka uya ꞌnokon serɨ ton pɨꞌ iweyu wapiya.<verse eid="MAT 24:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 24:26" />“Ɨnʉꞌ uya rɨ ta pe iyesi yau, ‘Mɨrɨ yau man, rɨmonoꞌ tau,’ ta aꞌtai, kʉtɨtʉu; mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ‘Serɨ yau man, ɨutɨ aꞌmu yau,’ ta aꞌtai, kʉsapurɨtʉu. <verse eid="MAT 24:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 24:27" />Apʉne pʉra kamiriꞌ nʉyeꞌaiꞌneꞌ wʉi enu uyepʉ winɨ nʉsenyaiꞌneꞌ wʉi enu utɨtoꞌ pona rɨ kasa, mɨrɨ kasa kuru Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyepʉ eꞌtoꞌ oton mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:27 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 17:23-24">Ʉruꞌ 17:23-24</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 24:28" />Ekeꞌ airɨ rɨ anwana amʉꞌ amʉratoꞌ oton,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:28 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 17:37">Ʉruꞌ 17:37</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 24:28" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Kʉrai Si Ennaꞌpo</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 13:24-27">Maꞌ 13:24-27</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 21:25-28">Ʉruꞌ 21:25-28</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 24:29" />“Inke pʉra rɨ, usewankaman pataꞌpʉ pe,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 24:29">“‘Wʉi enu ewarumantoꞌ oton,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 24:29">mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kapʉi eꞌweiꞌtɨtoꞌ oton pen;</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 24:29">Sirikɨ amʉꞌ utaꞌpoꞌtoꞌ oton kaꞌ apai,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 24:29">mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kaꞌ po teꞌsen ton nɨ eꞌtʉkʉukatoꞌ oton.’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">24:29 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Aisaya 13:10; Isowerʉ 2:10, 31; 3:15; Isenpoikasaꞌ 6:12</char></note> <note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:29 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EZK 32:7">Isiꞌkiyerʉ 32:7</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 34:4">Aisaya 34:4</ref>; <ref loc="REV 6:13">Isenpoikasaꞌ 6:13</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 24:29" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 24:30" />“Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyepʉ iꞌtutoꞌ ipɨꞌ usenpoikatoꞌ oton kaꞌ yau, mɨrɨpan tanporon kon non pon kon ukarantoꞌ oton tʉutaꞌkwarʉkaiꞌ. Toꞌ uya Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyepʉ kapuruꞌ po, kaꞌ yau entoꞌ oton, tʉmeruntɨrʉ ke mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ eke aꞌkwa yau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:30 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DAN 7:13">Taniyerʉ 7:13</ref>; <ref loc="ZEC 12:10-14">Sakaraya 12:10-14</ref>; <ref loc="REV 1:7">Isenpoikasaꞌ 1:7</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 24:31" />Mɨrɨpan uya tinserʉʉi ton ennoꞌtoꞌ oton eke wai tʉronpiꞌ turunpa pe, mɨrɨpan kon uya mɨ aꞌsetun uyeꞌtoꞌ yawɨron kon nɨ inanʉmʉꞌsan amʉranʉꞌtoꞌ oton, kaꞌ pʉꞌkʉ awɨron kon nɨ.<verse eid="MAT 24:31" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 24:32" />“Ɨsenupatɨꞌ serɨ piꞌ eꞌ pɨꞌ: Emennaꞌ pe ipanta ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyare aꞌta aꞌtai, iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon wʉi uyeꞌkapʉ aꞌko pe tukaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 24:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 24:33" />Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ tanporo serɨ ton eꞌkupʉ ene auyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon aꞌko pe iyesi, mʉraꞌta nau rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 24:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 24:34" />Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, serɨ aꞌtaino kon kuru rɨ pʉra iyenatoꞌ oton pen nɨ tanporo serɨ ton eꞌkupʉ pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 24:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 24:35" />Epʉn mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ non pʉra iyenatoꞌ oton, eꞌtane umaimu mɨrɨ tereuta ton pen nɨ.<verse eid="MAT 24:35" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Ɨnʉꞌ Uya Mɨrɨ Wʉi Iꞌtu Pʉra Iyesi</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 13:32-37">Maꞌ 13:32-37</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 17:26-30">Ʉruꞌ 17:26-30</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 17:34-36">17:34-36</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 24:36" />“Ɨnʉꞌ uya mɨrɨ wʉi mɨrɨ pe pʉra iwekusi iꞌtu pʉra rɨ iyesi; inserʉ amʉꞌ Epʉn pon kon uya rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra imu uya rɨ<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">24:36 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tʉron nɨ imenukasaꞌ ton esi, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra imu uya rɨ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta pʉra iyesi.</char></note> eꞌtane ikʉipʉnʉ uya rɨken serɨ iꞌtu. <verse eid="MAT 24:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 24:37" />Nowa aꞌtai iyesiꞌpʉ naꞌneꞌ kasa, mɨrɨ kasa iyeꞌtoꞌ oton Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyepʉ aꞌtai.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:37 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 6:5-8">Iseneses 6:5-8</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 24:38" />Apʉne pʉra wʉi ton iꞌmʉnpʉ rawɨron yau, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ esiꞌpʉ utaꞌreꞌtɨn pɨꞌ, emariꞌman pɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ eꞌtʉrʉn pɨꞌ emariꞌman nɨtoꞌ yau, Nowa ewomʉ aꞌ yaꞌ weyu pona rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 24:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 24:39" />Ɨꞌrɨ rɨ teꞌkuꞌton iꞌtu toꞌ uya pʉra rɨ iyesiꞌpʉ iꞌmʉnpʉ uyepʉ pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ, mɨrɨpan kon arɨꞌpʉ iya tanporo rɨ. Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ iyeꞌtoꞌ oton, Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyepʉ aꞌtai.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:39 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 7:6-24">Iseneses 7:6-24</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 24:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 24:40" />Asaꞌron kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ eꞌtoꞌ oton umɨ yau; tikin nɨ itanʉntoꞌ oton, isakon eꞌnɨntoꞌ oton. <verse eid="MAT 24:40" /><verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 24:41" />Asaꞌron kon uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ eꞌtoꞌ oton aꞌnaiꞌ eꞌpa pɨꞌ; tikin nɨ itanʉntoꞌ oton, isakon eꞌnɨntoꞌ oton.<verse eid="MAT 24:41" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 24:42" />“Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, eneiꞌma eꞌtɨꞌ, apʉne pʉra iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon kasa pʉra ɨꞌrɨ aꞌtai ɨyepuru kon uyepʉ tukaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 24:42" /><verse number="43" style="v" sid="MAT 24:43" />Eꞌtane se itoꞌkaꞌnʉꞌtɨꞌ: Ɨutɨ esaꞌ uya mɨrɨ aꞌtai kuru ewarupɨ nau amaꞌ uyepʉ tukaiꞌ iꞌtusaꞌ yau, tenu ke iyesiꞌpʉ nesiiꞌno, mɨrɨpan tiwʉꞌ taꞌ ewon nɨ kuuꞌpʉ iya nesiiꞌno pen. <verse eid="MAT 24:43" /><verse number="44" style="v" sid="MAT 24:44" />Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon kanan tekonekaiꞌ meꞌtʉiꞌ, apʉne pʉra Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyeꞌtoꞌ oton itenupɨkɨrɨ pʉra rɨ ɨweꞌtaneꞌnokon,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">24:44 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 12:39-40">Ʉruꞌ 12:39-40</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 24:44" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Main Awɨron Mɨrɨ Pe Pʉra Main Awɨron Pen Ipoitorʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 12:41-48">Ʉruꞌ 12:41-48</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="45" style="v" sid="MAT 24:45" />“Ɨnʉꞌ ken usauroꞌnɨꞌpʉ awɨron mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ emiyaꞌpokenaꞌ ipoitorʉ pe nai itesaꞌ nʉnonkaꞌpʉ tiwʉꞌ tawon kon tʉpoitorʉ ton esaꞌ pe toꞌ iꞌkiyari ke toꞌ repanin pe itʉtoꞌ weyu aꞌtai? <verse eid="MAT 24:45" /><verse number="46" style="v" sid="MAT 24:46" />Wakʉ pe rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ ipoitorʉ eꞌtoꞌ oton itepuru neporonʉ ikupʉ pɨꞌ tennaꞌposaꞌ aꞌtai. <verse eid="MAT 24:46" /><verse number="47" style="v" sid="MAT 24:47" />Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; itepuru uya tanporon nɨ tapuruui esaꞌ pe ikuꞌtoꞌ oton. <verse eid="MAT 24:47" /><verse number="48" style="v" sid="MAT 24:48" />Eꞌtane si, aꞌtai pʉra kʉrɨ rɨ ipoitorʉ esi ɨri pe, mɨrɨpan uya, ‘Uyepuru ukoꞌmamʉ serɨ sunwa inke rɨ,’ ta, <verse eid="MAT 24:48" /><verse number="49" style="v" sid="MAT 24:49" />mɨrɨpan eꞌsaraꞌtɨ tʉron kon ipoitorʉ ton pantaꞌma pɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ entaꞌnan pɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ eꞌtaripan pɨꞌ teꞌtaripasan pokon pe. <verse eid="MAT 24:49" /><verse number="50" style="v" sid="MAT 24:50" />Kʉrɨ rɨ ipoitorʉ epuru uyeꞌtoꞌ oton wʉi aꞌtai itenupɨkɨrɨ iyeꞌtane pʉra, mɨrɨ aꞌkʉraꞌ iyepʉ ta tane iya pʉra rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 24:50" /><verse number="51" style="v" sid="MAT 24:51" />Mɨrɨpan uya ipɨrʉkatoꞌ oton, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ inonkatoꞌ iya oton wakʉ pe teꞌkuꞌsan pataꞌseꞌ yaꞌ. Mɨrɨ yau nin si, ipan pe ukaran nɨ pɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉyɨ ton kɨtɨtɨiꞌma pɨꞌ iyeꞌtoꞌ oton,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<verse eid="MAT 24:51" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 24" />
  <chapter number="25" style="c" sid="MAT 25" />
  <para style="s1">10 Kaisaron Kon Uriꞌsamiꞌsi Amʉꞌ Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 25:1" />Miyarɨ rɨ Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton auroꞌkaꞌpʉ. “Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, Papa eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe eꞌtoꞌ oton mɨrɨ se kasa; moine warawoꞌ emariꞌma enseꞌna 10 kaisaron kon uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ utɨꞌpʉ tʉraanꞌpuui keꞌne.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">25:1 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 12:35">Ʉruꞌ 12:35</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 25:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 25:2" />5 kaisaron kon uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ esiꞌpʉ itaꞌkwarʉ pʉra, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ 5 kaisaron kon kanan esiꞌpʉ taꞌkwarʉ ke. <verse eid="MAT 25:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 25:3" />Itaꞌkwarʉ pʉꞌ nan uya tʉraanꞌpuui kon arɨꞌpʉ, eꞌtane iparu uꞌmaꞌsaꞌ aꞌtaino arɨꞌpʉ toꞌ uya pen nɨ. <verse eid="MAT 25:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 25:4" />Eꞌtane taꞌkwarʉkenaꞌ nan uya tʉraanꞌpuui kon arɨꞌpʉ iparu uꞌmaꞌsaꞌ aꞌtaino aꞌkɨrɨ. <verse eid="MAT 25:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 25:5" />Inke rɨ toꞌ enurikʉꞌpʉ kʉrɨ rɨ temariꞌmasen uyepʉ iꞌse, mɨrɨpan kon enaꞌpʉ eꞌmoronʉꞌ pe, mɨrɨpan kon nin si eꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ mɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 25:5" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 25:6" />“Anomʉraꞌ aꞌtai nin si, kaꞌpon uya eke pe ekamaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, ‘Temariꞌmasen si uyeꞌnɨ pɨꞌ man! Entanʉꞌtɨꞌ si!’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 25:6" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 25:7" />“Kamoro si uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ usenpakaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan kon eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ tʉraanꞌpuui kon poꞌtɨseꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 25:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 25:8" />Iyaꞌkwarʉ pʉꞌ nan uya taꞌkwarʉkenaꞌ nan pɨꞌ, ‘Ina raanꞌpuui paru oton ke ina irepatɨꞌ, ina raanꞌpuui usenkʉꞌnʉꞌ nɨ pɨꞌ man,’ taꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 25:8" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 25:9" />“Eꞌtane kamoro uya, ‘Kane, eke pe pʉra rʉꞌkwɨ iparu man; ukaisarɨꞌnokon pʉra man,’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya. ‘Eꞌtane ruꞌku, siyaꞌpu taꞌ araanꞌpuui kon paru ɨneꞌmatantɨꞌ ɨiwanoꞌ kon pe,’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 25:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 25:10" />“Utɨn pɨꞌ rɨ nin si toꞌ eꞌtane tʉraanꞌpuui kon paru ennaiꞌ, temariꞌmasen uyeꞌkaaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ. Kamoro nin si iyekonekasaꞌ kon uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ ewomʉꞌpʉ mɨrɨ temariꞌmasen aꞌkɨrɨ ataꞌreꞌtɨseꞌna. Mʉraꞌta nin si utaꞌkoroꞌpʉ mɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 25:10" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 25:11" />“Emennʉꞌpʉ rɨ kamoro nin si uyeeꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya taꞌpʉ, ‘Ina epuru, mʉraꞌta aꞌkokakɨ ina iwanoꞌ pe!’ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 25:11" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 25:12" />“Eꞌtane toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ iya, ‘Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, ɨiꞌtu uya ꞌnokon pʉra man,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">25:12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 13:25">Ʉruꞌ 13:25</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 25:12" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 25:13" />“Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, eneiꞌma eꞌtɨꞌ; apʉne pʉra iweyu mɨrɨ pe pʉra iwekusi iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi pɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 25:13" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Osorʉwawon Kon Ipoitorʉ Ton Pantomʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="LUK 19:11-27">Ʉruꞌ 19:11-27</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 25:14" />“Mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kanan, kaꞌpon tʉutɨsen kasa iyeꞌtoꞌ oton, tʉpoitorʉ ton kɨꞌmanin mɨrɨpan kon enaꞌ timamin tʉnin. <verse eid="MAT 25:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 25:15" />Tikin nan enaꞌ 5 kaisa rɨ ipaikii pʉrata<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">25:15 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tikin nan paiki esi eke kuru rɨ pʉrata aꞌsinin.</char></note> tʉrʉꞌpʉ iya, tʉron nɨ enaꞌ asaꞌrɨ ipaikii tʉrʉꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan kon tonpa enaꞌ tikin nɨ ipaikii pʉrata tʉrʉꞌpʉ iya. Toꞌ repaꞌpʉ iya mɨrɨ toꞌ uya ikupʉ poken iyesi tiꞌtuiꞌ, mɨrɨpan nin si utɨꞌpʉ tʉutɨtoꞌ yaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 25:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 25:16" />Kʉrɨ rɨ si 5 kaisaron paiki pʉrata eponin nʉꞌpʉ utɨꞌpʉ inke pʉra rɨ mɨrɨ pʉrata eꞌtonpaꞌtɨtoꞌ pe itʉrawasomaseꞌna, emennʉꞌpʉ tʉpoiꞌne rɨ nin si, 5 kaisarɨ rɨ marɨ iyeꞌtonpaꞌtɨsaꞌ esiꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 25:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 25:17" />Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, asaꞌrɨ ipaikii eponin nʉꞌpʉ utɨꞌpʉ inke pʉra rɨ mɨrɨ pʉrata eꞌtonpaꞌtɨtoꞌ pe itʉrawasomaseꞌna, mɨrɨpan uya asaꞌrɨ rɨ marɨ paikii tonpaꞌtɨꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 25:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 25:18" />Eꞌtane nin si, kʉrɨ tikin nɨ paiki eponin nʉꞌpʉ utɨꞌpʉ, non akaꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan uya tepuru pʉrataai onamʉꞌpʉ iyaꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 25:18" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 25:19" />“Inke rɨ tʉukoꞌmamʉ tʉpo, toꞌ epuru ennaꞌpoꞌpʉ toꞌ piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya toꞌ pokon pe tʉpʉrataai eseru konekaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 25:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 25:20" />5 kaisa rɨ eponin nʉꞌpʉ uya 5 kaisarɨ rɨ marɨ ipona tʉneporoꞌpʉ tʉrʉꞌpʉ itenaꞌ. ‘Uyepuru, 5 kaisa rɨ ipaikii urepaꞌpʉ auya, mɨrɨpan tonpaꞌtɨsaꞌ uya man mɨrɨ rɨ tʉtʉrawasomaiꞌ, 5 kaisarɨ rɨ marɨ ipona,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 25:20" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 25:21" />“‘Wakʉ kuru rɨ kuꞌsaꞌ auya man, upoitorʉ, wakʉ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ usauroꞌnɨsaꞌ awɨron! Tuꞌkan pen nʉꞌkwɨ rɨ pɨꞌ yawɨrɨ ɨweꞌsaꞌ man. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, tuꞌkan nɨ esaꞌ pe ɨnonka uya. Ɨsiꞌkɨ upiyaꞌ poriꞌ pe eꞌtanʉꞌkɨ ɨyepuru pokon pe!’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 25:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 25:22" />“Asaꞌrɨ ipaikii pʉrata eponin nʉꞌpʉ uyeeꞌpʉ tepuru piyaꞌ, ‘Uyepuru, asaꞌrɨ ipaikii pʉrata urepataineꞌ tonpaꞌtɨsaꞌ uya man mɨrɨ rɨ tʉtʉrawasomaiꞌ, asaꞌrɨ rɨ marɨ ipaikii ipona,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 25:22" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 25:23" />“Itepuru uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, ‘Wakʉ kuru rɨ kuꞌsaꞌ auya man, upoitorʉ, wakʉ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ usauroꞌnɨsaꞌ awɨron! Tuꞌkan pen nʉꞌkwɨ rɨ pɨꞌ yawɨrɨ ɨweꞌsaꞌ man. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, tuꞌkan nɨ esaꞌ pe ɨnonka uya. Ɨsiꞌkɨ, poriꞌ pe ɨyepuru esi pokon pe eꞌtanʉꞌkɨ,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 25:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 25:24" />“Kʉrɨ rɨ si tikin nɨ pʉrata paikii eponin nʉꞌpʉ uyeeꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ tepuru pɨꞌ, ‘Uyepuru, ɨiꞌtu uya, saꞌman pe rɨ teꞌsen pe ɨwesi. Ɨnpɨmɨꞌpʉ pen nɨ anʉnnin pe ɨwesi, iteꞌ ɨntʉrʉꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ pen nɨ amʉranʉꞌnin pe ɨwesi. <verse eid="MAT 25:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 25:25" />Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ, enariꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan pɨꞌ ɨpʉrataai onanseꞌna utɨꞌpʉ non yaꞌ. Se si ɨiwanoꞌ pe teꞌsen,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 25:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 25:26" />“Mɨrɨpan pɨꞌ taꞌpʉ itepuru uya, ‘Ɨmɨrɨ, emiyaꞌneꞌ rɨ ipoitorʉ! Iꞌtu auya si unpɨmɨꞌpʉ pen nɨ anʉnnin pe esi, iteꞌ untʉrʉꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ pen nɨ amʉranʉꞌnin pe esi? <verse eid="MAT 25:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 25:27" />Upʉrataai rɨ saꞌne mʉtʉrʉiꞌno pʉrata eꞌtonpaꞌtɨtoꞌ iwʉꞌ taꞌ; ennaꞌposaꞌ aꞌtai, iyeꞌtonpaꞌtɨsaꞌ simoꞌkaiꞌno,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 25:27" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 25:28" />“‘Mɨrɨ pʉrata paikii imoꞌkatɨꞌ itenapai, mɨrɨpan itʉtɨꞌ kʉrɨ 10 kaisaron pʉrata paikii esaꞌ enaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 25:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 25:29" />Apʉne pʉra tanporon kon itesaꞌ pe naꞌneꞌ nan nɨ repa, miyarɨ ipona rɨ, mɨrɨpan esaꞌ pe iyeꞌtoꞌ oton eke pe rɨ. Ɨnʉꞌ rɨ kʉrɨ itesaꞌ pe pʉra naꞌneꞌ enapai, itenau rʉꞌkwɨ rɨ naꞌneꞌ emoꞌka mɨrɨ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">25:29 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 13:12">Maꞌsiu 13:12</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 4:25">Maꞌ 4:25</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 8:18">Ʉruꞌ 8:18</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 25:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 25:30" />Mɨrɨpan ɨri rɨ poitorʉ enoꞌma pʉroroi pona, ewarupɨ yaꞌ. Mɨrɨ yau, ukaran nɨ pɨꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉyɨ kɨtɨtɨiꞌka pɨꞌ iyeꞌtoꞌ pe,’ taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">25:30 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 8:12">Maꞌsiu 8:12</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 22:13">22:13</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 13:28">Ʉruꞌ 13:28</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 25:30" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Karimeru Amʉꞌ Mɨrɨ Awonsiꞌkɨ Kapirita Amʉꞌ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 25:31" />“Kaꞌpon, Papa winon uyepʉ aꞌtai tʉmeruntɨrʉ yau, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tinserʉʉi amʉꞌ pokon pe, iyereutatoꞌ oton tapon po.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">25:31 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 16:27">Maꞌsiu 16:27</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 19:28">19:28</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 25:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 25:32" />Tanporo rɨ tʉpataron kon amʉratoꞌ oton irau, mɨrɨpan uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ menka, karimeru amʉꞌ paꞌsimanin uya karimeru amʉꞌ menka kasa kapirita amʉꞌ piyapai. <verse eid="MAT 25:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 25:33" />Karimeru amʉꞌ tʉrʉ iya mɨrɨ tenwoꞌnetʉ winɨkʉiꞌ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kapirita amʉꞌ tʉkamisi winɨkʉiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 25:33" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 25:34" />“Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, ta iya mɨrɨ tenwoꞌnetʉ winɨ teꞌsan pɨꞌ, ‘Ɨsiꞌtɨꞌ ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon ukʉipʉnʉ nʉpʉremaꞌsan. Ananʉmʉnʉ kon anʉntɨꞌ, serɨ si ɨyesaꞌ kon pe eꞌnɨtoꞌ yau iyekonekasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ pata eꞌkaaꞌpʉ siꞌkɨrɨ rɨ, <verse eid="MAT 25:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 25:35" />apʉne pʉra iwan pe esi aꞌtai, urepaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon uiꞌkiyari ke; tunaꞌkiriꞌ ke esi aꞌtai, uwoꞌpaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon; kaꞌkʉran pe rɨ eꞌtane, ukɨꞌmaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon ɨiwʉꞌ kon taꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 25:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 25:36" />Ipon pʉra esi aꞌtai, urepaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon upon ke; takuruꞌke esi aꞌtai, umainanpa pɨꞌ ɨwesiꞌpʉ kon; parikiꞌsi tau esi aꞌtai, ukaꞌkʉranpaseꞌna ɨutɨꞌpʉ kon,’ tatoꞌ iya oton.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">25:36 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="SIR 7:32-36">Sairaꞌ 7:32-36</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 25:36" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 25:37" />“Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, ipokenaꞌ ton uya ta mɨrɨ ipɨꞌ, ‘Uyepuru, ɨꞌrɨ aꞌtai si iwan pe ina uya ɨyeneꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan ina uya ɨyewekʉꞌpʉ; mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tunaꞌkiriꞌ ke, mɨrɨpan oꞌpaꞌpʉ ina uya? <verse eid="MAT 25:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 25:38" />Ɨꞌrɨ aꞌtai kaꞌkʉran pe ina uya ɨyeneꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan ɨkɨꞌmaꞌpʉ ina uya tiwʉꞌ kon taꞌ? Ɨꞌrɨ aꞌtai ipon pʉra ina uya ɨyeneꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan ɨpontɨꞌpʉ ina uya? <verse eid="MAT 25:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 25:39" />Ɨꞌrɨ aꞌtai rɨ takuruꞌke mɨrɨ pe pʉra parikiꞌsi tau ɨweꞌtane, ina utɨꞌpʉ akaꞌkʉranpaiꞌ?’ tatoꞌ oton toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 25:39" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 25:40" />“Mɨrɨ aꞌtai nin si, kin uya ta mɨrɨ toꞌ pɨꞌ, ‘Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, ɨꞌrɨ rɨ kuꞌsaꞌ auyaꞌnokon naꞌneꞌ pʉsamoro sepaꞌ nan nʉꞌkwɨ kuru utonpa ton pe teꞌsan pɨꞌ, urɨ pɨꞌ ikuꞌsaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pe iyesi,’ tatoꞌ iya oton.<verse eid="MAT 25:40" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 25:41" />“Mɨrɨ aꞌtai ta iya mɨrɨ, tʉkamisi winon kon pɨꞌ, ‘Atamatɨꞌ upiyapai, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon Papa nʉpaꞌnʉkʉꞌsan! Entantɨꞌ apoꞌ yaꞌ, Papa nʉkonekaꞌpʉ makoi mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itinserʉʉi ton iwanoꞌ pe! <verse eid="MAT 25:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 25:42" />Apʉne pʉra iwan pe eꞌtane, urepasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi uiꞌkiyari ke; tunaꞌkiriꞌ ke eꞌtane, uwoꞌpaꞌpʉ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi; <verse eid="MAT 25:42" /><verse number="43" style="v" sid="MAT 25:43" />kaꞌkʉran pe eꞌtane, ɨiwʉꞌ kon taꞌ ukɨꞌmasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi; upon iꞌse eꞌtane, upon ke urepasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi; takuruꞌke eꞌtane, umainanpasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pʉra iyesi; parikiꞌsi tau eꞌtane, ukaꞌkʉranpaiꞌ ɨutɨsaꞌ kon pʉra iyesi,’ tatoꞌ iya oton toꞌ pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 25:43" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="44" style="v" sid="MAT 25:44" />“Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, toꞌ uya rɨ marɨ eiꞌtoꞌ oton, ‘Ina epuru, ɨꞌrɨ aꞌtai rɨ si ina uya ɨyeneꞌpʉ iwan pe, tunaꞌkiriꞌ ke, mɨrɨ pe pʉra kaꞌkʉran pe, mɨrɨpan ina uya asanomasaꞌ pʉra iyesi? Ɨꞌrɨ aꞌtai rɨ si ɨpon iꞌse, takuruꞌke mɨrɨ pe pʉra parikiꞌsi tau ɨweꞌtane, ina uya ɨpikaꞌtɨsaꞌ pʉra iyesi?’ tatoꞌ oton.<verse eid="MAT 25:44" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="45" style="v" sid="MAT 25:45" />“Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, toꞌ eikʉ iya mɨrɨ, ‘Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, ɨꞌrɨ rɨ kuꞌsaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pʉra naꞌneꞌ, pʉsamoro sepaꞌ nan nʉꞌkwɨ kuru utonpa ton pe teꞌsan pɨꞌ, urɨ pɨꞌ ikuꞌsaꞌ auyaꞌnokon pe pʉra rɨ iyesi.’<verse eid="MAT 25:45" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="46" style="v" sid="MAT 25:46" />“Mɨrɨpan kon utɨtoꞌ oton tɨwɨrɨ rɨ ekotaꞌman nɨtoꞌ yaꞌ, eꞌtane ipokenaꞌ ton pe iyeꞌsaꞌ kon utɨtoꞌ oton tɨwɨrɨ rɨ ukoꞌman nɨtoꞌ yaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Sises uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">25:46 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DAN 12:2">Taniyerʉ 12:2</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 25:46" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 25" />
  <chapter number="26" style="c" sid="MAT 26" />
  <para style="s1">Toꞌ Eꞌkamaꞌpʉ Sises Aꞌsi Pɨꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 14:1-2">Maꞌ 14:1-2</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:1-2">Ʉruꞌ 22:1-2</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 11:45-53">Isaan 11:45-53</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 26:1" />Tanporo si serɨ ton ekama tʉuya tʉpo, Sises uya taꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨꞌ, <verse eid="MAT 26:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 26:2" />“Miꞌtuyatʉiꞌneꞌ kasa rɨ Toꞌ Epoi Itɨꞌpʉ Weyu Rʉꞌpʉ esi awanapai rɨ emaꞌsaꞌ yau. Kaꞌpon, Papa winon tʉtoꞌ oton ipokapɨꞌtoꞌ pe kurusuꞌ pona,” taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">26:2 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 12:1-27">Eꞌsotas 12:1-27</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 26:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 26:3" />Mɨrɨ tʉpo si, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru ton amʉraꞌpʉ. Toꞌ eꞌseporoꞌpʉ Kayaꞌpas pataꞌseꞌ yau, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru eke pe kuru teꞌsen. <verse eid="MAT 26:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 26:4" />Toꞌ eꞌkamaꞌpʉ amaꞌai Sises aꞌsi pɨꞌ iwɨtoꞌ pe tʉuyaꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 26:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 26:5" />“Eꞌtane iweyu rʉꞌpʉ aꞌtai pen. Mɨrɨ kuꞌsaꞌ pe iyesi yau, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya nin urɨꞌnokon ewaꞌnoma mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 26:5" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Karapaimaꞌpʉ Peꞌtani Po</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 14:3-9">Maꞌ 14:3-9</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 12:1-8">Isaan 12:1-8</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 26:6" />Sises esi koroꞌtau Peꞌtani po, Saiman, erekʉꞌpan tukaiꞌ tiꞌtusen iwʉꞌ tau, <verse eid="MAT 26:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 26:7" />uriꞌsan uyeeꞌpʉ poꞌtoro arapasta yawon poꞌpiyun epeꞌkenaꞌ kuru rɨ esaꞌ pe, mɨrɨpan uya aꞌkokaꞌpʉ Sises iꞌpai pona imaꞌpʉ iya, tʉteireꞌ po tenaiꞌ tepʉrʉ piyau iyesi koroꞌtau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">26:7 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 7:37-38">Ʉruꞌ 7:37-38</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 26:7" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 26:8" />Ipoitorʉ ton uya serɨ ensaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ usakorotaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya, “Ɨꞌrɨtoꞌ pe imaꞌtanʉkʉ iya?” taꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 26:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 26:9" />“Serɨ poꞌpiyun kʉrʉpoꞌpomaiꞌno saꞌne epeꞌkenaꞌ pe, mɨrɨpan epeꞌpʉ tʉrʉiꞌno entuꞌmanin nan enaꞌ!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 26:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 26:10" />Sises uya toꞌ iꞌtusaꞌ esiꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Ɨꞌrɨ toꞌ pe pʉse rɨ uriꞌsan aꞌpɨꞌpɨtʉ auyaꞌnokon? Wakʉ rɨ kuꞌsaꞌ iya mɨrɨ upɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 26:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 26:11" />Tɨwɨrɨ rɨ entuꞌmanin nan esi ɨpiyauꞌnokon, eꞌtane tɨwɨrɨ rɨ urɨ esi pʉra iyesi ɨpiyauꞌnokon.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">26:11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 15:11">Isuꞌtaronomi 15:11</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 26:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 26:12" />Serɨ poꞌpiyun masaꞌ iya upona ikuꞌsaꞌ iya mɨrɨ upun koneka pe uwuꞌnaꞌtɨ eꞌma taꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 26:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 26:13" />Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon, itekare nʉsekamayaiꞌneꞌ airɨ rɨ pata emʉꞌ kaisa rɨ inkupʉꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ rɨ marɨ usekama mɨrɨ, en yau ikupʉ pe rɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:13" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Isutas Eꞌkamaꞌpʉ Sises Eparankatoꞌ Pe Tʉuya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 14:10-11">Maꞌ 14:10-11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:3-6">Ʉruꞌ 22:3-6</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 26:14" />12 kaisaron kon ipoitorʉ ton tonpa, Isutas Eskariyaꞌ tatoꞌ ipɨꞌ, utɨꞌpʉ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru piyaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 26:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 26:15" />“Ɨꞌrɨ ke uyeꞌma auyaꞌnokon ɨyenaꞌnokon itʉsaꞌ uya yau?” taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya 30 kaisa rɨ sirʉpa pʉrata pun iꞌtuꞌpʉ itiwanoꞌ pe.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">26:15 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ZEC 11:12">Sakaraya 11:12</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 26:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 26:16" />Mɨrɨ siꞌkɨrɨ Isutas esiꞌpʉ itʉtoꞌ tʉuya weyu eporo iꞌse.<verse eid="MAT 26:16" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Itepuru Entaꞌnatoꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 14:12-21">Maꞌ 14:12-21</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:7-13">Ʉruꞌ 22:7-13</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 22:21-23">21-23</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 13:21-30">Isaan 13:21-30</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 26:17" />Aꞌsarutanʉꞌsaꞌ Pen Pʉreti Pɨꞌ Entaꞌnan Weyu eꞌsaraꞌtɨ aꞌtai, Sises poitorʉ ton uyeeꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ ekamaꞌposeꞌna, “Nai yau kuru ina uya Toꞌ Epoi Itɨꞌpʉ Weyu Rʉꞌpʉ pɨꞌ ɨyentaꞌnatoꞌ koneka ina uya iꞌse meꞌan?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 26:17" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 26:18" />Toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ iya, “Entantɨꞌ eke pata Surusiran pona kaꞌpon piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan pɨꞌ, ‘Tiꞌsa uya tasaꞌ man, “Papa nʉkonekaꞌpʉ uweyu eꞌseposaꞌ man, aꞌko pe. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, urɨ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ upoitorʉ ton pokon pe Toꞌ Epoi Itɨꞌpʉ Weyu Rʉꞌpʉ kupʉ uya ɨiwʉꞌ tau,” tukaiꞌ,’ mekamatʉiꞌ ipɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 26:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 26:19" />Ipoitorʉ ton uya mɨrɨ kasa rɨ nin si Toꞌ Epoi Itɨꞌpʉ Weyu Rʉꞌpʉ pɨꞌ teꞌtoꞌ kon konekaꞌpʉ, taꞌpʉ iya naꞌneꞌ awɨrɨ rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 26:19" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 26:20" />Pata ukoꞌmansaꞌ aꞌtai, Sises esiꞌpʉ tʉteireꞌ po tenaiꞌ 12 kaisaron kon pokon pe tepʉrʉ piyau. <verse eid="MAT 26:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 26:21" />Toꞌ entaꞌna koroꞌtau, taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌnokon; ɨtonpa kon uya uyeparankatoꞌ oton,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 26:22" />Mɨrɨpan kon upokoitaꞌpʉ, toꞌ uya tʉkaisarɨꞌnokon, “Iꞌnapai rɨ, uyepuru, urɨ pen kuru rɨ nin!” taꞌpʉ Sises pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 26:22" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 26:23" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ, “Kʉrɨ tʉyu kiꞌaiꞌneꞌ pʉsau yaꞌ upokon pe uya uyeparankatoꞌ oton.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">26:23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 41:9">Eren 41:9</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 26:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 26:24" />Kaꞌpon, Papa winon utɨtoꞌ oton tʉpɨꞌ imenukasaꞌ naꞌneꞌ kasa rɨ, eꞌtane ɨsɨ yau rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ kaꞌpon esi Kaꞌpon, Papa winon eparankanin. Wakʉ pe nesiiꞌno iyentusaꞌ pʉra iyesi yau,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:24" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 26:25" />Mɨrɨpan Isutas, eparankanin oton uya nin si taꞌpʉ, “Rapai,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">26:25 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Rapai, Tiꞌsa </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe </char></note> iꞌnapai rɨ, urɨ pen kuru rɨ nin,” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 26:25">“Ewaiꞌ, ɨmɨrɨ rɨ,” tukaiꞌ Sises uya eikʉꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 26:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 26:26" />Toꞌ entaꞌna koroꞌtau rɨ, Sises uya pʉreti anʉmʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya tenki taꞌpʉ Papa pɨꞌ. Iꞌkwɨꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan ekamʉꞌpʉ iya tʉpoitorʉ ton enaꞌ, taiꞌma toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Anʉntɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan ɨꞌtɨꞌ. Serɨ serɨ upun,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:26" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 26:27" />Mɨrɨpan uya koꞌ, waain yen anʉmʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya tenki taꞌpʉ Papa pɨꞌ. Toꞌ enaꞌ itʉrʉꞌpʉ iya, taiꞌma toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Se yawon ensitɨꞌ, ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 26:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 26:28" />Serɨ serɨ emennaꞌ<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">26:28 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tʉron nɨ imenukasaꞌ ton yau “emennaꞌ pe” tasaꞌ pʉra iyesi.</char></note> ekonekan nɨtoꞌ iwanoꞌ umʉnʉ, tuꞌkan kon iwanoꞌ pe rɨ iyeꞌkwansaꞌ makoi ton pɨꞌ usentuꞌman nɨtoꞌ pe.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">26:28 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 24:8">Eꞌsotas 24:8</ref>; <ref loc="JER 31:31-34">Iseremaya 31:31-34</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 26:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 26:29" />Ekama uya serɨ entaꞌ iteperu euku ensitoꞌ uya oton pen ɨpokon pe ꞌnokon ukʉipʉnʉ eꞌtoꞌ esaꞌ wannɨ pe yau emennaꞌ pe ensi uya pʉꞌkʉ pona,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:29" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 26:30" />Eren<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">26:30 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Eren</char><char style="ft" closed="false">–iyaꞌtai pʉra “Eke Kuru Arerʉ” kuuꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, Eren 113-118.</char></note> pɨꞌ tʉuserenka kon tʉpo, toꞌ utɨꞌpʉ Areꞌ Wʉpʉ pona.<verse eid="MAT 26:30" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Piꞌta Uya Tʉnonkatoꞌ Oton Ekamaꞌpʉ Sises Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 14:27-31">Maꞌ 14:27-31</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:31-34">Ʉruꞌ 22:31-34</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 13:36-38">Isaan 13:36-38</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 26:31" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uya toꞌ panaꞌtɨꞌpʉ, “Serɨ ewarupɨɨi tau kuru, tanporo rɨ unɨmɨ auyaꞌnokon mɨrɨ, teꞌkuꞌsen upɨꞌ wenai, apʉne pʉra iyeꞌmenukasaꞌ,</para>
  <para style="q1" vid="MAT 26:31">“‘Karimeru amʉꞌ paꞌsimanin wɨnɨ uya mɨrɨ,</para>
  <para style="q2" vid="MAT 26:31">mɨrɨpan karimeru amʉꞌ eꞌtaꞌnʉꞌtoꞌ oton tamʉꞌ ke teꞌtoꞌ kon apai,’<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">26:31 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Sakaraya 13:7</char></note></para>
  <para style="m" vid="MAT 26:31">tukaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 26:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 26:32" />Eꞌtane eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkasaꞌ tʉpo, utɨ mɨrɨ arawɨrɨꞌnokon Kiyarari pona,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">26:32 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 28:16">Maꞌsiu 28:16</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 26:32" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 26:33" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Piꞌta uya, “Tanporon kon uya ɨnɨntane teꞌkuꞌsen ɨpɨꞌ wenai, urɨ uya nin ɨnonka pen mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ Sises pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 26:33" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 26:34" />Sises uya imaimu eikʉꞌpʉ, “Iꞌnapairon ekama uya ɨpɨꞌ, serɨ ewarupɨɨi tau kuru, kɨrɨtɨkɨ uturumʉ rawɨrɨ, osorʉwau iteꞌkwa unonkatoꞌ auya oton,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:34" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 26:35" />Eꞌtane rɨ Piꞌta uya, “Umaꞌtatoꞌ pe rɨ ayaꞌkɨrɨ, ɨnonka uya pen nɨ mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ. Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ itonpa ton uya taꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 26:35" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Ɨpʉremaꞌpʉ Keꞌsemani Po</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 14:32-42">Maꞌ 14:32-42</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:39-46">Ʉruꞌ 22:39-46</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 26:36" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises utɨꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe Keꞌsemani tukaiꞌ tesaꞌsen pata yaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Se airɨ ereutatɨꞌ, mɨ airɨ ɨpʉremaiꞌ utɨ tane,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 26:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 26:37" />Taꞌkɨrɨ Piꞌta mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ asaꞌrɨ Sepiti munkɨ amʉꞌ arɨꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan enaꞌpʉ pokoi pe mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ikaꞌnɨꞌ pʉra rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 26:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 26:38" />“Uyewan man ikaꞌnɨꞌ pʉra rɨ, eꞌtapeꞌneꞌ pe rɨ iyesi umaꞌtanʉkʉ iya rɨ. Serɨ yau eꞌtɨꞌ, uyaꞌkɨrɨ tenu ke eꞌtɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:38" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 26:39" />Itɨꞌpʉ miyarɨ parɨ ɨnnɨ iwa toꞌ piyapai, mɨrɨpan utaꞌmoꞌkaꞌpʉ non pona temʉꞌ po, mɨrɨpan ɨpʉremaꞌpʉ, “Ukʉipʉnʉ, iyeꞌkupʉ pe iyesi yau tɨwɨ upiyapai koꞌ nʉtamai, eꞌtane uyeseru awɨrɨ pen, eꞌtane ɨyeseru awɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:39" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 26:40" />Mɨrɨpan ennaꞌpoꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya toꞌ eꞌnʉmʉ eporoꞌpʉ. Piꞌta ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ iya, “Uyaꞌkɨrɨ peꞌ ɨmɨrɨꞌnokon warawotiꞌsi amʉꞌ esi poken pʉra iyesi tenu ke mara rʉꞌkwɨ rɨ?” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 26:40" /><verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 26:41" />“Tenu ke esiiꞌma ɨpʉrematɨꞌ, iꞌtupɨꞌnɨtoꞌ yaꞌ autaꞌmoꞌka kon namaiꞌ. Iyaꞌkwarʉ esi ɨnkuꞌpai, eꞌtane ipun esi ɨꞌsɨꞌmʉra,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:41" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 26:42" />Sises ennaꞌpokaaꞌpʉ iyakon iteꞌkwa pe ɨpʉremaseꞌna. “Ukʉipʉnʉ, iyeꞌkupʉ poken pʉra rɨ iyesi yau, serɨ koꞌ utama poken pʉra upiyapai ensi uya aꞌtai rɨken, tɨwɨ ɨyeseru neꞌkupʉi,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:42" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="43" style="v" sid="MAT 26:43" />Iyennaꞌposaꞌ aꞌtai kanan, toꞌ rɨ marɨ eꞌnʉnpɨꞌsaꞌ eporoꞌpʉ iya, apʉne pʉra eꞌtapeꞌneꞌ peꞌne toꞌ enu piꞌpɨ ton esi ke, <verse eid="MAT 26:43" /><verse number="44" style="v" sid="MAT 26:44" />mɨrɨpan kon piyapai ɨpʉremakaꞌseꞌna kanan itɨꞌpʉ itosorʉwano iteꞌkwa pe, wapiya tʉwɨpʉremaꞌpʉ kasa rɨ marɨ iyepʉremaꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 26:44" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="45" style="v" sid="MAT 26:45" />Mɨrɨpan ennaꞌpoꞌpʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Mɨrɨ si eꞌnʉn nɨ pɨꞌ rɨ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ umoronkaꞌnɨ pɨꞌ rɨ ɨwesi kon? Apʉne entɨꞌ! Iweyu eꞌseposaꞌ man! Kaꞌpon, Papa winon eparankasaꞌ man tʉmakooikenaꞌ nan enaꞌ! <verse eid="MAT 26:45" /><verse number="46" style="v" sid="MAT 26:46" />Eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkatɨꞌ! Utɨnpaiꞌnokon! Uyeparankanin si uyeꞌkaꞌnɨ pɨꞌ man!” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:46" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Aꞌsiꞌpʉ Toꞌ Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 14:43-50">Maꞌ 14:43-50</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:47-53">Ʉruꞌ 22:47-53</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 18:3-12">Isaan 18:3-12</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="47" style="v" sid="MAT 26:47" />Usauroꞌnɨ pɨꞌ rɨ marɨ iyesi koroꞌtau, Isutas, 12 kaisaron kon tonpa pe teꞌsen uyeeꞌpʉ. Ipokon pe anpisin kuru rɨ usepaiꞌtɨpɨꞌsaꞌ supara ke mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ waꞌtana ke esiꞌpʉ, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ epuru ton nennokoꞌsan. <verse eid="MAT 26:47" /><verse number="48" style="v" sid="MAT 26:48" />Eparankanin uya tʉnkuꞌton ekamasaꞌ esiꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ: “Kʉrɨ saꞌsuꞌkayaiꞌneꞌ si kʉrɨ rɨ; maꞌsitʉiꞌ,” tasaꞌ esiꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 26:48" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="49" style="v" sid="MAT 26:49" />Isutas utɨꞌpʉ Sises piyaꞌ toꞌsarɨ rɨ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Miyarɨ, Rapai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">26:49 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Rapai, Tiꞌsa </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe </char></note>!” mɨrɨpan aꞌsuꞌkaꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:49" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="50" style="v" sid="MAT 26:50" />Sises uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Utonpa, ikuꞌse ɨuyeꞌsaꞌ naꞌneꞌ rɨ ikuꞌkɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">26:50 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">“Utonpa, ikuꞌse ɨuyeꞌsaꞌ naꞌneꞌ rɨ ikuꞌkɨ,” </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">“Utonpa, ɨꞌrɨ kan ɨuyeꞌsaꞌ?”</char></note> Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ utɨꞌpʉ Sises winɨkʉiꞌ mɨrɨpan kon uya aꞌsiꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 26:50" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="51" style="v" sid="MAT 26:51" />Mɨrɨ pɨꞌ tikin nan nɨ Sises tonpa ton tonpa uya tʉsuparaai moꞌkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru poitorʉ pana aꞌtɨꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 26:51" /><verse number="52" style="v" sid="MAT 26:52" />Sises uya nin si taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Ɨsuparaai inaꞌpokaꞌkɨ si ipataꞌpʉ yaꞌ! Kamoro supara apurɨnin nʉꞌsan nɨ eriꞌtoꞌ oton esi mɨrɨ supara ke rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 26:52" /><verse number="53" style="v" sid="MAT 26:53" />Iꞌtu auyaꞌnokon pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ, ukʉipʉnʉ pɨꞌ ɨpʉrematoꞌ, mɨrɨ aꞌtai upiyaꞌ 12 kaisa rɨ iteꞌkwa anpisin ton kuru rɨ inserʉ amʉꞌ ennoꞌtoꞌ iya upikaꞌtɨnin nan pe. <verse eid="MAT 26:53" /><verse number="54" style="v" sid="MAT 26:54" />Eꞌtane mɨrɨ kuꞌsaꞌ uya pe iyesi yau, itekare uya ekamasaꞌ naꞌneꞌ utaꞌkuꞌtɨ pʉra rɨ iyesi, mɨrɨ eꞌkuꞌtoꞌ oton tasaꞌ iya naꞌneꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:54" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="55" style="v" sid="MAT 26:55" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Sises uya taꞌpʉ anpisin pɨꞌ, “Main awɨron kon pen peꞌ esaꞌ pe esi serɨ, ɨuyeꞌsaꞌ kon naꞌneꞌ supara amʉꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ waꞌtana amʉꞌ esaꞌ pe uyaꞌsiseꞌna? Wʉi kaisarɨ rɨ eꞌtai ko useꞌman nɨtoꞌ, ɨpʉreman nɨtoꞌ iwʉꞌ pʉꞌkʉ tau tereutaiꞌ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ enupa pɨꞌ, uyaꞌsi auyaꞌnokon pʉra rɨ. <verse eid="MAT 26:55" /><verse number="56" style="v" sid="MAT 26:56" />Eꞌtane tanporo rɨ serɨ eꞌkuꞌsaꞌ puꞌkenaꞌ amʉꞌ nʉmenukaꞌpʉ utaꞌkuꞌtɨtoꞌ pe,” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 26:56">Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, tanporo ipoitorʉ ton uya inonkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon ainʉmʉꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 26:56" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Esiꞌpʉ Esuwerʉ Amʉꞌ Konsʉrʉʉi Ton Piyau</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 14:53-65">Maꞌ 14:53-65</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:54-55">Ʉruꞌ 22:54-55</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 22:63-71">63-71</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 18:13-14">Isaan 18:13-14</ref>, <ref loc="JHN 18:19-24">19-24</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="57" style="v" sid="MAT 26:57" />Kamoro, Sises aꞌsinin nʉꞌsan uya arɨꞌpʉ Kayaꞌpas, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru piyaꞌ, Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru ton amʉrasaꞌ airɨ. <verse eid="MAT 26:57" /><verse number="58" style="v" sid="MAT 26:58" />Eꞌtane Piꞌta uya eꞌmaꞌpʉkaꞌpʉ ɨnnonsiꞌkɨ rɨ, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru iwʉꞌ pʉrorooi pona, mɨrɨpan ewomʉꞌpʉ, iyereutaꞌpʉ erasu ton piyaꞌ teꞌkuꞌsen enseꞌna.<verse eid="MAT 26:58" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="59" style="v" sid="MAT 26:59" />Useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tanporon kon nɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ Konsʉrʉʉi ton esiꞌpʉ kasi pe rɨ Sises eseruꞌtɨtoꞌ warinpa pɨꞌ, iyeriꞌtoꞌ yaꞌ itʉtoꞌ pe tʉuyaꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 26:59" /><verse number="60" style="v" sid="MAT 26:60" />Eꞌtane toꞌ uya ɨꞌrɨ rɨ iteseru eporoꞌpʉ pen nɨ mɨrɨ rɨ eꞌtane tuꞌke rɨ kasi yeꞌ pe tʉusauroꞌsan esiꞌpʉ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 26:60">Emennʉꞌpʉ tʉpo rɨ, asaꞌron kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uyeeꞌpʉ, <verse eid="MAT 26:60" /><verse number="61" style="v" sid="MAT 26:61" />mɨrɨpan kon uya si ekamaꞌpʉ, “Pʉse rɨ uya taꞌpʉ, ‘Papa iwanoꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ, ɨpʉreman nɨtoꞌ iwʉꞌ maꞌtanʉkʉ uya mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan konekatoꞌ pe uya kanan osorʉwau wʉi yau,’ taꞌpʉ iya,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 26:61" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="62" style="v" sid="MAT 26:62" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru eꞌsotoꞌkaꞌpʉ Sises pɨꞌ taseꞌna, “Eikʉ auya pen nɨ peꞌ mɨrɨ? Ɨꞌrɨ tukaiꞌ pʉsamoro kaꞌpon amʉꞌ usaurokʉ ɨpɨꞌ?” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 26:62" /><verse number="63" style="v" sid="MAT 26:63" />Eꞌtane Sises enkurumʉꞌpʉ eꞌpana rɨ. Useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru uya taꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ, “Ayapiyoꞌma uya serɨ Papa tʉukoꞌmansen uya eta tane iꞌnapairon pe ɨusekama pa ina pɨꞌ; Kʉrai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">26:63 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya; Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe; v. 68 yau nɨrɨ.</char></note> pe peꞌ ɨwesi, Papa Mumu pe?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:63" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="64" style="v" sid="MAT 26:64" />Sises uya imaimu eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ewaiꞌ, ta auya naꞌneꞌ kasa rɨ, eꞌtane tanporo ɨpɨꞌnokon ta uya; Serɨ entaꞌ, Kaꞌpon, Papa winon entoꞌ auyaꞌnokon oton iyereutasaꞌ Meruntɨ pe Teꞌsen enwoꞌnetʉ winɨ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iyepʉ Epʉn poi kapuruꞌ yau,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:64" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="65" style="v" sid="MAT 26:65" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru uya tʉpon karakaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ, “Papa sapema pe isaurokʉ! Ɨꞌrɨtoꞌ pe miyarɨ rɨ ekamanin nan iꞌse eꞌnɨ? Entɨꞌ, Papa sapema pe isaurokʉ etasaꞌ auyaꞌnokon. <verse eid="MAT 26:65" /><verse number="66" style="v" sid="MAT 26:66" />Ɨꞌrɨ ken tukaiꞌ mɨsenuminkayatʉu?” taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 26:66">“Imaꞌtatoꞌ pe rɨ iyesi!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 26:66" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="67" style="v" sid="MAT 26:67" />Mɨrɨpan kon etaꞌtapɨtʉꞌpʉ itemʉꞌ pona, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ toꞌ uya tʉmokorooi kon ke iwɨnɨꞌpʉ. Tʉron kon uya rɨ intaꞌmopɨtʉꞌpʉ, <verse eid="MAT 26:67" /><verse number="68" style="v" sid="MAT 26:68" />taiꞌma, “Kʉrai, puꞌkenaꞌ pe ekamakɨ ina pɨꞌ. Ɨnʉꞌ ɨwɨnɨi?” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 26:68" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Piꞌta Uya Sises Nonkaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 14:66-72">Maꞌ 14:66-72</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:56-62">Ʉruꞌ 22:56-62</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 18:15-18">Isaan 18:15-18</ref>, <ref loc="JHN 18:25-27">25-27</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="69" style="v" sid="MAT 26:69" />Piꞌta ereutasaꞌ esiꞌpʉ Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru iwʉꞌ pʉrorooi po, mɨrɨpan piyaꞌ toꞌ poitorʉ, uriꞌsan uyeeꞌpʉ. “Ɨmɨrɨ saꞌne kʉrɨ rɨ ko Sises, Kiyarari pon aꞌkɨron nʉꞌpʉ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:69" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="70" style="v" sid="MAT 26:70" />Eꞌtane iꞌtunin pe pʉra iyeꞌkuuꞌpʉ tanporo mɨrɨ yawon kon rau esiiꞌma. “Iꞌtu uya pʉra rɨ man ɨꞌrɨ pɨꞌ ausaurokʉ tukaiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 26:70" /><verse number="71" style="v" sid="MAT 26:71" />Mɨrɨpan utɨꞌpʉ pʉroroi mʉraꞌtaai pona. Mɨrɨ yau, tʉron nɨ uriꞌsan uya kanan eneꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ mɨrɨ yau teꞌsan pɨꞌ, “Pʉse rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Sises, Nasareꞌ pon aꞌkɨron nʉꞌpʉ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:71" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="72" style="v" sid="MAT 26:72" />Iꞌtunin pe pʉra kanan iyeꞌkuꞌkaaꞌpʉ, Papa kuru tesaꞌpɨꞌse: “Kʉrɨ rɨ iꞌtu uya pʉra man!” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 26:72" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="73" style="v" sid="MAT 26:73" />Mara rɨ iyesiꞌpʉ tʉpo kamoro mɨrɨ yau teꞌsotoꞌpɨꞌse teꞌsan utɨꞌpʉ Piꞌta piyaꞌ, taseꞌna ipɨꞌ, “Iꞌnapai rɨ kuru rɨ ɨmɨrɨ kʉrɨ rɨ toꞌ tonpa, ausaurokʉ eseru uya ɨyekama,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 26:73" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="74" style="v" sid="MAT 26:74" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, Piꞌta eꞌpaꞌnʉkʉꞌpʉ tiwanoꞌ pe rɨ, mɨrɨpan uya, “Tɨwɨ Papa ukotaꞌmai kasi pe usaurokʉ pɨꞌ. Kʉrɨ rɨ iꞌtu uya pʉra man!” taꞌpʉ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 26:74">Mɨrɨ ta iya aꞌtai rɨ, kɨrɨtɨkɨ uturumʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 26:74" /><verse number="75" style="v" sid="MAT 26:75" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai si, Piꞌta uya Sises maimu rʉꞌpʉ neeꞌpʉ tenu yaꞌ, “Osorʉwau iteꞌkwa, ‘Iꞌtu uya pʉra man,’ tatoꞌ auya oton, kɨrɨtɨkɨ uturumʉ rawɨrɨ!” tawon. Mɨrɨpan epaꞌkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan ukaramʉꞌpʉ ipan pe rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 26:75" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 26" />
  <chapter number="27" style="c" sid="MAT 27" />
  <para style="s1">Sises Arɨꞌpʉ Toꞌ Uya Paireꞌ Piyaꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 15:1">Maꞌ 15:1</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 23:1-2">Ʉruꞌ 23:1-2</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 18:28-32">Isaan 18:28-32</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 27:1" />Awanakʉiꞌ kuru, tanporo useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru ton ekonekaꞌpʉ Sises umaꞌtatoꞌ pe ikuꞌtoꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 27:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 27:2" />Toꞌ uya auronpɨtʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan arɨꞌpʉ toꞌ uya Paireꞌ, kopʉna enaꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 27:2" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Isutas Eꞌsaꞌmaꞌpʉ Tiwanoꞌ Pe</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="ACT 1:18-19">Inkupʉꞌpʉ 1:18-19</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 27:3" />Sises eparankanin nʉꞌpʉ, Isutas uya si ensaꞌ esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, toꞌ uya ikonekasaꞌ Sises umaꞌtatoꞌ pe, ipan pe rɨ ipokoitaꞌpʉ Sises eparankasaꞌ tʉuya pɨꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya 30 kaisaron sirʉpa pun naꞌpoꞌpʉ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru ton enaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 27:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 27:4" />“Umakoitasaꞌ man, imakooi pʉn nɨ mʉnʉ teparankaiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 27:4">“Ɨꞌrɨ pe ken si mɨrɨ uya ina kupʉ? Ɨiwanoꞌ saꞌne mɨrɨ ko!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 27:4" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 27:5" />Mɨrɨ wenai, Isutas uya pʉrata pun enoꞌmaꞌpʉ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ, ɨpʉreman nɨtoꞌ iwʉꞌ pʉꞌkʉ taꞌ, mɨrɨpan ennaꞌpoꞌpʉ tiwanoꞌ pe rɨ eꞌsaꞌmaseꞌna.<verse eid="MAT 27:5" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 27:6" />Useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton uya pʉrata pun amukuꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya taꞌpʉ, “Main, Mosiꞌ winon nɨ pʉremekʉ pe iyesi mɨrɨ inonkasaꞌ aꞌtai pʉrata yen yaꞌ, apʉne pʉra mʉn epeꞌpʉ pe iyesi ke,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 27:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 27:7" />Mɨrɨpan kon ekonekaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ pʉrata ke ɨinɨ kaꞌnin pataꞌseꞌ eꞌmatoꞌ pe tukaiꞌ. Mɨrɨ si kupʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya kaꞌkʉran amʉꞌ pe teꞌsan eriꞌsaꞌ uꞌnaꞌtɨtoꞌ yau pe. <verse eid="MAT 27:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 27:8" />Mɨrɨ wenai, kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya mɨrɨ pata esakʉ Mʉn Pataꞌseꞌ tukaiꞌ serɨ pʉꞌkʉ pona.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:8 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 1:18-19">Inkupʉꞌpʉ 1:18-19</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 27:8" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 27:9" />Mɨrɨ si puꞌkenaꞌ Iseremaya nekamaꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ pena rɨ utaꞌkuꞌtɨꞌpʉ se tawon: “Toꞌ uya si 30 kaisa rɨ sirʉpa pun anʉmʉꞌpʉ, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ nʉkupʉꞌpʉ itepeꞌ pe, <verse eid="MAT 27:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 27:10" />mɨrɨpan kon uya mɨrɨ pʉrata ke ɨinɨ kaꞌnin nan pataꞌseꞌ eꞌmaꞌpʉ, uyepuru uya uyapiyoꞌmaꞌpʉ awɨrɨ rɨ,” <note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">27:10 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Sakaraya 11:12-13</char></note> tawon.<verse eid="MAT 27:10" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Eꞌsotoꞌkaꞌpʉ Paireꞌ Piyau</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 15:2-5">Maꞌ 15:2-5</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 23:3-5">Ʉruꞌ 23:3-5</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 18:33-38">Isaan 18:33-38</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 27:11" />Mɨrɨ koroꞌtau rɨ Sises eꞌsotoꞌkasaꞌ esiꞌpʉ kopʉna Paireꞌ piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ Paireꞌ uya, “Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ kin peꞌ ɨmɨrɨ?” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 27:11">Sises uya imaimu eikʉꞌpʉ, “Ewaiꞌ, mʉkayaiꞌneꞌ kasa rɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 27:11" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 27:12" />Useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru ton uya ɨri pe, kasi pe rɨ teseruꞌtɨ aꞌtai eikʉꞌpʉ iya pen.<verse eid="MAT 27:12" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 27:13" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, Paireꞌ uya ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Eta auya pʉra peꞌ iyesi ɨri pe toꞌ usaurokʉ ɨpɨꞌ?” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 27:13" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 27:14" />Eꞌtane Sises uya tikin nan pɨꞌ rɨ toꞌ eikʉꞌpʉ pen nɨ, ɨri pe toꞌ uya tʉkuꞌtoꞌ pɨꞌ, kopʉna tewansiukaiꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 27:14" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Umaꞌtatoꞌ Pe Taꞌpʉ Toꞌ Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 15:6-15">Maꞌ 15:6-15</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 23:13-26">Ʉruꞌ 23:13-26</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 18:39-19:16">Isaan 18:39–19:16</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 27:15" />Kopʉna eseru esiꞌpʉ kaꞌpon nonkatoꞌ parikiꞌsi tapai toꞌ entaꞌnatoꞌ weyu aꞌtai anpisin ton nanʉmʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 27:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 27:16" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, tese ke teꞌsen aꞌsisaꞌ parikiꞌsi taꞌ esiꞌpʉ, Parapas tukaiꞌ tesaꞌsen. <verse eid="MAT 27:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 27:17" />Tuꞌkan kon amʉrasaꞌ aꞌtai, Paireꞌ uya toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Nai kʉrɨ rupɨ enpaꞌka uya iꞌse meꞌatʉu ɨiwanoꞌ kon pe? Parapas, mɨrɨ pe pʉra Sises, Kʉrai<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">27:17 </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Kʉrai; </char><char style="ft" closed="false">mɨrɨ pe pʉra, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">Meꞌsaya; Papa Nanʉmʉꞌpʉ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta eꞌkwa pe; v. 22 yau nɨrɨ.</char></note> tatoꞌ katɨ?” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 27:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 27:18" />Apʉne pʉra tɨkɨnta kon pɨꞌ toꞌ uya itʉsaꞌ tenaꞌ tukaiꞌ iꞌtu tʉuya pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 27:18" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 27:19" />Eseru aimenkatoꞌ apon po Paireꞌ ereutasaꞌ koroꞌtau rɨ, inoꞌpʉ uya se main ennoꞌsaꞌ esiꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ: “Ɨꞌrɨ pe kʉrɨ rɨ, ɨꞌrɨ kuꞌnin nʉꞌpʉ pen nɨ kaꞌpon kʉꞌkupʉi. Ɨri pe serɨ pe tekotaꞌmapɨꞌse eꞌneꞌpɨꞌsaꞌ man kʉrɨ rɨ uriyaꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 27:19" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 27:20" />Eꞌtane useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru ton uya kaꞌpon amʉꞌ poriꞌmaꞌpʉ toꞌ uya Parapas ekamaꞌpotoꞌ pe inonkatoꞌ pe iya, Sises maꞌtanʉkʉiꞌma.<verse eid="MAT 27:20" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MAT 27:21" />Kopʉna uya toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ, “Nai kʉrɨ kuru nonka uya iꞌse meꞌatʉu ɨyenaꞌnokon?” taꞌpʉ iya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 27:21">“Parapas,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 27:21" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MAT 27:22" />“Ɨꞌrɨ pe ken si Sises, Kʉrai tatoꞌ ipɨꞌ kupʉ uya?” tukaiꞌ Paireꞌ uya toꞌ ekamaꞌpoꞌpʉ.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 27:22">Tanporon kon uya imaimu eikʉꞌpʉ, “Kurusuꞌ pona ipokapɨꞌkɨ!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 27:22" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MAT 27:23" />“Ɨꞌrɨtoꞌ pe? Ɨꞌrɨ ɨri kuꞌsaꞌ iya?” taꞌpʉ Paireꞌ uya.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="MAT 27:23">Eꞌtane eke pe kuru toꞌ ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnpɨtʉꞌpʉ, “Kurusuꞌ pona ipokapɨꞌkɨ!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 27:23" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MAT 27:24" />Paireꞌ uya eneꞌpʉ ɨꞌrɨ pe ikuꞌtoꞌ iya awɨrɨ pʉra rɨ, eꞌtane ɨsɨ pe rɨ toꞌ ena esiꞌpʉ. Tuna anʉmʉꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan isemiyakʉꞌpʉ tuꞌkan kon rau esiiꞌma. “Tʉmakooi ke pʉra esi serɨ pʉse rɨ kaꞌpon mʉnʉ pɨꞌ. Ɨyenauꞌnokon nɨ iyesi mɨrɨ!” taꞌpʉ iya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:24 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 21:6-9">Isuꞌtaronomi 21:6-9</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 27:24" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MAT 27:25" />Tanporon kon uya imaimu eikʉꞌpʉ, “Tɨwɨ ina mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ina munkɨ amʉꞌ iwanoꞌ pe imʉnʉ nesii!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 27:25" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MAT 27:26" />Mɨrɨpan uya Parapas nonkaꞌpʉ toꞌ enaꞌ, eꞌtane ariꞌpoꞌpɨꞌtoꞌ pe Sises kupʉꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itʉrʉꞌpʉ iya kurusuꞌ pona toꞌ uya ipokapɨꞌtoꞌ pe.<verse eid="MAT 27:26" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Sapemaꞌpʉ Soisa Amʉꞌ Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 15:16-21">Maꞌ 15:16-21</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 19:2-3">Isaan 19:2-3</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MAT 27:27" />Kopʉna soisaai amʉꞌ uya si Sises arɨꞌpʉ kopʉna pe eꞌnɨ iwʉꞌ taꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon uya tuꞌkan kon nɨ soisa amʉꞌ amʉranʉkʉꞌpʉ Sises woi. <verse eid="MAT 27:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="MAT 27:28" />Toꞌ uya iponkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan tʉtariren pon ke toꞌ uya ipontɨꞌpʉ, <verse eid="MAT 27:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="MAT 27:29" />mɨrɨpan kon uya tikʉ ke teꞌsen eꞌmepɨtʉꞌpʉ aroꞌ, kʉron pe, mɨrɨpan ke toꞌ uya arʉkoꞌtɨꞌpʉ. Toꞌ uya iyɨɨiꞌtɨꞌpʉ itenwoꞌnetʉ winon itemiyatʉ yaꞌ, mɨrɨpan kon eꞌsekunkapɨtʉꞌpʉ irau, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ toꞌ uya isapemaꞌpʉ. “Miyarɨ, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ kin!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya Sises pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 27:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="MAT 27:30" />Toꞌ etaꞌtapɨtʉꞌpʉ ipona; itɨɨi moꞌkaꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, mɨrɨ ke toꞌ uya iꞌpai wɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 27:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="MAT 27:31" />Isapema tʉpo, toꞌ uya iponkaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan pontɨꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipon yaꞌ, mɨrɨpan arɨꞌpʉ toꞌ uya kurusuꞌ pona ipokapɨꞌseꞌna.<verse eid="MAT 27:31" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Kurusuꞌ Pona Sises Pokapɨtʉꞌpʉ Toꞌ Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 15:21-32">Maꞌ 15:21-32</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 23:26-43">Ʉruꞌ 23:26-43</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 19:17-27">Isaan 19:17-27</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MAT 27:32" />Toꞌ utɨ koroꞌtau, kaꞌpon Sairini winon, Saiman iteseꞌ eporoꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, mɨrɨpan aꞌkwarʉkaꞌpʉ toꞌ uya kurusuꞌ atoꞌ pe iya. <verse eid="MAT 27:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="MAT 27:33" />Toꞌ uyeeꞌpʉ pata Korʉkoꞌta tatoꞌ yaꞌ (Puꞌpɨ Ɨꞌpʉ Rʉꞌpʉ Pata ta eꞌkwa pe). <verse eid="MAT 27:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="MAT 27:34" />Mɨrɨ yau, toꞌ uya Sises oꞌpaꞌpʉ iꞌneꞌ ke waain tisumaiꞌ. Onpasaꞌ tʉuya aꞌtai, ɨnensipai pʉra iyesiꞌpʉ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:34 </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Eren 69:21</char></note><verse eid="MAT 27:34" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="35" style="v" sid="MAT 27:35" />Kurusuꞌ pona ipokapɨꞌsaꞌ tʉuyaꞌnokon aꞌtai, ipon nʉꞌpʉ taꞌnʉkʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya teꞌwapiyaꞌkapɨꞌse,<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">27:35 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Tuꞌkan pen nɨ emennaꞌ pe imenukasaꞌ ton uya, </char><char style="fq" closed="false">itonpaꞌtɨsaꞌ iꞌtutoꞌ ipɨꞌ tawon ke puꞌkenaꞌ usaurokʉꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ utaꞌkuꞌtɨtoꞌ pe: “Upon taꞌnʉkʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya tʉkaisarɨꞌnokon teꞌwapiyaꞌkaiꞌ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ iꞌtutoꞌ ipɨꞌ tenoꞌmapɨꞌse upon anʉmʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya” </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ta (Eren 22:18).</char></note> <verse eid="MAT 27:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="MAT 27:36" />mɨrɨpan kon ereutaꞌpʉ enpɨꞌseꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 27:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="MAT 27:37" />Iwɨtoꞌ iwenai menukasaꞌ pokaꞌpʉ toꞌ uya iꞌpai epoi; <char style="sc">sises pʉse rɨ, esuwerʉ amʉꞌ kin,</char> tawon. <verse eid="MAT 27:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="MAT 27:38" />Asaꞌron kon amaꞌ rʉꞌsan pokapɨtʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya ipokon pe; tikin nɨ itenwoꞌnetʉ winɨ mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ ikamisi winɨ tikin nɨ.<verse eid="MAT 27:38" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="39" style="v" sid="MAT 27:39" />Kamoro ipiyawɨrɨ tʉutɨsan uya ɨri pe isapemaꞌpʉ, tiꞌpai kon sʉkʉsʉkʉmaꞌpʉ toꞌ uya,<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:39 </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Eren 22:7; 109:25; <ref loc="SIR 12:17-18">Sairaꞌ 12:17-18</ref>; <ref loc="SIR 13:7">13:7</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 27:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="MAT 27:40" />mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya, “Ɨmɨrɨ, useꞌman nɨtoꞌ, ɨpʉreman nɨtoꞌ iwʉꞌ aꞌmorʉkanin, mɨrɨpan amɨ auya osorʉwawon wʉi yau, epikaꞌtɨꞌ! Ɨuꞌtɨkɨ kurusuꞌ poi, Papa Mumu pe ɨwesi yau!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:40 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 26:61">Maꞌsiu 26:61</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 2:19">Isaan 2:19</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 27:40" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="41" style="v" sid="MAT 27:41" />Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Main pɨꞌ enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru ton uya rɨ isapemaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 27:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="MAT 27:42" />“Tʉron kon pikaꞌtɨꞌpʉ iya, eꞌtane tiwa rɨ iyepikaꞌtɨ pʉra iyesi! Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ kin saꞌne si! Tɨwɨ si nʉuꞌtɨi kurusuꞌ poi, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ urɨꞌnokon uya apurɨtoꞌ pe. <verse eid="MAT 27:42" /><verse number="43" style="v" sid="MAT 27:43" />Papa apurɨnin kʉrɨ rɨ. Tɨwɨ Papa nʉpikaꞌtɨi iꞌse tesi yau, ‘Papa Mumu urɨ,’ tasaꞌ iya pɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:43 </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Eren 22:8; <ref loc="PRO 2:18-20">Ipuꞌketʉ 2:18-20</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 27:43" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="44" style="v" sid="MAT 27:44" />Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ iyaꞌkɨrɨ kurusuꞌ pona ipokapɨꞌsaꞌ kon uya isapemaꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 27:44" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Erikʉꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 15:33-41">Maꞌ 15:33-41</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 23:44-49">Ʉruꞌ 23:44-49</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 19:28-30">Isaan 19:28-30</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="45" style="v" sid="MAT 27:45" />12 aꞌkʉraꞌ awonsiꞌkɨ 3 aꞌkʉraꞌ pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ, tanporo rɨ pata ewarumamʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 27:45" /><verse number="46" style="v" sid="MAT 27:46" />3 aꞌkʉraꞌ aꞌtaiꞌne rɨ, Sises ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉmʉꞌpʉ, <char style="tl">“Iroi, Iroi, rama sapaꞌtani?”</char> taꞌpʉ iya, “Papa, Papa, ɨꞌrɨtoꞌ pe unonkasaꞌ auya?” ta eꞌkwa pe.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:46 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 22:1">Eren 22:1</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 27:46" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="47" style="v" sid="MAT 27:47" />Mɨrɨ yau si teꞌsotoꞌpɨꞌse teꞌsan uya serɨ etasaꞌ aꞌtai, “Iraisa kɨꞌma pɨꞌ man!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 27:47" /><verse number="48" style="v" sid="MAT 27:48" />Inke pʉra, tikin nɨ toꞌ tonpa pe teꞌsen si ekaꞌtumʉꞌpʉ mɨrɨ suꞌpa epose, waain makuꞌpɨ peneka kaꞌ ikiiꞌpʉ iya, yʉi pɨꞌ tepuꞌtɨiꞌ Sises uya ensitoꞌ pe ikupʉꞌpʉ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:48 </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Eren 69:21</char></note><verse eid="MAT 27:48" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="49" style="v" sid="MAT 27:49" />Eꞌtane tʉron kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya, “Tɨwɨ nesii. Apʉne, Iraisa uyepʉ enpaiꞌnokon ipikaꞌtɨiꞌ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 27:49" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="50" style="v" sid="MAT 27:50" />Sises kanan ukɨꞌpɨꞌnʉnkaaꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌkwarʉ tʉrʉꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 27:50" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="51" style="v" sid="MAT 27:51" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai rɨ si, Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ useꞌmatoꞌ, ɨpʉrematoꞌ itau wapu pe teꞌsen ekarakaꞌpʉ inakapu ponsiꞌkɨ non pona aꞌsaꞌmʉyai. Tʉrʉꞌpʉnʉ amʉꞌ esiꞌpʉ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tɨꞌ amʉꞌ utaꞌmorʉpɨtʉꞌpʉ.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:51 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 26:31-33">Eꞌsotas 26:31-33</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 27:51" /><verse number="52" style="v" sid="MAT 27:52" />Uruwaiꞌ amʉꞌ utaꞌkokapɨtʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan wakʉ ton kaꞌpon amʉꞌ iyeriꞌsaꞌ kon eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ kanan. <verse eid="MAT 27:52" /><verse number="53" style="v" sid="MAT 27:53" />Toꞌ nin si epaꞌkaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ uruwaiꞌ yapai. Emennʉꞌpʉ po, Sises eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkasaꞌ aꞌtai nin si, toꞌ utɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ Surusiran pona. Mɨrɨ yau, tuꞌkan kon nɨ kaꞌpon amʉꞌ uya toꞌ eneꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 27:53" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="54" style="v" sid="MAT 27:54" />Roman amʉꞌ soisaai ton epuru mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ itaꞌkɨrɨ teꞌsan itonpa ton Sises erasuntɨ pɨꞌ teꞌsan uya tʉrʉꞌpʉnʉ amʉꞌ utɨ iꞌtuꞌpʉ, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tanporon nɨ teꞌkuꞌsen eneꞌpʉ, ipan pe rɨ toꞌ etʉipɨtʉꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya, “Iꞌnapai rɨ kuru rɨ kaꞌsi, pʉse rɨ esiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ wa Papa Mumu pe!” taꞌpʉ.<verse eid="MAT 27:54" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="55" style="v" sid="MAT 27:55" />Tuꞌkan kon nɨ uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ esiꞌpʉ enpɨtʉ pɨꞌ ɨnnonsiꞌkɨ. Sises eꞌmaꞌpʉkasaꞌ toꞌ uya esiꞌpʉ Kiyarari poi, ipikaꞌtɨ pɨꞌ toꞌ esiꞌpʉ iꞌse iyeꞌtoꞌ ke. <verse eid="MAT 27:55" /><verse number="56" style="v" sid="MAT 27:56" />Toꞌ koroꞌtau Meri Mataren; Meri, Isens mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Isoseꞌ san; mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Sepiti munkɨ amʉꞌ san.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:56 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 8:2-3">Ʉruꞌ 8:2-3</ref></char></note><verse eid="MAT 27:56" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Uꞌnaꞌtɨꞌpʉ Isoseꞌ Uya</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 15:42-47">Maꞌ 15:42-47</ref>; Ʉruꞌ 23:50-56; <ref loc="JHN 19:38-42">Isaan 19:38-42</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="57" style="v" sid="MAT 27:57" />Pata ukoꞌmankapʉ koroꞌtau, imaminkeꞌ kaꞌpon, Aramaꞌtiya winon uyeeꞌpʉ. Iteseꞌ esiꞌpʉ Isoseꞌ, Sises poitorʉ pe iyenasaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 27:57" /><verse number="58" style="v" sid="MAT 27:58" />Paireꞌ piyaꞌ itɨꞌpʉ Sises ekepu ekamaꞌpose, atoꞌ pe tʉuya. Paireꞌ uya tʉsoisaai ton apiyoꞌmaꞌpʉ Sises ekepu tʉtoꞌ pe toꞌ uya itenaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 27:58" /><verse number="59" style="v" sid="MAT 27:59" />Isoseꞌ uya nin si itekepu arɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ. Iwontɨꞌpʉ iya epeꞌkenaꞌ pon renen tatoꞌ atʉ ke, <verse eid="MAT 27:59" /><verse number="60" style="v" sid="MAT 27:60" />mɨrɨpan uya Sises ekepu nonkaꞌpʉ tiwanoꞌ pe emennaꞌ pe tɨꞌ akasaꞌ uruwaiꞌ pe yaꞌ. Eke rɨ tɨꞌ tʉtɨrinkaiꞌ imʉraꞌtaai aꞌkoroꞌpʉ iya, mɨrɨpan nin si utɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ yapai. <verse eid="MAT 27:60" /><verse number="61" style="v" sid="MAT 27:61" />Meri Mataren mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉron nɨ Meri ereutasaꞌ esiꞌpʉ tɨꞌ akasaꞌ uruwaiꞌ pe ratoi pe.<verse eid="MAT 27:61" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Uruwaiꞌ Erasuntɨnin</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="62" style="v" sid="MAT 27:62" />Mɨrɨ emaꞌsaꞌ yau, Sapaꞌ aꞌtai, Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton, Pariꞌsi amʉꞌ utɨꞌpʉ Paireꞌ piyaꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 27:62" /><verse number="63" style="v" sid="MAT 27:63" />“Ina epuru, kʉrɨ Sises kasi yeꞌ esi aꞌtai serɨ yau nurɨne isaurokʉꞌpʉ esi ina enu yau, ‘Osorʉwau wʉi pataꞌpʉ pe eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkatoꞌ oton,’ tawon.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">27:63 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 16:21">Maꞌsiu 16:21</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 17:23">17:23</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 20:19">20:19</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 8:31">Maꞌ 8:31</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 9:31">9:31</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 10:33-34">10:33-34</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 9:22">Ʉruꞌ 9:22</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 18:31-33">18:31-33</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 27:63" /><verse number="64" style="v" sid="MAT 27:64" />Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, ɨsoisaai ton apiyoꞌmaꞌ iuruwasii erasuntɨtoꞌ pe toꞌ uya serɨ awonsiꞌkɨ osorʉwau wʉi pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ imaꞌtaꞌpʉ awonsiꞌkɨ. Mɨrɨ pʉra nin iyesi yau, ipoitorʉ ton uyepʉ mɨrɨ itekepu onanseꞌna, mɨrɨpan aꞌtai nin si kaꞌpon amʉꞌ pɨꞌ, ‘Sises eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkakaaꞌpʉ man,’ ta toꞌ uya mɨrɨ. Serɨ nin si eꞌkuꞌsaꞌ aꞌtai, wapiya iyesiꞌpʉ entai rɨ nin si ennakan nɨtoꞌ eꞌtoꞌ oton mɨrɨ ipan pe rɨ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya.<verse eid="MAT 27:64" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="65" style="v" sid="MAT 27:65" />“Ayaꞌkɨrɨꞌnokon si usoisaai ton atɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ Paireꞌ uya. “Entantɨꞌ, wakʉ pe uruwaiꞌ erasuntɨtantɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ iya. <verse eid="MAT 27:65" /><verse number="66" style="v" sid="MAT 27:66" />Mɨrɨpan kon nin si utɨꞌpʉ mɨrɨ uruwaiꞌ piyaꞌ erasuntɨseꞌna. Toꞌ uya aꞌsiꞌpɨtʉꞌpʉ wakʉ pe tɨꞌ pɨꞌ. Mɨrɨ tʉpo nin si, soisa amʉꞌ uya erasuntɨtoꞌ pe toꞌ uya ikupʉꞌpʉ mɨrɨ.<verse eid="MAT 27:66" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 27" />
  <chapter number="28" style="c" sid="MAT 28" />
  <para style="s1">Sises Eꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 16:1-10">Maꞌ 16:1-10</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 24:1-12">Ʉruꞌ 24:1-12</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 20:1-10">Isaan 20:1-10</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MAT 28:1" />Awanakʉiꞌ kuru rɨ nin si, suntaaka epiyaꞌtɨ pe, Sapaꞌ emaꞌsaꞌ yau, Meri Mataren mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ tʉron nɨ Meri utɨꞌpʉ Sises uruwasii tɨꞌ akasaꞌ enseꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 28:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="MAT 28:2" />Mɨrɨ aꞌtai, ɨsɨ pe tʉrʉꞌpʉnʉ esiꞌpʉ, apʉne pʉra Itepuru inserʉʉi uꞌtɨ esiꞌpʉ Epʉn poi. Tɨꞌ akasaꞌ uruwaiꞌ piyaꞌ itɨꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya tɨꞌ amaꞌpʉ imʉraꞌtaai apai, mɨrɨpan po iyereutaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 28:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="MAT 28:3" />Sirɨn pe iyesiꞌpʉ kamiriꞌ kasa. Ipon esiꞌpʉ ipan pe rɨ aimuꞌne, sino kasa. <verse eid="MAT 28:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="MAT 28:4" />Erasuntɨ pɨꞌ si teꞌsan soisa amʉꞌ etʉipɨtʉꞌpʉ ipɨꞌ ipan pe, mɨrɨpan kon eꞌtɨtɨtɨꞌkaꞌpʉ toꞌ utaꞌmoꞌkaꞌpʉ iyeriꞌsaꞌ kon kasa.<verse eid="MAT 28:4" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MAT 28:5" />Uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ pɨꞌ inserʉ uya, “Kenariꞌnʉntʉu! Sises, toꞌ nʉpokapɨtʉꞌpʉ kurusuꞌ pona warinpa auyaꞌnokon tukaiꞌ siꞌtuyaiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 28:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="MAT 28:6" />Eꞌtane ipʉra man serɨ yau. Iyeꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkaꞌpʉ taꞌpʉ tʉuya kasa rɨ. Apʉne, ipataꞌpʉ entanʉꞌtɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 28:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="MAT 28:7" />Inke pʉra ipoitorʉ ton ipanaꞌtɨtantɨꞌ: ‘Iyeꞌmʉꞌsaꞌkasaꞌ man terikʉꞌpʉ apai, mɨrɨpan utɨn pɨꞌ man arawɨrɨꞌnokon Kiyarari pona. Mɨrɨ yau ene auyaꞌnokon mɨrɨ.’ Apanaꞌtɨsaꞌ uya ꞌnokon si mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ inserʉ uya.<verse eid="MAT 28:7" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MAT 28:8" />Kamoro si uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ ennaꞌpoꞌpʉ mɨrɨ uruwaiꞌ piyapai toꞌ etʉipɨꞌsaꞌ esiꞌpʉ eꞌtane ipan pe rɨ kanan toꞌ esiꞌpʉ poriꞌ pe, mɨrɨpan kon utɨꞌpʉ tekaꞌtunse ipoitorʉ ton panaꞌtɨseꞌna. <verse eid="MAT 28:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="MAT 28:9" />Iteꞌkwanau pʉra rɨ, Sises uya toꞌ eporoꞌpʉ, mɨrɨpan uya, “Miyarɨꞌnokon!” taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ. Toꞌ utɨꞌpʉ ipiyaꞌ iꞌta pɨꞌ tʉutaꞌsiiꞌ, toꞌ uya apurɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 28:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="MAT 28:10" />“Kenariꞌnʉntʉu!” taꞌpʉ Sises uya toꞌ pɨꞌ. “Utonpa ton pɨꞌ Kiyarari pona entantɨꞌ kaꞌtantɨꞌ; mɨrɨ yau nin si toꞌ uya uyene mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya.<verse eid="MAT 28:10" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Erasu Ton Nekamaꞌpʉ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MAT 28:11" />Utɨn pɨꞌ rɨ uriꞌsamiꞌsi amʉꞌ eꞌtane, Sises uruwasii erasuntɨnin nan soisa amʉꞌ utɨꞌpʉ Surusiran pona, mɨrɨpan kon uya tanporo rɨ iyeꞌkuꞌsaꞌ rʉꞌpʉ ekamaꞌpʉ Papa enaꞌ useꞌman nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 28:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="MAT 28:12" />Kamoro si Papa enaꞌ useꞌma nɨtoꞌ tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru eꞌseposaꞌ aꞌtai Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ epuru ton pokon pe, toꞌ ekonekaꞌpʉ mɨrɨ kuꞌtoꞌ kon pe tukaiꞌ. Soisa amʉꞌ enaꞌ eke pe rɨ pʉrata tʉrʉꞌpʉ toꞌ uya. <verse eid="MAT 28:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="MAT 28:13" />“Se mɨkatʉiꞌ, ‘Ina eꞌnʉntane, ewarupɨ nau, Sises poitorʉ ton uya itekepu arɨꞌpʉ,’ mɨkatʉiꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 28:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="MAT 28:14" />Serɨ etasaꞌ kopʉna uya yau, ɨkotaꞌma iya ꞌnokon namaiꞌ ina uya auroꞌka mɨrɨ,” taꞌpʉ toꞌ uya toꞌ pɨꞌ. <verse eid="MAT 28:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="MAT 28:15" />Soisa amʉꞌ uya nin si pʉrata aꞌsiꞌpʉ mɨrɨ; kamoro uya mɨrɨ kasa meꞌtʉiꞌ tasaꞌ awɨrɨ rɨ toꞌ uya ikupʉꞌpʉ. Mɨrɨ uriyaꞌ, siya rɨ serɨ panton utɨsaꞌ mɨrɨ Esuwerʉ amʉꞌ koroꞌtau rɨ serɨ pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ.<verse eid="MAT 28:15" /></para>
  <para style="s1">Sises Usenpoikaꞌpʉ Tʉpoitorʉ Ton Piyaꞌ</para>
  <para style="r">(<ref loc="MRK 16:14-18">Maꞌ 16:14-18</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 24:36-49">Ʉruꞌ 24:36-49</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 20:19-23">Isaan 20:19-23</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 1:6-8">Inkupʉꞌpʉ 1:6-8</ref>)</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MAT 28:16" />Mɨrɨ pataꞌpʉ pe, 11 kaisaron kon ipoitorʉ ton utɨꞌpʉ Kiyarari pona, wʉꞌ pona, Sises uya, “Mɨrɨ yaꞌ entantɨꞌ,” taꞌpʉ rʉꞌpʉ pona.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">28:16 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 26:32">Maꞌsiu 26:32</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 14:28">Maꞌ 14:28</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 28:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="MAT 28:17" />Toꞌ uya ensaꞌ aꞌtai, toꞌ uya apurɨpɨtʉꞌpʉ, eꞌtane tʉron kon uya ikasimaꞌpʉ. <verse eid="MAT 28:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="MAT 28:18" />Sises uyeeꞌpʉ toꞌ piyaꞌ, mɨrɨpan uya taꞌpʉ toꞌ pɨꞌ, “Umeruntɨrʉ ke urepasaꞌ man tanporon nɨ Epʉn mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ non poron kon nɨ esaꞌ pe eꞌtoꞌ pe. <verse eid="MAT 28:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="MAT 28:19" />Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨꞌ, siya rɨ entantɨꞌ tanporon kon kaꞌpon amʉꞌ ikonekatantɨꞌ upoitorʉ pe toꞌ eꞌtoꞌ pe. Toꞌ ipaꞌtaisimatantɨꞌ ikʉipʉnʉ, imu, mɨrɨ awonsiꞌkɨ Wakʉ Aꞌkwarʉ eseꞌ yau.<note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">28:19 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 1:8">Inkupʉꞌpʉ 1:8</ref></char></note> <verse eid="MAT 28:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="MAT 28:20" />Toꞌ menupatʉiꞌ tanporon nɨ ayauroꞌkaꞌpʉ uya ꞌnokon awɨron pe toꞌ eꞌtoꞌ pe. Iꞌnapai rɨ kuru rɨ ɨpiyauꞌnokon esi iweyu uꞌmatʉ pʉꞌkʉ pona rɨ,” taꞌpʉ iya toꞌ pɨꞌ.<verse eid="MAT 28:20" /></para>
  <chapter eid="MAT 28" />
</usx>